definition: The type of personal information verified through the Personal Information Verification evidence.

name: Personal Information Verification
definition: The evidence by which a persons name, address, date of birth, etc. is confirmed.

name: Student Identification System
definition: A coding scheme that is used for identification and record-keeping purposes by schools, social services, or other agencies to refer to a student.

name: Student Identifier
definition: A unique number or alphanumeric code assigned to a student by a school, school system, a state, or other agency or entity.
use_case: K-12 -> High School Generated Transcript K-12 -> LEA-to-LEA Student Record Exchange K-12 -> LEA-to-SEA Student Record Exchange K-12 -> Teacher-Student Data Link -> Enrollment Postsecondary Education -> Transition
usage_notes:
CEDS "Identifier" elements reflect the intent of the XSD:Token format, i.e. a string in which carriage return, line feed, and tab characters have been removed as well as any internal sequences of two or more spaces and any leading or trailing spaces.

An Identifier MAY be a Universally Unique Identifier (UUID) / Globally Unique Identifier (GUID), i.e.128-bit unique identifiers generated according to the algorithms and encoding standards of RFC 4122.

name: ISO 639-2 Language Code
definition: The code for the specific language or dialect that a person uses to communicate.
use_case: Early Learning -> Program Compliance Early Learning -> Program Entry Early Learning -> Staff Quality Early Learning -> Workforce Development K-12 -> EDFacts
usage_notes: The CEDS ISO 639-2 Language Code option set comes from the ISO 639-2 standard, the character encoding in ISO 8859-1 download. Discontinued codes from the ISO standard are not included in the CEDS list.

name: ISO 639-3 Language Code
definition: The code for the specific language or dialect that a person uses to communicate.
usage_notes: The CEDS ISO 639-3 Language Code option set comes from the ISO 639-3 standard, the Latin-1 download. Only living language code types from the ISO standard are included in the CEDS list. Special scope and discontinued codes are excluded.

name: ISO 639-5 Language Family
definition: A code for a specific language family, which supplements the language groups and families in the ISO 639-2 Language Code.
usage_notes: The CEDS ISO 639-5 Language Family option set comes from the ISO 639-5 standard.

name: Language Type
definition: An indication of the function and context in which a person uses a language to communicate.

name: Application Date
definition: The year, month and day on which an individual  application is received by the organization.

name: Career Cluster
definition: The career cluster that defines the industry or occupational focus which may be associated with a career pathways program, plan of study, or course.
usage_notes: Options from O*NET OnLine an application that was created for the general public to provide broad access to the O*NET database of occupational information. O*NET OnLine offers a variety of search options and occupational data, while My Next Move is a streamlined application for students and job seekers. Both applications were developed for the U.S. Department of Labor by the National Center for O*NET Development.  See onetonline.org for more information.

name: Career Pathways Program Participation Exit Date
definition: The year, month and day on which the person ceased to participate in a program.
usage_notes: All CEDS Exit and End Dates represent the last day of the date range specified, such as the last day that a person was enrolled, participated, or received services.

name: Career Pathways Program Participation Indicator
definition: An indication of an individual who is participating in a program that is a component of or leads to a specific or recognized career pathway, as defined by the state.

name: Career Pathways Program Participation Start Date
definition: The year, month and day on which the person began to participate in a career pathway program.

name: Career and Technical Education Concentrator
definition: An indication of a student who has met the state-defined threshold of career and technical education concentrators, as defined in the State's approved Perkins IV State Plan.
use_case: K-12 -> EDFacts K-12 -> High School Generated Transcript K-12 -> LEA-to-LEA Student Record Exchange K-12 -> LEA-to-SEA Student Record Exchange

name: Career and Technical Education Participant
definition: An indication a student has met the state-defined threshold of Career and Technical Education participation as defined in the State's approved Perkins IV State Plan.
use_case: K-12 -> EDFacts

name: Career-Technical-Adult Education Displaced Homemaker Indicator
definition: A person who ; (A) (i) has worked primarily without remuneration to care for a home and family, and for that reason has diminished marketable skills;    (ii) has been dependent on the income of another family member but is no longer supported by that income; or    (iii) is a parent whose youngest dependent child will become ineligible to receive assistance under part A of title IV of the Social Security Act (42 U.S.C. 601 et seq.) not later than 2 years after the date on which the parent applies for assistance under such title; and (B)   is unemployed or underemployed and is experiencing difficulty in obtaining or upgrading employment.
use_case: K-12 -> EDFacts

name: Classification of Instructional Program Code
definition: A six-digit code in the form xx.xxxx that identifies instructional program specialties within educational institutions.
use_case: K-12 -> High School Feedback Report Postsecondary Education -> Complete College America Postsecondary Education -> IPEDS Postsecondary Education -> Transition

name: Out of Workforce Indicator
definition: An individual: (A) who is a displaced homemaker, as defined in section 3 of the Workforce Innovation and Opportunity Act (29 U.S.C. 3102); or (B) who (i)(I) has worked primarily without remuneration to care for a home and family, and for that reason has diminished marketable skills; or (II) is a parent whose youngest dependent child will become ineligible to receive assistance under part A of title IV of the Social Security Act (42 U.S.C. 601 et seq.) not later than 2 years after the date on which the parent applies for assistance under such title; and (ii) is unemployed or underemployed and is experiencing difficulty in obtaining or upgrading employment.

name: Program Entry Reason
definition: The documented or assumed reason a person is being served by a program.

name: Program Participation Exit Date
definition: The year, month and day on which the person ceased to participate in a program.

name: Role

name: Single Parent or Single Pregnant Woman Status
definition: A student who, at some time during the school year, is either a pregnant female student who is unmarried; or a male or female student who is unmarried or legally separated from a spouse and has a minor child or children.
use_case: K-12 -> EDFacts Persistence and Attainment of Nontraditional Students

name: Work-based Learning Opportunity Type
definition: The type of work-based learning opportunity a student participated in.

name: Person Relationship Type
definition: The nature of a person's relationship to another person.
use_case: K-12 -> Migrant Student Data Exchange
usage_notes: For implementation in the CEDS Integrated Data Store (IDS), the "person" in the description would be the person referred to in the PersonId column in the IDS. The "related person" in the description would be the person referred to in the "RelatedPersonId" in the IDS. Example: Foster mother - The person (PersonId) is the related person's (RelatedPersonId) Foster mother.

name: Awaiting Foster Care Status
definition: An indication of whether this child is awaiting foster care.

name: Career Technical Education Nontraditional Gender Status
definition: An indication of whether CTE participants were members of an underrepresented gender group (where one gender comprises less than 25 percent of the persons employed in those occupations or field of work).
use_case: K-12 -> EDFacts

name: Public Assistance Status
definition: A person who receives financial assistance from Federal, State, or local government agencies, including Temporary Assistance for Needy Families or equivalent.

name: Additional Credit Type
definition: The type of credits or units of value available for the completion of a course in addition to Carnegie Units.

name: Available Carnegie Unit Credit
definition: Measured in Carnegie units, the amount of credit available to a student who successfully meets the objectives of the course. A course meeting every day for one period of the school day over the span of a school year offers one Carnegie unit. A Carnegie unit is thus a measure of "seat time" rather than a measure of attainment of the course objectives.

name: Course Title
definition: The descriptive name given to a course of study offered in a school or other institution or organization. In departmentalized classes at the elementary, secondary, and postsecondary levels (and for staff development activities), this refers to the name by which a course is identified (e.g., American History, English III). For elementary and other non-departmentalized classes, it refers to any portion of the instruction for which a grade or report is assigned (e.g., reading, composition, spelling, and language arts).

definition: The five-digit SCED code. The first two-digits of the code represent the Course Subject Area and the next three digits identify the course number. name: School Courses for the Exchange of Data Sequence of Course
definition: Where a specific course lies when it is part of a consecutive sequence of courses. This element should be interpreted as "part 'n' of 'm' parts.

definition: The amount of credit available to the student who successfully meets the objectives of the course or learning opportunity based on the units defined by Credit Unit Type.
use_case: Postsecondary Education -> Transition
format: Numeric - up to 2 digits after decimal place
usage_notes: For K-12 a course meeting every day for one period of the school day over the span of a school year typically offers one Carnegie unit. In this case a Carnegie unit is  a measure of "seat time" rather than a measure of attainment of the course objectives.

name: High School Course Requirement
definition: An indication that this course credit is required for a high school diploma.
use_case: K-12 -> High School Generated Transcript K-12 -> LEA-to-LEA Student Record Exchange K-12 -> LEA-to-SEA Student Record Exchange K-12 -> Teacher-Student Data Link -> Class Section

name: NCES College Course Map Code
definition: A taxonomy system for coding postsecondary courses in NCES research studies.

name: Postsecondary Course Title
definition: The name or title of the course taken by a student at an academic institution.
use_case: Postsecondary Education -> Transition

name: Related Competency Definitions
definition: An indication of the competency definition(s) addressed in the Course Section.
alternate_name: Related Learning Standard Items, Related Competency Items

name: School Courses for the Exchange of Data Sequence of Course
definition: Where a specific course lies when it is part of a consecutive sequence of courses. This element should be interpreted as "part 'n' of 'm' parts.
use_case: K-12 -> High School Generated Transcript K-12 -> LEA-to-LEA Student Record Exchange K-12 -> LEA-to-SEA Student Record Exchange K-12 -> Teacher-Student Data Link -> Class Section
usage_notes: For example: if a school offers 4 years of Theater, Theater 3 within this school would be indicated in the sequence elements as 3 4, denoting the 3rd part of a 4-part sequence of courses.

name: Course Academic Grade
definition: The final grade awarded for participation in the course.
use_case: K-12 -> High School Feedback Report Postsecondary Education -> Transition

name: Course Add Date
definition: The date an individual was added to an academic course at a school.

name: Course Drop Date
definition: The date on which the individual drops or withdraws from the course.
use_case: Postsecondary Education -> Student Achievement Measure

name: Course Override School
definition: The school where the credit was earned if different from the institution reporting.
use_case: Postsecondary Education -> Transition

name: Course Quality Points Earned
definition: The numerical value assigned to a letter grade to provide a basis of quantitative determination of an average.
use_case: Postsecondary Education -> Transition
format: Numeric - up to 2 digits after decimal place

name: Degree Applicability
definition: An indication that the course is a part of a degree program.
use_case: Postsecondary Education -> Transition

name: Enrollment Capacity
definition: Maximum number of age-appropriate students who can be enrolled.
usage_notes: Enrollment capacity can be collected at a variety of levels, such as classroom, grade, school, and facility.

name: Number of Credits Earned
definition: The number of credits an individual earns by the successful completion of a course.
use_case: K-12 -> High School Feedback Report K-12 -> High School Generated Transcript K-12 -> LEA-to-LEA Student Record Exchange K-12 -> LEA-to-SEA Student Record Exchange Postsecondary Education -> Transition
format: Numeric - up to 2 digits after decimal place

name: Student Course Section Grade Earned
definition: A final indicator of student performance in a course section as submitted by the instructor.
use_case: K-12 -> High School Generated Transcript K-12 -> LEA-to-LEA Student Record Exchange K-12 -> LEA-to-SEA Student Record Exchange

name: Student Course Section Grade Narrative
definition: The narrative of the student performance in a course section as submitted by the instructor.

name: Student Identification System
definition: A coding scheme that is used for identification and record-keeping purposes by schools, social services, or other agencies to refer to a student.
use_case: K-12 -> High School Generated Transcript K-12 -> LEA-to-LEA Student Record Exchange K-12 -> LEA-to-SEA Student Record Exchange K-12 -> Teacher-Student Data Link -> Enrollment Postsecondary Education -> Transition

name: Student Identifier
definition: A unique number or alphanumeric code assigned to a student by a school, school system, a state, or other agency or entity.
use_case: K-12 -> High School Generated Transcript K-12 -> LEA-to-LEA Student Record Exchange K-12 -> LEA-to-SEA Student Record Exchange K-12 -> Teacher-Student Data Link -> Enrollment Postsecondary Education -> Transition
usage_notes:
CEDS "Identifier" elements reflect the intent of the XSD:Token format, i.e. a string in which carriage return, line feed, and tab characters have been removed as well as any internal sequences of two or more spaces and any leading or trailing spaces.

An Identifier MAY be a Universally Unique Identifier (UUID) / Globally Unique Identifier (GUID), i.e.128-bit unique identifiers generated according to the algorithms and encoding standards of RFC 4122.

name: Course Academic Grade Status Code
definition: Additional information regarding the context of the given grade.

name: Grade Value Qualifier
definition: The scale of equivalents, if applicable, for grades awarded as indicators of performance in schoolwork. For example, numerical equivalents for letter grades used in determining a student's Grade Point Average (A=4, B=3, C=2, D=1 in a four-point system) or letter equivalents for percentage grades (90-100%=A, 80-90%=B, etc.)
usage_notes: A list of "Academic Grade Qualifiers" is available from the Association of American Medical Colleges, 2450 N St., N.W., Washington, DC 20037

name: Marking Period Name
definition: The name or description of the marking period (e.g., fall, first marking period).
use_case: K-12 -> High School Generated Transcript K-12 -> LEA-to-LEA Student Record Exchange K-12 -> LEA-to-SEA Student Record Exchange

name: Mid Term Mark
definition: Indicator of student performance at the mid-point of the marking period.
use_case: K-12 -> High School Generated Transcript K-12 -> LEA-to-LEA Student Record Exchange K-12 -> LEA-to-SEA Student Record Exchange

name: Student Course Section Grade Earned
definition: A final indicator of student performance in a course section as submitted by the instructor.
use_case: K-12 -> High School Generated Transcript K-12 -> LEA-to-LEA Student Record Exchange K-12 -> LEA-to-SEA Student Record Exchange

name: Student Course Section Mark Final Indicator
definition: Indicates that the mark is a final mark the learner has earned for the course section.

name: Assignment End Date
definition: The last year, month and day on which the assignment is valid.
usage_notes: All CEDS Exit and End Dates represent the last day of the date range specified, such as the last day that a person was enrolled, participated, or received services.

name: Assignment Start Date
definition: The year, month and day from which the assignment is valid.

name: Classroom Position Type
definition: The type of position the staff member holds in the specific course section.

name: Staff Member Identification System
definition: A coding scheme that is used for identification and record-keeping purposes by schools, social services, registry, or other agencies to refer to a staff member.
use_case: Early Learning -> Staff Quality K-12 -> LEA-to-LEA Student Record Exchange K-12 -> LEA-to-SEA Student Record Exchange K-12 -> Teacher Compensation Survey K-12 -> Teacher-Student Data Link -> Staff Assignment

name: Staff Member Identifier
definition: A unique number or alphanumeric code assigned to a staff member by a school, school system, a state, registry, or other agency or entity.
use_case: Early Learning -> Staff Quality K-12 -> LEA-to-LEA Student Record Exchange K-12 -> LEA-to-SEA Student Record Exchange K-12 -> Teacher Compensation Survey K-12 -> Teacher-Student Data Link -> Staff Assignment Postsecondary Education -> IPEDS -> HR
usage_notes:
CEDS "Identifier" elements reflect the intent of the XSD:Token format, i.e. a string in which carriage return, line feed, and tab characters have been removed as well as any internal sequences of two or more spaces and any leading or trailing spaces.

An Identifier MAY be a Universally Unique Identifier (UUID) / Globally Unique Identifier (GUID), i.e.128-bit unique identifiers generated according to the algorithms and encoding standards of RFC 4122.

name: Teacher of Record
definition: Staff member who has a Teacher of Record responsibility for a Class Section based upon the state's definition of Teacher of Record.
use_case: K-12 -> Teacher-Student Data Link -> Staff Assignment
usage_notes: There is usually one Teacher of Record assignment in a Class Section except in the case of co-teaching/team-teaching.

name: Teaching Assignment Contribution Percentage
definition: A percentage used to weight the educator's assigned responsibility for student learning in a Class Section, particularly when more than one educator is assigned to the class section.
use_case: K-12 -> Teacher-Student Data Link -> Staff Assignment
format: Numeric - up to 3 digits before and 2 digits after decimal place

name: Teaching Assignment Role
definition: The role that the Staff Member has been assigned for a Class Section.  (A teacher may have the lead responsibility for one section and serve a supporting role for another section of the same course.)
use_case: K-12 -> Teacher-Student Data Link -> Staff Assignment

name: Ability Grouping Status
definition: An indication of whether the school has students who are ability grouped for classroom instruction in mathematics or English/reading/language arts.
use_case: K-12 -> Civil Rights Data Collection

name: Additional Credit Type
definition: The type of credits or units of value available for the completion of a course in addition to Carnegie Units.

name: Adjusted Capacity
definition: The maximum number of participants that can be served in a program.

name: Adjusted Capacity Reason Type
definition: Identifies the reason for adjusted capacity in a program.

name: Advanced Placement Course Code
definition: Course areas for advanced placement or credit.  For a list of codes see http://apcentral.collegeboard.com/apc/public/courses/teachers_corner/index.html .

name: Blended Learning Model Type
definition: A type of formal education program in which a student learns at least in part through online learning, with some element of student control over time, place, path, and/or pace; at least in part in a supervised brick-and-mortar location away from home; and the modalities along each student’s learning path within a course or subject are connected to provide an integrated learning experience.
usage_notes: This may be an attribute of a Course (as designed) or a Class Section (as delivered). It also may be attributed to a school, institution, or program for "whole-school" blended models.

name: Career Cluster
definition: The career cluster that defines the industry or occupational focus which may be associated with a career pathways program, plan of study, or course.
usage_notes: Options from O*NET OnLine an application that was created for the general public to provide broad access to the O*NET database of occupational information. O*NET OnLine offers a variety of search options and occupational data, while My Next Move is a streamlined application for students and job seekers. Both applications were developed for the U.S. Department of Labor by the National Center for O*NET Development.  See onetonline.org for more information.

name: Class Beginning Time
definition: An indication of the time of day the class begins.
use_case: Early Learning -> Access to Services Early Learning -> Program Quality

name: Class Ending Time
definition: An indication of the time of day the class ends.
use_case: Early Learning -> Access to Services Early Learning -> Program Quality

name: Class Meeting Days
definition: The day(s) of the week (e.g., Monday, Wednesday) that the class meets or an indication that a class meets "out-of-school" or "self-paced".

name: Class Period
definition: An indication of the portion of a typical daily session in which students receive instruction in a specified subject (e.g., morning, sixth period, block period, or AB schedules).

name: Classroom Identifier
definition: A unique number or alphanumeric code assigned to a room by a school, school system, state, or other agency or entity.
usage_notes:
CEDS "Identifier" elements reflect the intent of the XSD:Token format, i.e. a string in which carriage return, line feed, and tab characters have been removed as well as any internal sequences of two or more spaces and any leading or trailing spaces.

An Identifier MAY be a Universally Unique Identifier (UUID) / Globally Unique Identifier (GUID), i.e.128-bit unique identifiers generated according to the algorithms and encoding standards of RFC 4122.

name: Classroom Position Type
definition: The type of position the staff member holds in the specific course section.

name: Course Academic Grade Scale Code
definition: The grading scale used by an academic educational institution for an academic course.
usage_notes: Based on the American Medical Colleges Admissions Services (AMCAS) grade scale, values 01 through 99. See Appendix E of the PESC XML High School Transcript Implementation Guide for a complete list of code values. 3-digit values (500 and above) established in earlier versions of the standard for miscellaneous grades are deprecated.

name: Course Aligned with Standards
definition: An indication whether a course is aligned with the established standards of a curriculum framework.

name: Course Applicable Education Level
definition: The education level, grade level or primary instructional level at which a course is intended.
usage_notes: This element is repeatable for most use cases.  Examples: (1.) SCED identifiers may specify a grade span of two or more grades.  (2) A postsecondary course designed to qualify a student for an associates degree and professional certification could be repeated with both of those options.

name: Course Certification Description
definition: A description of the certification or recognition associated with this course (ex. Networking, CAD, etc.)

name: Course Credit Basis Type
definition: The type of enrollment associated with the credit hours for the course.

name: Course Credit Level Type
definition: The level of credit associated with the credit hours earned for the course.

name: Course Description
definition: A description of the course content and/or goals. Reference may be made to state or national content standards.

name: Course Funding Program
definition: A program through which the course is funded.
usage_notes: This may be a program targeted to a specific student population (e.g. SPED, ESOL) and the funding guidelines may specify that all or some of the students in the course are members of the subgroup.

name: Course Grade Point Average Applicability
definition: An indicator of whether or not this course being described is included in the computation of the student’s Grade Point Average (GPA).
use_case: K-12 -> High School Generated Transcript K-12 -> LEA-to-LEA Student Record Exchange K-12 -> LEA-to-SEA Student Record Exchange K-12 -> Teacher-Student Data Link -> Class Section

name: Course Honors Type
definition: An indication that the course is or can be counted as an honors course.

name: Course Instruction Method
definition: The primary method of instruction used for the course.

name: Course Instruction Site Name
definition: The name of the location at which the course is taught.

name: Course Instruction Site Type
definition: An indication of the type of location at which the course is taught.

name: Course Interaction Mode
definition: The primary type of interaction, synchronous or asynchronous, defined for the course.
usage_notes: This may be an attribute of a Course (as designed) or an instance of a Class Section (as delivered).

name: Course Level Type
definition: The level of work which is reflected in the credits associated with the academic course being described or the level of the typical individual taking the academic course.

name: Course Narrative Explanation Grade
definition: The narrative of the grade awarded to an individual in an academic course in those cases where a course does not receive a letter or numeric grade included in the grading scale of the Course Academic Grade Qualifier.

name: Course Number
definition: The official reference number portion of a course identifier.  This number normally designates the level of the course as well as the level of the individual expected to enroll in the course.

name: Course Repeat Code
definition: Indicates that an academic course has been repeated by a student and how that repeat is to be computed in the student's academic grade average.
use_case: K-12 -> High School Generated Transcript K-12 -> LEA-to-LEA Student Record Exchange K-12 -> LEA-to-SEA Student Record Exchange

name: Course Section Identifier
definition: A unique number or alphanumeric code assigned by an institution, school, school system, state, or other agency or entity for a particular course-section.
usage_notes:
CEDS "Identifier" elements reflect the intent of the XSD:Token format, i.e. a string in which carriage return, line feed, and tab characters have been removed as well as any internal sequences of two or more spaces and any leading or trailing spaces.

An Identifier MAY be a Universally Unique Identifier (UUID) / Globally Unique Identifier (GUID), i.e.128-bit unique identifiers generated according to the algorithms and encoding standards of RFC 4122.

name: Course Section Instructional Delivery Mode
definition: The primary setting or medium of delivery for the course.

name: Course Section Maximum Capacity
definition: The maximum number of students the Course Section can maintain.
format: Integer - greater than or equal to 0

name: Course Section Number
definition: The number assigned to differentiate among distinct occurrences of courses that have the same course abbreviation and number but are considered to be different courses.

name: Course Section Single Sex Class Status
definition: Section in a co-educational school where only male or only female students are permitted to take the course.
use_case: K-12 -> Civil Rights Data Collection K-12 -> Teacher-Student Data Link -> Class Section

name: Course Section Time Required for Completion
definition: The actual or estimated number of clock minutes required for course completion. This number is especially important for career and technical education course and may represent (in minutes) the clock hour requirement of the course, the number of minutes (or clock hours) of class time per week, times the number of equivalent weeks the class typically meets.
use_case: K-12 -> Teacher-Student Data Link -> Class Section
format: Integer - greater than or equal to 0

name: Developmental Education Type
definition: An indicator of the category of developmental education.
use_case: Postsecondary Education -> Voluntary Framework of Accountability

name: Family and Consumer Sciences Course Indicator
definition: An indication that the course is associated with the Family and Consumer Sciences plan of study.

name: Instruction Language
definition: The language of instruction, other than English, used in the program or course.
use_case: K-12 -> Consolidated State Performance Report
usage_notes: The CEDS ISO 639-2 Language Code option set comes from the ISO 639-2 standard, the character encoding in ISO 8859-1 download. Discontinued codes from the ISO standard are not included in the CEDS list.

name: National Collegiate Athletic Association Eligibility
definition: An indication that the course is approved for determining NCAA eligibility.

name: Original Course Identifier
definition: The course identifier as it was listed when the credit was earned (e.g. before a system conversion) to show consistency between present transcripts and older ones.
usage_notes:
CEDS "Identifier" elements reflect the intent of the XSD:Token format, i.e. a string in which carriage return, line feed, and tab characters have been removed as well as any internal sequences of two or more spaces and any leading or trailing spaces.

An Identifier MAY be a Universally Unique Identifier (UUID) / Globally Unique Identifier (GUID), i.e.128-bit unique identifiers generated according to the algorithms and encoding standards of RFC 4122.

name: Override School Course Number
definition: An indication of the way an academic course was identified at an educational institution.

name: Receiving Location of Instruction
definition: The type of location at which instruction or service takes place.

name: Session Attendance Term Indicator
definition: Indicates that the session is an attendance term.

name: Session Begin Date
definition: The year, month and day on which a session begins.
use_case: K-12 -> High School Generated Transcript K-12 -> LEA-to-LEA Student Record Exchange K-12 -> LEA-to-SEA Student Record Exchange K-12 -> Teacher-Student Data Link -> Class Section

name: Session Code
definition: A local code given to the session, usually for a session that represents a term within the school year such as a marking term.

name: Session Description
definition: A short description of the Session.

name: Session Designator
definition: The academic session for which the data are recorded and applicable.
use_case: K-12 -> High School Feedback Report Postsecondary Education -> Transition

name: Session End Date
definition: The year, month and day on which a session ends.
use_case: K-12 -> High School Generated Transcript K-12 -> LEA-to-LEA Student Record Exchange K-12 -> LEA-to-SEA Student Record Exchange K-12 -> Teacher-Student Data Link -> Class Section
usage_notes: All CEDS Exit and End Dates represent the last day of the date range specified, such as the last day that a person was enrolled, participated, or received services.

name: Session Marking Term Indicator
definition: Indicates that the session is a marking term.

name: Session Scheduling Term Indicator
definition: Indicates that the session is a scheduling term.

name: Session Type
definition: A prescribed span of time when an education institution is open, instruction is provided, and students are under the direction and guidance of teachers and/or education institution administration. A session may be interrupted by one or more vacations.
use_case: K-12 -> High School Generated Transcript K-12 -> LEA-to-LEA Student Record Exchange K-12 -> LEA-to-SEA Student Record Exchange K-12 -> Teacher-Student Data Link -> Class Section

name: Timetable Day Identifier
definition: The unique identifier for the locally defined rotation cycle date code when the class meets (e.g., in a two day schedule, valid values could be "A" and "B", or "1" and "2").
usage_notes:
CEDS "Identifier" elements reflect the intent of the XSD:Token format, i.e. a string in which carriage return, line feed, and tab characters have been removed as well as any internal sequences of two or more spaces and any leading or trailing spaces.

An Identifier MAY be a Universally Unique Identifier (UUID) / Globally Unique Identifier (GUID), i.e.128-bit unique identifiers generated according to the algorithms and encoding standards of RFC 4122.

name: Tuition Funded
definition: Indicates that tuition for person's participation in a program, service, or course is funded or partially funded by an external grant program.
usage_notes: The initial use case is for professional development courses/programs, but could apply to student programs/courses as well.

name: Virtual Indicator
definition: An indication that a childcare, early education, or early learning program, school, institution, program, or course section focuses primarily on instruction in which children and teachers are separated by time and/or location and interact through the use of computers and/or telecommunications technology.

name: Work-based Learning Opportunity Type
definition: The type of work-based learning opportunity a student participated in.

name: Career Cluster
definition: The career cluster that defines the industry or occupational focus which may be associated with a career pathways program, plan of study, or course.
usage_notes: Options from O*NET OnLine an application that was created for the general public to provide broad access to the O*NET database of occupational information. O*NET OnLine offers a variety of search options and occupational data, while My Next Move is a streamlined application for students and job seekers. Both applications were developed for the U.S. Department of Labor by the National Center for O*NET Development.  See onetonline.org for more information.

name: Enrollment Capacity
definition: Maximum number of age-appropriate students who can be enrolled.
usage_notes: Enrollment capacity can be collected at a variety of levels, such as classroom, grade, school, and facility.

name: Primary Program Indicator
definition: An indication that the associated program is the primary function of this organization.
usage_notes: This element is used in conjunction with Program Type.

name: Program Name
definition: The name of the program of instruction, training, services or benefits available through federal, state, or local agencies.
use_case: Postsecondary Education -> Student Achievement Measure

name: Program Sponsor Type
definition: A type of organization providing funds for a particular educational or service program or activity or for an individual's participation in the program or activity.

name: Program Type
definition: The system outlining instructional or non-instructional activities and procedures designed to accomplish a predetermined educational objective or set of objectives or to provide support services to a person and/or the community.
use_case: K-12 -> High School Generated Transcript K-12 -> LEA-to-LEA Student Record Exchange K-12 -> LEA-to-SEA Student Record Exchange

name: Competency Association Connection Citation
definition: Any citation appropriate to evidence the connection between nodes
alternate_name: Learning Standard Item Association Connection Citation

name: Competency Association Destination Node Name
definition: Name of the destination node when the Competency Association is used as a connector in a learning map.
alternate_name: Learning Standard Item Association Destination Node Name

name: Competency Association Destination Node URI
definition: URI of the destination node when the Competency Association is used as a connector in a learning map.
alternate_name: Learning Standard Item Association Destination Node URI

name: Competency Association Identifier URI
definition: A URI that establishes uniqueness of an association between a competency definition and another competency item or other objects such as learning resources.
alternate_name: Learning Standard Item Association Identifier URI

name: Competency Association Origin Node Name
definition: Name of the origin node when the Competency Association is used as a connector in a learning map.
alternate_name: Learning Standard Item Association Origin Node Name

name: Competency Association Origin Node URI
definition: URI of the origin node when the Competency Association is used as a connector in a learning map.
alternate_name: Learning Standard Item Association Origin Node URI

name: Competency Association Type
definition: Defines the nature of the association between a Competency Definition and an associated data object such as a Learning Resource, an Assessment Item, or even another Competency Definition.
usage_notes:
The Learning Standard Item Association entity defines metadata relationships between a Learning Standard Item and other objects or relationships between Learning Standard Items not otherwise defined in the normal taxonomy of the framework such as for competency-based pathways, relationships between different versions of the same learning standard, and relationships to resources.


For example, "Prerequisite" may indicate that the Associated Learning Standard Item is a Prerequisite of this Learning Standards Item. Another association may specify that a Learning Resource "Teaches" the specified Learning Standard Item, or is aligned to the "Reading Level" specified as part of the Learning Standard Item.

name: Competency Association Weight
definition: Indicates the relative significance this connection has for the destination node in a learning map.
format: Numeric - up to 3 digits after decimal place
usage_notes: This element is used to support learning maps and may be used in two ways 1) use a 1.000 to flag incoming nodes as important prerequisites/predecessors and 0.000 to indicate those with less significance, or 2) to indicate a levels of significance for the connection as a decimal between 0.000 and 1.000.

name: Competency Definition Blooms Taxonomy Domain
definition: Classification of the Competency Definition using Bloom's Taxonomy Domains.
alternate_name: Learning Standard Item Blooms Taxonomy Domain, Competency Item Blooms Taxonomy Domain

name: Competency Definition Code
definition: A human-referenceable code designated by the publisher to identify the item in the hierarchy of competency definitions.
usage_notes: For example: "M.1.N.3"  The code is usually not globally unique and usually has embedded meaning such as a number that represents a grade/level and letters that represent content strands.
alternate_name: Learning Standard Item Code, Competency Item Code

name: Competency Definition Concept Keyword
definition: The significant topicality of the competency definition using free-text keywords and phrases.
alternate_name: Learning Standard Item Concept Keyword, Competency Item Concept Keyword

name: Competency Definition Concept Term
definition: The topicality of the competency definition, e.g. "Pythagorean Theorem," "Trigonometric functions," "Forces and energy," "Scientific method," "Oral history," etc.
alternate_name: Learning Standard Item Concept Term, Competency Item Concept Term

name: Competency Definition Current Version Indicator
definition: Indicates that this is the most current version of the Competency Definition.
usage_notes: This element supports version histories at the statement level. If corrections have been made to individual items/statements that are not part of a new Competency Framework, the elements 'Competency Definition Previous Version Identifier' and 'Competency Definition Current Version Indicator' provide a reference to historical versions of the current statement. In such uses the 'Competency Definition Code' could be the same for multiple versions of a statement and 'Competency Definition URL' could resolve to the most current version of the statement.
alternate_name: Learning Standard Item Current Version Indicator, Competency Item Current Version Indicator

name: Competency Definition Education Level
definition: The education level, grade level or primary instructional level at which a Competency Definition is intended.
usage_notes: More than one Learning Standard Grade Level may be associated with one Learning Standard Item.
alternate_name: Learning Standard Item Education Level, Competency Item Education Level

name: Competency Definition Identifier
definition: The globally unique identifier (GUID) issued by the publisher of the competency framework that uniquely identifies the definition in the hierarchy of competency definitions using a RFC 4122 compliant 32-character hexadecimal string, such as 21EC2020-3AEA-1069-A2DD-08002B30309D.
use_case: School Readiness
usage_notes:
CEDS "Identifier" elements reflect the intent of the XSD:Token format, i.e. a string in which carriage return, line feed, and tab characters have been removed as well as any internal sequences of two or more spaces and any leading or trailing spaces.

An Identifier MAY be a Universally Unique Identifier (UUID) / Globally Unique Identifier (GUID), i.e.128-bit unique identifiers generated according to the algorithms and encoding standards of RFC 4122.
alternate_name: Learning Standard Item Identifier, Competency Item Identifier

name: Competency Definition Language
definition: The default language of the text used for the content in the competency definition statement.
usage_notes: The CEDS ISO 639-2 Language Code option set comes from the ISO 639-2 standard, the character encoding in ISO 8859-1 download. Discontinued codes from the ISO standard are not included in the CEDS list.
alternate_name: Learning Standard Item Language, Competency Item Language

name: Competency Definition License
definition: The full text or URL reference to a legal document giving official permission to do something with the competency definition statement.
alternate_name: Learning Standard Item License, Competency Item License

name: Competency Definition Multiple Intelligence
definition: Classification of the Competency Definition using intelligences defined for Howard Earl Gardner's Theory of Multiple Intelligences.
alternate_name: Learning Standard Item Multiple Intelligence, Competency Item Multiple Intelligence

name: Competency Definition Node Accessibility Profile
definition: When the Competency Definition is used as a node in a learning map, this element supports alternative pathways based on a learner's accessibility profile. The type selected indicates which accessibility profile the node is designed to address.
alternate_name: Learning Standard Item Node Accessibility Profile, Competency Item Node Accessibility Profile

name: Competency Definition Notes
definition: Information about the derivation of a Competency Definition Statement.
alternate_name: Learning Standard Item Notes, Competency Item Notes

name: Competency Definition Parent Code
definition: A human-referenceable code designated by the publisher to identify the parent item in the hierarchy of competency definitions.
alternate_name: Learning Standard Item Parent Code, Competency Item Parent Code

name: Competency Definition Parent Identifier
definition: The globally unique identifier (GUID) issued by the publisher of the competency framework that uniquely identifies the parent item in the hierarchy of competency definitions using a RFC 4122 compliant 32-character hexadecimal string, such as 21EC2020-3AEA-1069-A2DD-08002B30309D.
usage_notes:
CEDS "Identifier" elements reflect the intent of the XSD:Token format, i.e. a string in which carriage return, line feed, and tab characters have been removed as well as any internal sequences of two or more spaces and any leading or trailing spaces.

An Identifier MAY be a Universally Unique Identifier (UUID) / Globally Unique Identifier (GUID), i.e.128-bit unique identifiers generated according to the algorithms and encoding standards of RFC 4122.
alternate_name: Learning Standard Item Parent Identifier, Competency Item Parent Identifier

name: Competency Definition Parent URL
definition: A network-resolvable Uniform Resource Locator (URL) pointing to the authoritative reference for the hierarchal parent of the competency definition.
alternate_name: Learning Standard Item Parent URL, Competency Item Parent URL

name: Competency Definition Prerequisite Identifier
definition: The unique identifier of an immediate prerequisite Competency Definition, a competency needed prior to learning this one. (Some items may have no prerequisites while others may have one or more prerequisites. This should only be used to represent the immediate predecessors in a competency-based pathway, i.e. not prerequisites of prerequisites.)
use_case: School Readiness
usage_notes: The recommended approach is to use the entity Learning Standard Item Association instead of this data element. Learning Standard Item Association also supports associating other entities, such as Learning Resources, to learning standard items.    CEDS "Identifier" elements reflect the intent of the XSD:Token format, i.e. a string in which carriage return, line feed, and tab characters have been removed as well as any internal sequences of two or more spaces and any leading or trailing spaces.    An Identifier MAY be a Universally Unique Identifier (UUID) / Globally Unique Identifier (GUID), i.e.128-bit unique identifiers generated according to the algorithms and encoding standards of RFC 4122.
alternate_name: Learning Standard Item Prerequisite Identifier, Competency Item Prerequisite Identifier

name: Competency Definition Previous Version Identifier
definition: The unique identifier of the previous version of the Competency Definition if the statement was modified.
usage_notes:
This element supports version histories at the statement level. If corrections have been made to individual items/statements that are not part of a new Competency Framework, the elements 'Competency Definition Previous Version Identifier' and 'Competency Definition Current Version Indicator' provide a reference to historical versions of the current statement. In such uses the 'Competency Definition Code' could be the same for multiple versions of a statement and 'Competency Definition URL' could resolve to the most current version of the statement.


CEDS "Identifier" elements reflect the intent of the XSD:Token format, i.e. a string in which carriage return, line feed, and tab characters have been removed as well as any internal sequences of two or more spaces and any leading or trailing spaces.


An Identifier MAY be a Universally Unique Identifier (UUID) / Globally Unique Identifier (GUID), i.e.128-bit unique identifiers generated according to the algorithms and encoding standards of RFC 4122.
alternate_name: Learning Standard Item Previous Version Identifier, Competency Item Previous Version Identifier

name: Competency Definition Sequence
definition: A set of one or more alphanumeric characters and/or symbols denoting the positioning of the statement being described in a sequential listing of statements.
usage_notes: Based on ASN's ListID. (add reference URL)
alternate_name: Learning Standard Item Sequence, Competency Item Sequence

name: Competency Definition Short Name
definition: The short name or label for the competency definition or its node in a competency framework.
alternate_name: Learning Standard Item Node Name, Competency Item Node Name

name: Competency Definition Statement
definition: The text of the statement. The textual content that either describes a specific competency or describes a less granular group of competencies within the taxonomy of the competency framework.
use_case: School Readiness
usage_notes: Note: This element is designed to support statements from various learning standards frameworks. The Head Start Child Outcomes Framework includes statements for Domains, Elements, and Indicators. Examples from the K-12 Common Core State Standards are the domain: “Geometry", the cluster: “Understand and apply the Pythagorean Theorem,” and standard:  “Apply the Pythagorean Theorem to determine unknown side lengths in right triangles in real-world and mathematical problems in two and three dimensions.”
alternate_name: Learning Standard Item Statement, Competency Item Statement

name: Competency Definition Testability Type
definition: Indicates if the competency described in the Competency Definition Statement can be tested using one or more assessment items.
alternate_name: Learning Standard Item Testability Type, Competency Item Testability Type

name: Competency Definition Text Complexity Maximum Value
definition: The maximum value in the range of text complexity applicable to a language competency definition using the scaling system defined by Text Complexity System, e.g. Lexile(tm).
alternate_name: Learning Standard Item Text Complexity Maximum Value, Competency Item Text Complexity Maximum Value

name: Competency Definition Text Complexity Minimum Value
definition: The minimum value in the range of text complexity applicable to a language competency definition using the scaling system defined by Text Complexity System, e.g. Lexile(tm).
alternate_name: Learning Standard Item Text Complexity Minimum Value, Competency Item Text Complexity Minimum Value

name: Competency Definition Text Complexity System
definition: The scaling system used to specify the text complexity of a competency item.
alternate_name: Learning Standard Item Text Complexity System, Competency Item Text Complexity System

name: Competency Definition Type
definition: The class of statement in the structure of statements in the Competency Framework according to a controlled vocabulary, specified as a textual label.
use_case: School Readiness
usage_notes: This property points to a class, not to instances of that class. For example, where two competencies in a competency framework have been identified respectively  as "Strand: Renaissance" and "Strand: Social history", the competencyCategory for both these competencies is "Strand"."
alternate_name: Learning Standard Item Type, Competency Item Type

name: Competency Definition Type URL
definition: The class of statement in the structure of statements in the Competency Framework according to a controlled vocabulary, specified as a URI referencing a controlled vocabulary.
usage_notes: This property points to a class, not to instances of that class. For example, where two competencies in a competency framework have been identified respectively  as "Strand: Renaissance" and "Strand: Social history", the competency category for both these competencies is "Strand"."

name: Competency Definition Typical Age Range Maximum
definition: The typical maximum age at which a person learns the defined competency.
format: Integer - greater than or equal to 0
usage_notes: Use this element with "Competency Definition Typical Age Range Minimum" instead of "Competency Item Typical Age Range"

name: Competency Definition Typical Age Range Minimum
definition: The typical minimum age at which a person learns the defined competency.
format: Integer - greater than or equal to 0
usage_notes: Use this element with "Competency Definition Typical Age Range Maximum" instead of "Competency Item Typical Age Range"

name: Competency Definition URL
definition: A network-resolvable Uniform Resource Locator (URL) pointing to the authoritative reference for the competency definition.
usage_notes: An Identifier MAY be a Universally Unique Identifier (UUID) / Globally Unique Identifier (GUID), i.e.128-bit unique identifiers generated according to the algorithms and encoding standards of RFC 4122.
alternate_name: Learning Standard Item URL, Competency Item URL

name: Competency Definition Valid End Date
definition: The year, month and day the competency definition was deprecated/replaced by the jurisdiction in which it was intended to apply.
usage_notes: When not specified, the entity is assumed to contain the most current version of the specified competency definition. All CEDS Exit and End Dates represent the last day of the date range specified, in this case the last day the competency definition was valid.
alternate_name: Learning Standard Item Valid End Date, Competency Item Valid End Date

name: Competency Definition Valid Start Date
definition: The year, month and day the competency definition was adopted by the jurisdiction in which it was intended to apply.
alternate_name: Learning Standard Item Valid Start Date, Competency Item Valid Start Date

name: Competency Definition Version
definition: A label assigned by the publisher indicating the version of the competency framework statement.
alternate_name: Learning Standard Item Version, Competency Item Version

name: Competency Framework Identifier URI
definition: An unambiguous reference to the competency framework using a network-resolvable URI.
use_case: School Readiness

name: Competency Framework Source URL
definition: A URL that resolves to the original or authoritative competency framework document.
usage_notes: This is the URL of a human-readable artifact. Often this document is published in html and/or pdf and is used by the standard setting entity as part of its approval process.

name: Competency Framework Creator
definition: The person or organization chiefly responsible for the intellectual content of the competency framework.
usage_notes: Implementations may choose to model this element as a repeatable field to support the case of multiple authors.  Others may just use a comma delimited string for multiple authors.

name: Competency Framework Description
definition: A textual description of the scope and contents of the competency framework.

name: Competency Framework Identifier URI
definition: An unambiguous reference to the competency framework using a network-resolvable URI.
use_case: School Readiness

name: Competency Framework Jurisdiction
definition: A legal, quasi-legal, organizational or institutional domain of the entity mandating the use of the statement--e.g., California.

name: Competency Framework Language
definition: The default language of the text used for the content in the competency framework.
usage_notes: The CEDS ISO 639-2 Language Code option set comes from the ISO 639-2 standard, the character encoding in ISO 8859-1 download. Discontinued codes from the ISO standard are not included in the CEDS list.

name: Competency Framework License
definition: A legal document giving official permission to do something with the competency framework.

name: Competency Framework Publication Date
definition: The date on which this content was first published.
usage_notes: This may or may not be different from the Learning Standard Document Valid Start Date.

name: Competency Framework Publication Status
definition: The publication status of the competency framework.

name: Competency Framework Publisher
definition: The entity responsible for making the competency framework available.

name: Competency Framework Rights
definition: The information about rights held in and over the resource.

name: Competency Framework Rights Holder
definition: The person or organization owning or managing rights over the competency framework.

name: Competency Framework Source URL
definition: A URL that resolves to the original or authoritative competency framework document.
usage_notes: This is the URL of a human-readable artifact. Often this document is published in html and/or pdf and is used by the standard setting entity as part of its approval process.

name: Competency Framework Subject
definition: The topic or academic subject of the competency framework.
use_case: School Readiness

name: Competency Framework Title
definition: The name of the competency framework.
use_case: School Readiness

name: Competency Framework Valid End Date
definition: The year, month and day the competency framework was deprecated/replaced by the jurisdiction in which it was intended to apply.
usage_notes: All CEDS Exit and End Dates represent the last day of the date range specified, such as the last day that a person was enrolled, participated, or received services.
alternate_name: Learning Standard Document Valid End Date

name: Competency Framework Valid Start Date
definition: The year, month and day the competency framework was adopted by the jurisdiction in which it was intended to apply.
alternate_name: Learning Standard Document Valid Start Date

name: Competency Framework Version
definition: Defines the revision of the competency framework as a version number or date.
use_case: School Readiness

name: Competency Set Completion Criteria
definition: The criteria for the set of competencies that represent completion or partial completion of a unit, course, program, degree, certification, or other achievement/award. Specifies whether completion requires achievement of all items in the set or some number of items.
usage_notes: The criteria may be ‘all’ competencies in the set or ‘at-least’ # of competencies. Sets may be nested, e.g. all in subset A and 3 of 5 from subset B.

name: Competency Set Completion Criteria Threshold
definition: The minimum number of competencies in the set that must be achieved for completion or partial completion of a unit, course, program, degree, certification, or other achievement/award.
format: Integer - greater than or equal to 0
usage_notes: Used to define the completion criteria when Competency Set Completion Criteria is "At Least".  Not used when Competency Set Completion Criteria is "All".

name: CTDL Organization Type
definition: The type of credentialing organization or entity as defined by the Credential Transparency Description Language.
usage_notes: Includes free-standing medical, law or other first-professional schools, schools that offer postbaccalaureate certificates only, those that offer graduate programs only, etc.

name: Organization Identification System
definition: A coding scheme that is used for identification and record-keeping purposes by schools, social services, or other agencies to refer to an organization.
use_case: Early Learning -> Program Quality

name: Organization Identifier
definition: A unique number or alphanumeric code assigned to an organization by a school, school system, a state, or other agency or entity.
use_case: Early Learning -> Program Quality
usage_notes:
CEDS "Identifier" elements reflect the intent of the XSD:Token format, i.e. a string in which carriage return, line feed, and tab characters have been removed as well as any internal sequences of two or more spaces and any leading or trailing spaces.

An Identifier MAY be a Universally Unique Identifier (UUID) / Globally Unique Identifier (GUID), i.e.128-bit unique identifiers generated according to the algorithms and encoding standards of RFC 4122.

name: Person Identification System
definition: A coding scheme that is used for identification of a person.

name: Person Identifier
definition: A unique number or alphanumeric code assigned to a person by a school, school system, a state, or other agency or entity.
usage_notes:
CEDS "Identifier" elements reflect the intent of the XSD:Token format, i.e. a string in which carriage return, line feed, and tab characters have been removed as well as any internal sequences of two or more spaces and any leading or trailing spaces.

An Identifier MAY be a Universally Unique Identifier (UUID) / Globally Unique Identifier (GUID), i.e.128-bit unique identifiers generated according to the algorithms and encoding standards of RFC 4122.

name: State Issuing Professional Credential or License
definition: State where the professional license/credential was issued.
use_case: Early Learning -> Staff Quality

name: Adult Education Certification Type
definition: An indication of the category of the adult education certification a person holds.

name: Assessment Identification System
definition: A coding scheme that is used for identification and record-keeping purposes by schools, social services, or other agencies to refer to an assessment.
use_case: K-12 -> High School Feedback Report K-12 -> High School Generated Transcript K-12 -> LEA Assessments K-12 -> LEA-to-LEA Student Record Exchange K-12 -> LEA-to-SEA Student Record Exchange K-12 -> SEA Assessments

name: Assessment Identifier
definition: A unique number or alphanumeric code assigned to an assessment by a school, school system, a state, or other agency or entity.  This may be the publisher identifier.
use_case: College Readiness K-12 -> High School Feedback Report K-12 -> High School Generated Transcript K-12 -> LEA Assessments K-12 -> LEA-to-LEA Student Record Exchange K-12 -> LEA-to-SEA Student Record Exchange K-12 -> SEA Assessments School Readiness
usage_notes:
CEDS "Identifier" elements reflect the intent of the XSD:Token format, i.e. a string in which carriage return, line feed, and tab characters have been removed as well as any internal sequences of two or more spaces and any leading or trailing spaces.

An Identifier MAY be a Universally Unique Identifier (UUID) / Globally Unique Identifier (GUID), i.e.128-bit unique identifiers generated according to the algorithms and encoding standards of RFC 4122.

name: Credential Advanced Standing Description
definition: A description of a credential that reduced the time or cost of attaining this credential.

name: Credential Advanced Standing URL
definition: A URL that resolves to information about a credential that reduced the time or cost of attaining this credential.

name: Credential Award Approver Name
definition: Pronouncement of a favorable judgment by the agent being referenced.

name: Credential Award End Date
definition: The date, if any, on which the qualification, achievement, personal or organizational quality, or aspect of an identity expires or requires renewal.
usage_notes: All CEDS Exit and End Dates represent the last day of the date range specified, such as the last day that a person was enrolled, participated, or received services.

name: Credential Award Evidence URL
definition: A URL to a page that describes the evidence that the learner met the criteria for attainment of the credential award.

name: Credential Award Issuer Name
definition: The name of the agent issuing the qualification, achievement, personal or organizational quality, or aspect of an identity.

name: Credential Award Issuer Origin URL
definition: The Uniform Resource Locator (URL) from which the qualification, achievement, personal or organizational quality, or aspect of an identity was issued.
usage_notes: Used only if an award is issued electronically for the achievement.

name: Credential Award Start Date
definition: The date on which the qualification, achievement, personal or organizational quality, or aspect of an identity was conferred.
usage_notes: Diploma or Credential Award Date is the same concept but used when only month and year are known or needed.

name: Credential Completion Date
definition: The date on which the person's requirements for earning a credential were met or completed.

name: Credential Evidence Statement
definition: A statement or reference describing the evidence that the learner met the criteria for attainment of the qualification, achievement, personal or organizational quality, or aspect of an identity.
usage_notes: A narrative that may connect multiple pieces of evidence OR an IRI or document describing the work that the recipient did to earn the achievement. This can be a page that links out to other pages if linking directly to the work is infeasible. May be used in an array of multiple values.

name: Credential Issuer Revocation List URL
definition: The URL to a document that includes a list of credential award assertions an issuer has revoked.
usage_notes: See OpenBadges standard example http://openbadges.github.io/openbadges-specification/#RevocationList

name: Credential Revoked Date
definition: The date on which the qualification, achievement, personal or organizational quality, or aspect of an identity was revoked.
usage_notes: An empty string means the assertion was not revoked. Some uses (e.g. OpenBadges) may append time info in ISO 8601 format.

name: Credential Revoked Indicator
definition: Indicates whether the credential has been revoked by the credential provider.

name: Credential Revoked Reason
definition: Published reason for revocation of a credential award.

name: Number of Credits Attempted
definition: The number of credits that a student can earn for enrolling in and completing a given course.
use_case: K-12 -> High School Generated Transcript K-12 -> LEA-to-LEA Student Record Exchange K-12 -> LEA-to-SEA Student Record Exchange
format: Numeric - up to 2 digits after decimal place

name: Number of Credits Earned
definition: The number of credits an individual earns by the successful completion of a course.
use_case: K-12 -> High School Feedback Report K-12 -> High School Generated Transcript K-12 -> LEA-to-LEA Student Record Exchange K-12 -> LEA-to-SEA Student Record Exchange Postsecondary Education -> Transition
format: Numeric - up to 2 digits after decimal place

name: Professional Certificate or License Number
definition: The number issued by the credentialing/licensing agency.

name: CTDL Audience Level Type
definition: Type of level indicating a point in a progression through an educational or training context, for which the credential is intended; select from an existing enumeration of such types.
usage_notes: This is similar to "PESC Award Level Type" and "Academic Award Level Conferred" but uses a different controlled vocabulary. See https://credreg.net/ctdl/terms/Credential#AudienceLevel.

name: Career Cluster
definition: The career cluster that defines the industry or occupational focus which may be associated with a career pathways program, plan of study, or course.
usage_notes: Options from O*NET OnLine an application that was created for the general public to provide broad access to the O*NET database of occupational information. O*NET OnLine offers a variety of search options and occupational data, while My Next Move is a streamlined application for students and job seekers. Both applications were developed for the U.S. Department of Labor by the National Center for O*NET Development.  See onetonline.org for more information.

name: Classification of Instructional Program Code
definition: A six-digit code in the form xx.xxxx that identifies instructional program specialties within educational institutions.
use_case: K-12 -> High School Feedback Report Postsecondary Education -> Complete College America Postsecondary Education -> IPEDS Postsecondary Education -> Transition

name: Competency Definition URL
definition: A network-resolvable Uniform Resource Locator (URL) pointing to the authoritative reference for the competency definition.
usage_notes: An Identifier MAY be a Universally Unique Identifier (UUID) / Globally Unique Identifier (GUID), i.e.128-bit unique identifiers generated according to the algorithms and encoding standards of RFC 4122.
alternate_name: Learning Standard Item URL, Competency Item URL

name: Credential Definition Alternate Name
definition: An alias for the credential, which may include acronyms, alpha-numeric notations, and other forms of name abbreviations in common use such as PhD, MA, and BA.

name: Credential Definition Assessment Method Type
definition: The method used to conduct the assessment being referenced.

name: Credential Definition Category System
definition: The system that defines the categories of the qualification, achievement, personal or organizational quality, or aspect of an identity used in Credential Category Type.
usage_notes: This element recognizes formal adoption of categories for the Achievement Category Type to aid in comparability of data when a formally adopted vocabulary is used.

name: Credential Definition Category Type
definition: A category for defining the qualification, achievement, personal or organizational quality, or aspect of an identity.
usage_notes: Categories could include "Competency Mastered", "Competency Retained", "Course Completed", "Level Completed", "Certificate Earned", "Diploma Earned", "License Earned", "License Endorsement Earned", "Participation", "Academic Honor", "Non-Academic Honor", etc. (This element supports an emerging use case, therefore a complete set of options are not known.  Future CEDS versions may define an Achievement Type element when a fixed option set can be compiled.)  Note: The Achievement entity is most valuable when linked to a specific competency set that defined the learning standards related to the achievement.(SEE "Achievement Category System")

name: Credential Definition Criteria
definition: The criteria for competency-based completion of the qualification, achievement, personal or organizational quality, or aspect of an identity.

name: Credential Definition Criteria URL
definition: The Uniform Resource Locator (URL) for the unique address of a web page describing the competency-based completion criteria for the qualification, achievement, personal or organizational quality, or aspect of an identity.

name: Credential Definition Date Effective
definition: Effective date of the content of a credential definition.
usage_notes: This is the date the content/definition of the credential became effective, not necessarily the date that one or more credentialing organizations began offering the credential.

name: Credential Definition Description
definition: A description of the qualification, achievement, personal or organizational quality, or aspect of an identity.

name: Credential Definition Estimated Duration
definition: The estimated amount of time in minutes it will take to earn the credential.

name: Credential Definition Identifier
definition: A globally unique identifier by which the creator/owner/provider of a credential recognizes the qualification, achievement, personal or organizational quality, or aspect of an identity in transactions with the external environment.
usage_notes: CEDS "Identifier" elements reflect the intent of the XSD:Token format, i.e. a string in which carriage return, line feed, and tab characters have been removed as well as any internal sequences of two or more spaces and any leading or trailing spaces.   An Identifier MAY be a Universally Unique Identifier (UUID) / Globally Unique Identifier (GUID), i.e.128-bit unique identifiers generated according to the algorithms and encoding standards of RFC 4122.

name: Credential Definition Identifier System
definition: A coding scheme that is used for identification and record-keeping purposes by a credentialing organization to refer to a qualification, achievement, personal or organizational quality, or aspect of an identity.

name: Credential Definition Intended Purpose Type
definition: The intended type of application of the credential by the holder.

name: Credential Definition Jurisdiction Region
definition: The geo-political region in which the credential is applicable.
usage_notes: http://geojson.org/geojson-spec.html#polygon

name: Credential Definition Jurisdiction Region Exception
definition: A geo-political region in which the credential does not apply.
usage_notes: http://geojson.org/geojson-spec.html#polygon

name: Credential Definition Keywords
definition: Keywords or key phrases describing aspects of a credential considered useful for its discovery.

name: Credential Definition Maximum Duration
definition: The maximum amount of time in minutes it will take to earn the described credential.

name: Credential Definition Minimum Age
definition: The minimum allowed age in years at which a person is eligible for the credential.

name: Credential Definition Minimum Duration
definition: The minimum amount of time in minutes it will take to earn the described credential.

name: Credential Definition NAICS Industry Type
definition: The North American Industry Classification System (NAICS) class identifier for an industry associated with the credential.

name: Credential Definition Status Type
definition: The status of the credential offered by a credentialing organization.

name: Credential Definition Terminal Degree Indicator
definition: This degree is the highest degree that can be awarded in this classification of instructional programs field or program area.

name: Credential Definition Title
definition: The title assigned to a qualification, achievement, personal or organizational quality, or aspect of an identity.

name: Credential Definition Validation Method Description
definition: Description of the methods used to evaluate the validity and reliability of a credential earned by a person.

name: Credential Definition Verification Type
definition: A resource describing the means by which someone can verify whether a credential has been attained by a person.

name: Credential Definition Version
definition: An alphanumeric identifier of a version of the credential being described that is unique within the organizational context.

name: Credential Image URL
definition: The Uniform Resource Locator (URL) for the unique address of an image representing an award or badge associated with the qualification, achievement, personal or organizational quality, or aspect of an identity.
usage_notes: Typical use is for online display of a badge image.

name: Employment NAICS Code
definition: The North American Industry Classification System (NAICS) code associated with an individual's employment.

name: O*NET-SOC Occupation Type
definition: The O*NET-SOC taxonomy defines the set of occupations across the world of work based on the Standard Occupational Classification.
usage_notes: https://www.onetcenter.org/taxonomy.html

name: CTDL Organization Type
definition: The type of credentialing organization or entity as defined by the Credential Transparency Description Language.
usage_notes: Includes free-standing medical, law or other first-professional schools, schools that offer postbaccalaureate certificates only, those that offer graduate programs only, etc.

name: Credential Definition Agent Role Type
definition: The role that an organization or person has in relation to this Credential Definition based on terms defined by Credential Engine.
usage_notes: Option codes and definitions are from the Credential Engine and the ceterms namespace, except the codes use Pascal case in CEDS to follow CEDS conventions and use camel case in the original  ceterms.

name: Child Outcomes Summary Progress A Indicator
definition: Indicates that the child demonstrates progress in positive social-emotional skills, including social relationships.

name: Child Outcomes Summary Progress B Indicator
definition: Indicates that the child demonstrates progress in acquisition and use of knowledge and skills, including early language/communication.

name: Child Outcomes Summary Progress C Indicator
definition: Indicates that the child demonstrates progress in use of appropriate behaviors to meet their needs.

name: Child Outcomes Summary Rating A
definition: Child's level of functioning in positive social-emotional skills (including social relationships).

name: Child Outcomes Summary Rating B
definition: Child's level of functioning in the acquisition and use of knowledge and skills (including early language/communication.

name: Child Outcomes Summary Rating C
definition: Child's level of functioning in the use of appropriate behaviors to meet their needs.

name: Early Learning Outcome Measurement Level
definition: Use for outcome measures in early learning.

name: Early Learning Outcome Time Point
definition: The point in time for which the result is used for an outcome measure.

name: Address Apartment Room or Suite Number
definition: The apartment, room, or suite number of an address.

name: Address City
definition: The name of the city in which an address is located.

name: Homelessness Status
definition: Children and youth who lack a fixed, regular, and adequate nighttime residence. Homeless children and youth include: 1) children and youth who are sharing the housing of other persons due to loss of housing, economic hardship, or a similar reason; are living in motels, hotels, trailer parks, or camping grounds due to the lack of alternative adequate accommodations; are living in emergency or transitional shelters; are abandoned in hospitals; or are awaiting foster care placement; 2) children and youth who have a primary nighttime residence that is a public or private place not designed for or originally used as a regular sleeping accommodation for human beings; or 3) children and youths who are living in cars, parks, public spaces, abandoned buildings, substandard housing, bus or train stations, or similar settings. 4) migratory children who qualify as homeless because the children are living in circumstances described in the above. (See Section 103 of the McKinney Act for a more detailed description of this data element).

name: Assessment Early Learning Developmental Domain
definition: Developmental domains related to early learning and used for assessing a child's kindergarten readiness.
use_case: K-12 -> EDFacts School Readiness
usage_notes:
Used by states in reporting Kindergarten Entry Assessment (KEA) results as defined for some federal grant programs.

For each domain used by the state, the state would provide:
- The total number of children who participated in the KEA for each domain
- The number of children who participated in the KEA for each domain AND was at or above what the state defines as “ready” for kindergarten for that domain.

The counts may be calculated using unit-level data defined for Assessment Subtest (scoring method and what is being measured, e.g. the Domain), related Assessment Performance Levels (e.g. "Ready"), related to each student Assessment Result.
