name: English Learner Status
definition: In coordination with the state's definition based on Section 8101(20) of the ESEA, as amended by the ESSA, the term 'English learner', when used with respect to an individual, means an individual:  (A) who is aged 3 through 21;  (B) who is enrolled or preparing to enroll in an elementary school or a secondary school;  (C)   (i) who was not born in the United States or whose native languages are languages other than English;  (ii)   (I) who is a Native American or Alaska Native, or a native resident of the outlying areas; and  (II) who comes from an environment where a language other than English has had a significant impact on the individual's level of English language proficiency; or  (iii) who is migratory, whose native language is a language other than English, and who come from an environment where a language other than English is dominant; and  (D) whose difficulties in speaking, reading, writing, or understanding the English language may be sufficient to deny the individual   (i) the ability to meet the challenging State academic standards;  (ii) the ability to successfully achieve in classrooms where the language of instruction is English; or  (iii) the opportunity to participate fully in society.
use_case: K-12 -> EDFacts K-12 -> High School Generated Transcript K-12 -> LEA-to-LEA Student Record Exchange K-12 -> LEA-to-SEA Student Record Exchange
usage_notes: To be classified as an English learner, an individual must be A, B, and (C or D). For C, an individual can be i, ii, or iii. If C-ii, the individual must be I and II. For D, an individual must be denied i or ii or iii and must be determined by a valid assessment.

name: Responsible Organization Identifier
definition: Identifies an organization responsible for specific educational services and/or instruction based on a type of responsibility  specified in the Responsible Organization Type.
usage_notes:
This may be used to specify responsibility when the organization is not a school (Responsible School) or school district (Responsible District).

CEDS "Identifier" elements reflect the intent of the XSD:Token format, i.e. a string in which carriage return, line feed, and tab characters have been removed as well as any internal sequences of two or more spaces and any leading or trailing spaces.

An Identifier MAY be a Universally Unique Identifier (UUID) / Globally Unique Identifier (GUID), i.e.128-bit unique identifiers generated according to the algorithms and encoding standards of RFC 4122.

definition: The number of minutes per week that a student with disabilities is served in a special education setting separate from his or her non-disabled peers.

definition: An indication of the significance of a date to an individualized program.

definition: The place in which a child's service plan meeting is held.

definition: Date student will be reevaluated for continued placement in a support program(s).

definition: The year, month and day on which the service plan document is signed.

name: Method of Service Delivery
definition: The method by which the services will be provided.

name: Role
definition: A description of the way in which a person relates to an organization.

name: Student Support Service Type
definition: Type of related or ancillary services offered or provided to a person or a group of persons within the formal educational system or by an outside agency which provides non-instructional services to support the general welfare of students. This includes physical and emotional health, the ability to select an appropriate course of study, admission to appropriate educational programs, and the ability to adjust to and remain in school through the completion of programs. In serving a student with an identified disability, related services include developmental, corrective, or supportive services required to ensure that the person benefits from special education.
usage_notes: At the organization level, this element indicates the services offered to students. At the person level, this element indicates the services received by students.

name: Goal Description
definition: A statement that describes the desired outcomes.

name: Goal End Date
definition: The date on which the goal expires or has been achieved.
usage_notes: For federal reporting use cases some codes are required to be reported and others are not. All CEDS Exit and End Dates represent the last day of the date range specified, such as the last day that a person was enrolled, participated, or received services.

name: Goal Start Date
definition: The date on which the goal becomes active.

name: Goal Success Criteria
definition: One or more statements that describes the criteria used by teachers and students to check for attainment of a goal.

name: Date of Transition Plan
definition: The date transition steps and services were added to the individualized service plan.

name: IDEA Part B 619 Potential Eligibility Indicator
definition: The determination of whether a child is potentially eligible for Part B 619 services

name: IDEA Part C to Part B Notification Date
definition: The date that notification is provided to the State Education Agency (SEA) and local education agency (LEA) of residence for a child potentially eligible for Part B (619) preschool services.

name: IDEA Part C to Part B Notification Opt Out Date
definition: The date that parents of a child potentially eligible for Part B preschool services opt out of the impending notification to the local education agency.

name: IDEA Part C to Part B Notification Opt Out Indicator
definition: Indicates whether parents of a child potentially eligible for Part B preschool services have opted out of the impending notification to the local education agency.

name: Reason for Delay of Transition Conference
definition: The reasons for the delay of a transition conference.

name: Transition Conference Date
definition: The date of the transition conference from IDEA Part C to Part B 619 or another early learning program or service.

name: Transition Conference Decline Date
definition: The date the parents declined approval for the transition conference from IDEA Part C to Part B 619 or another early learning program or service.

name: ISO 639-2 Language Code

usage_notes: The CEDS ISO 639-2 Language Code option set comes from the ISO 639-2 standard, the character encoding in ISO 8859-1 download. Discontinued codes from the ISO standard are not included in the CEDS list.

name: ISO 639-3 Language Code
definition: The code for the specific language or dialect that a person uses to communicate.
usage_notes: The CEDS ISO 639-3 Language Code option set comes from the ISO 639-3 standard, the Latin-1 download. Only living language code types from the ISO standard are included in the CEDS list. Special scope and discontinued codes are excluded.

name: ISO 639-5 Language Family
definition: A code for a specific language family, which supplements the language groups and families in the ISO 639-2 Language Code.
usage_notes: The CEDS ISO 639-5 Language Family option set comes from the ISO 639-5 standard.

usage_notes: Note: This applies to an enrollment period record.  Separate records using this element definition could capture attendance for regular enrollment, an out-of-school program or other program requiring attendance records.  CEDS now supports the detailed attendance events to capture attendance status on any given day, class period, or session.  CEDS generally doesn't include elements for counts when it has the unit level elements to calculate the count. These identifiers are fairly general but provide enough specificity to identify the course's topic and to distinguish it from other courses in that subject area.
usage_notes: https://nces.ed.gov/forum/SCED.asp

name: School Courses for the Exchange of Data Course Level

name: School Courses for the Exchange of Data Course Subject Area

name: School Courses for the Exchange of Data Sequence of Course

CEDS "Identifier" elements reflect the intent of the XSD:Token format, i.e. a string in which carriage return, line feed, and tab characters have been removed as well as any internal sequences of two or more spaces and any leading or trailing spaces.

An Identifier MAY be a Universally Unique Identifier (UUID) / Globally Unique Identifier (GUID), i.e.128-bit unique identifiers generated according to the algorithms and encoding standards of RFC 4122.

name: Family Income
definition: Total income of family from all sources. Income includes money, wages or salary before deductions; net income from non-farm self-employment; net income from farm self-employment; regular payments from Social Security or railroad retirement; payments from unemployment compensation, strike benefits from union funds, workers’ compensation, veterans benefits (with the exception noted below), public assistance (including Temporary Assistance for Needy Families, Supplemental Security Income, Emergency Assistance money payments, and non-Federally funded General Assistance or General Relief money payments); training stipends; alimony, child support, and military family allotments or other regular support from an absent family member or someone not living in the household; private pensions, government employee pensions (including military retirement pay), and regular insurance or annuity payments; college or university scholarships, grants, fellowships, and assistantships; and dividends, interest, net rental income, net royalties, and periodic receipts from estates or trusts; and net gambling or lottery winnings.
use_case: Early Learning -> Program Compliance Early Learning -> Program Entry
format: Numeric - up to 2 digits after decimal place
usage_notes: Family Income is calculated based on the method specified by “Income Calculation Method.”

name: Included in Counted Family Size
definition: Denotes whether this family member is counted in the family size as it pertains to the federal poverty level

name: Income Calculation Method

name: Marital Status
definition: The marital status of the person as of today.
usage_notes: This element supports FAFSA questions related to parent's marital status and student's marital status. The option set was developed using Census classifications.

name: Number of People in Family
definition: Total number of persons in immediate family. Family means for the purposes of the regulations in this part all persons: (i) Living in the same household who are: (A) Supported by the income of the parent(s) or guardian(s) of the child enrolling or participating in the program; or (B) Related to the child by blood, marriage, or adoption; or   (ii) Related to the child enrolling or participating in the program as parents or siblings, by blood, marriage, or adoption.
use_case: Early Learning -> Program Entry
format: Integer - greater than or equal to 0

usage_notes: For FAFSA, this includes the number of family members that are in the household, including the student, their spouse, children, and any other persons living in the household to whom they will provide more than half of their support

name: Economic Research Service Rural-Urban Continuum Code
definition: Rural-Urban Continuum Codes form a classification scheme that distinguishes metropolitan (metro) counties by the population size of their metro area, and nonmetropolitan (nonmetro) counties by degree of urbanization and adjacency to a metro area or areas. The metro and nonmetro categories have been subdivided into three metro and six nonmetro groupings, resulting in a nine-part county codification. The codes allow researchers working with county data to break such data into finer residential groups beyond a simple metro-nonmetro dichotomy, particularly for the analysis of trends in nonmetro areas that may be related to degree of rurality and metro proximity.

name: Financial Account Fund Classification
definition: A fund is a separate fiscal and accounting entity with a self-balancing set of accounts recording cash and other financial resources, together with all related liabilities and residual equities or balances or changes therein.
usage_notes: Based on codes specified in the NCES Handbook "Financial Accounting for Local and State School Systems: 2014 Edition".

name: Financial Account Name
definition: The name given to the financial account in an organization's accounting system.

name: Financial Account Number
definition: A number given to a financial account within a local source accounting system. The number may be a concatenation of a standard  prefix for the type of account with digits added that have specific meaning within the local system.

name: Financial Account Program Code
definition: A program is a plan of activities and procedures designed to accomplish a predetermined objective or set of objectives. The program classification provides the organization with a framework to classify instructional and other expenditures by program to determine cost.

name: Financial Account Program Name
definition: The name given to the program area in an organization's accounting system.

name: Financial Account Program Number
definition: A number given to a program area within an organization's accounting system.

name: Financial Account Revenue Code
definition: These codes are for recording revenue and other receivables by source.  Major revenue categories have codes ending in 00 and are further subdivided.
usage_notes:
Based on codes specified in the NCES Handbook "Financial Accounting for Local and State School Systems: 2014 Edition".

Early Learning: If related to an "in kind" contribution use codes 1920 or 100.

name: Financial Accounting Date
definition: The date of a financial transaction or when an account balance is reported.

name: Financial Accounting Period Actual Value
definition: The actual value of a financial account for the specified accounting period or fiscal year.
format: Numeric - up to 2 digits after decimal place

name: Financial Accounting Period Budgeted Value
definition: The budgeted value of a financial account for the specified accounting period or fiscal year.
format: Numeric - up to 2 digits after decimal place

name: Financial Accounting Period Encumbered Value
definition: The planned or obligated expense value of a financial account for the specified accounting period or fiscal year.
format: Numeric - up to 2 digits after decimal place
usage_notes: Used for purchase order balances, the value not already included in "Financial Accounting Period Actual Value" as an expense.

name: Financial Accounting Value
definition: The value of a financial account balance or transaction.
format: Numeric - up to 2 digits after decimal place
usage_notes: Used to represent a point-in-time transaction or snapshot of an account/fund balance. Use “Financial Accounting Period Budgeted Value”, “Financial Accounting Period Actual Value”, and “Financial Accounting Period Encumbered Value” for values representing a period (with begin and end dates).

name: Financial Expenditure Function Code
definition: The function describes the activity for which a service or material object is acquired. The functions of an organization are classified into five broad areas: instruction, support services, operation of non-instructional services, facilities acquisition and construction, and debt service. Functions are further classified into sub functions.
usage_notes: Based on codes specified in the NCES Handbook "Financial Accounting for Local and State School Systems: 2014 Edition".

name: Financial Expenditure Level of Instruction Code
definition: This classification permits expenditures to be segregated by instructional level.
usage_notes: Based on codes specified in the NCES Handbook "Financial Accounting for Local and State School Systems: 2014 Edition".

name: Financial Expenditure Object Code
definition: This classification is used to describe the service or commodity obtained as the result of a specific expenditure.  Nine major object categories have codes ending in 00 and are further subdivided.
usage_notes: Based on codes specified in the NCES Handbook "Financial Accounting for Local and State School Systems: 2014 Edition".

name: Financial Expenditure Project Reporting Code
definition: The project/reporting code permits organizations to accumulate expenditures to meet a variety of specialized reporting requirements at the local, state, and federal levels. It is a three-digit code with the format 00X. The first two digits identify the particular funding source, authority, or expenditure purpose for which a special record or report is required. The third digit is available to identify particular projects and the fiscal year of the appropriation within that funding source. Each classification is presented by a code range followed by a description.
usage_notes:
Based on the following code conventions specified in the NCES Handbook "Financial Accounting for Local and State School Systems: 2014 Edition":

010 to 190 Local Projects. Expenditures that require specialized reporting and are funded from local sources.

200 to 390 State Projects. Expenditures that require specialized reporting for categorically funded state programs.

400 to 990 Federal Projects. Expenditures that require specialized reporting to the federal government directly or through the state.

1000 Noncategorical. Expenditures that do not require specialized reporting.

usage_notes: This is the Hire Date beginning consecutive employment with the current employer in the same Professional-Educational Job Classification. A person may change positions within the same organization and job classification without triggering a new hire date. For example a teacher originally hire to teach 3rd grade may be reassigned to 4th grade.  However, a change of job classifications, e.g. from teacher to principal, would trigger a new Hire Date.

usage_notes:
CEDS "Identifier" elements reflect the intent of the XSD:Token format, i.e. a string in which carriage return, line feed, and tab characters have been removed as well as any internal sequences of two or more spaces and any leading or trailing spaces.

An Identifier MAY be a Universally Unique Identifier (UUID) / Globally Unique Identifier (GUID), i.e.128-bit unique identifiers generated according to the algorithms and encoding standards of RFC 4122.

name: Longitude
definition: The east or west angular distance from the prime meridian that, when combined with latitude, reflects an estimation of where the address is physically situated.

name: State Abbreviation
definition: The abbreviation for the state (within the United States) or outlying area in which an address is located.

name: Facility Financing Fee Type
definition: The type of fee that one must pay when getting a mortgage.

name: Facility Lease Amount
definition: The amount of money the school must pay to rent the facility that it is in.
format: Numeric - up to 2 digits after decimal place

name: Facility Lease Amount Category
definition: The category of payment that a school must pay to rent the facility that it is in.

name: Facility Lease Type
definition: The type of agreement that allows the use and possession of a school, building, or other facility from a third party in return for a regularly scheduled installment payment over an agreed-upon period.

name: Facility Mortgage Interest Amount
definition: The amount the borrower pays the lender to compensate the lender for the use of money to purchase a building or facility.
format: Numeric - up to 2 digits after decimal place

name: Facility Mortgage Interest Type
definition: The type of interest paid on a mortgage to the lender to compensate the lender for the use of money to purchase a building or facility.

name: Facility Mortgage Type
definition: The status of a mortgage as it relates to priority of payment.

name: Facility Total Assessed Value
definition: The total assessed value of property that constitutes the basis for public borrowing.
format: Numeric - up to 2 digits after decimal place

name: Building Air Distribution System Type
definition: The primary means by which air is circulated, freshened, and exhausted.

name: Building Communications Management Component System Type
definition: The type of system, interface, and management components for carrying voice, video, and data throughout a building.

name: Building Cooling Generation System Type
definition: The type of mechanical systems and building designs used for cooling.

name: Building Electrical System Type
definition: The components and system required to distribute electricity throughout the building or site.

name: Building Fire Protection System Type
definition: The type of system that protects the facility against fire.

name: Building HVAC System Type
definition: The building service system that provides for heating, ventilation and air-conditioning.

name: Building Heating Generation System Type
definition: The method by which the heat is distributed and delivered throughout the room(s) or building.

name: Building Institutional Equipment Description
definition: Equipment that is installed for use in support of instructional program such as kilns for art, planetarium equipment for astronomy, fitness equipment for physical education.

name: Building Mechanical Conveying System Type
definition: Mechanical means for moving people and equipment within buildings.

name: Building Mechanical System Type
definition: The major manufactured systems required to operate a building.

name: Building Plumbing System Type
definition: The component of an on-site system for supplying, eliminating, and treating water.

name: Building Security System Type
definition: The type of system that protects the facility from intrusion.

name: Building System Type
definition: The type of system that is installed in the building or site.

name: Building Technology Wiring System Type
definition: The means through which voice, video, audio, and data information are conveyed.

name: Building Vertical Transportation System Type
definition: The type of system used to convey persons or freight between floors.

name: Facility Applicable Federal Mandate Type
definition: The particular federal law, regulation, or standard that pertains to a school facility.

name: Facility Compliance Status
definition: An indication of whether the school, building, site, system, component, equipment, vehicle, or fixture conforms to the requirements or standards specified in federal, state, or local standards or codes or other officially required guidelines or regulations.

name: Facility Federal Mandate Interest Type
definition: The area of interest controlled by a federal law, regulation, or standard that pertains to a school facility.

name: Facility Location of Hazardous Materials
definition: The location at which the identified hazardous material is found.

name: Facility Nearby Environmental Hazard Description
definition: Description of any type of environmental hazards within range of the facility that has the potential to seriously affect the health, safety and operation of school facilities and their occupants.

name: Facility State or Local Mandate Interest Type
definition: The area of interest controlled by a law, rule, regulation, or standard of state and local governments that pertains to public school facilities.

name: Facility State or Local Mandate Name
definition: The specific law, rule, regulation, or standard of a state or local government that pertains to public school facilities.

name: Facility System or Component Condition
definition: The rating of the system or component functions under the demands of its regular operation.

name: Component or Fixture Check Date
definition: The month, day, and year that the condition of a system, component, equipment, or fixture was  checked.

name: Component or Fixture Scheduled Serviced Date
definition: The month, day, and year a major component, system, equipment, or fixture is scheduled to be serviced for preventive or routine maintenance.

name: Component or Fixture Serviced Date
definition: The month, day, and year a system, component, equipment, or fixture was serviced for repair or routine maintenance.

name: Component or Fixture Useful Life
definition: The anticipated time (in years) from the time of installation or service that a properly maintained system, component, equipment, or fixture is expected to operate effectively and efficiently.

name: Building Administrative Space Type
definition: The space designed primarily for conducting administrative and business functions.

name: Building Architect Name
definition: The name of the architect of record for the building.

name: Building Architectural Firm Name
definition: The name of the architectural firm responsible for the building design.

name: Building Art Specialty Space Type
definition: The space designed to support the teaching and learning of 2 dimensional or 3 dimensional visual arts.

name: Building Assembly Space Type
definition: An area designed primarily for theater productions, assemblies, and other large gatherings.

name: Building Basic Classroom Design Type
definition: A classroom designed for instruction of a particular age group, but not a specific subject.

name: Building Career-Technical Education Space Type
definition: The classroom, laboratory, or shop specially located, designed, furnished, and equipped to support instruction of technical and technology related curriculum, usually tied to particular industry, for example, bio-tech, construction, or agriculture.

name: Building Circulation Space Type
definition: A space designed to enable people to move within the building.

name: Building Design Type
definition: The primary design or purpose of a building, as determined by its physical layout and built-in systems and equipment, regardless of its current use.

name: Building Environmental or Energy Performance Rating Category
definition: The primary groupings that rating organizations use to evaluate environmental sustainability and energy use.

name: Building Food Service Space Type
definition: The space located, designed, furnished and equipped to support meal programs.

name: Building Full Service Kitchen Type
definition: The type of kitchen housed in the facility as defined by whether it prepares food to be served onsite and/or at additional locations.

name: Building Indoor Athletic or Physical Education Space Type
definition: The indoor space designed, located, furnished, and equipped for instruction and support of a physical education curriculum and athletic program.

name: Building Library or Media Center Specialty Space Type
definition: The primary and auxiliary space designed to provide and support student and staff access to books, periodicals, software, videos, and the Internet.

name: Building Operations or Maintenance Space Type
definition: The area designed primarily for conducting activities concerned with maintaining the grounds, buildings, and equipment.

name: Building Outdoor Athletic or Physical Education Space Type
definition: The outdoor space designed, located, furnished, and equipped for instruction and support of a physical education curriculum and athletic program.

name: Building Outdoor or Non-athletic Space Type
definition: The outdoor space located, designed, furnished, and equipped primarily for recreation, play and outdoor environmental education.

name: Building Performing Arts Specialty Space Type
definition: The space designed, located, furnished, and equipped for instruction and support of music and drama curricula and productions.

name: Building School Design Type
definition: The physical layout and character of a school facility, as determined by age groups served and educational programs provided.

name: Building Science Specialty Space Type
definition: The space designed, located, furnished, and equipped for instruction and experimentation in science.

name: Building Site Improvement Description
definition: A description of the designed and constructed improvements made to a site.

name: Building Space Design Type
definition: The primary design or purpose of a space, as determined by its physical layout and built-in systems and equipment, regardless of its current use.

name: Building Special Education Specialty Space Type
definition: The space designed, located, furnished, and equipped to support instruction of children with special physical, emotional, and/or educational needs.

name: Building Student Support Space Type
definition: The space designed to provide student support services such as administrative, technical (e.g., guidance and health), and logistical support to facilitate and enhance instruction.

name: Facility Compliance Determination Date
definition: The month, day, and year that the school, building, site, system, component, equipment, or fixture compliance status was determined.

name: Facility Compliance Name
definition: The name of the inspection or process that indicates conformity to the requirements or standards specified in federal, state, or local standards or codes.

name: Facility Component Deficiency Description
definition: A description of the component, system, or finish that needs replacement, repair, or maintenance to perform at an optimal level.

name: Facility Component Identification Code
definition: A unique number or alphanumeric code assigned to a component by a school, school system, state, or other agency or entity.

name: Facility Estimated Cost to Eliminate Deferred Maintenance
definition: The estimated cost to bring systems, components, finishes, fixtures, or equipment to a state of good repair.
format: Numeric - up to 2 digits after decimal place

name: Facility Furnishings Type
definition: Moveable assets that are provided so the building or interior assets can be utilized by occupants for their intended purposes.

name: Facility Hazardous Condition Expected Remediation Date
definition: The month, day, and year by which a hazardous condition of a site or building is expected to be remediated.

name: Facility Inspection Score Result Description
definition: The description of a meaningful raw score of statistical expression of the performance on an inspection.

name: Facility Inspection Violation Description
definition: A description of the standard violation(s) found in the inspection.

name: Facility Site Outdoor Area Type
definition: The designated constructed outdoor area on a public school site.

name: Facility Space Description
definition: A description of the space, as determined by its physical layout and built-in systems and equipment.

name: Hazardous Material or Condition Description
definition: A description of the seriousness a threat or hazardous material poses.

name: Hazardous Material or Condition Testing Date
definition: The month, day, and year that the site or building is tested for a specific hazardous material.

name: Installation Date
definition: The year in which the system, component, equipment, or fixture was originally installed.

name: Life-cycle Cost
definition: The total cost of acquiring, owning, operating, and disposing of a building, facility, or piece of equipment over its useful life.
format: Numeric - up to 2 digits after decimal place

name: Building Addition Code
definition: A unique number or alphanumeric code assigned to a building addition by a school, school system, state, or other agency or entity.

name: Building Addition Description
definition: A description of the permanent structure added to the original building.

name: Building Area
definition: The sum of the areas at each floor level included within the principal outside faces of exterior walls, including roofed areas with finished floors that may not have exterior walls, but are connected to the main building. This sum should include all stories or areas having floor surfaces with clear standing head room (6.5 feet or 1.98 meters) but omit architectural setbacks or projections.

name: Building Historic Status
definition: An indication of whether or not a building is eligible to be or has been declared a landmark or historic building.

name: Building Number of Stories
definition: The number of stories in a building, excluding the basement if its ceiling is less than three feet above ground level.

name: Building Primary Use Type
definition: The primary use type of the building in which a school is located.

name: Building Year Built
definition: The year a building was constructed, as indicated by cornerstone or official government records.

name: Building Year of Last Modernization
definition: The most recent year that a comprehensive upgrade of ALL major building systems and components was completed, such that it functions as a modern building, as measured by a facility condition index not greater than 15%.

name: Campus Facility Type
definition: The primary purpose for which a campus is designed and/or used.

name: Campus Status
definition: The generalized use or control of a campus, independent of program type.

name: Facilities Identifier
definition: A locally assigned unique number or alphanumeric code used to capture precise information on locations specific to a school (e.g., building number, class number, hall number, school bus number, computer station number, or internet protocol (IP) address).
usage_notes:
CEDS "Identifier" elements reflect the intent of the XSD:Token format, i.e. a string in which carriage return, line feed, and tab characters have been removed as well as any internal sequences of two or more spaces and any leading or trailing spaces.

An Identifier MAY be a Universally Unique Identifier (UUID) / Globally Unique Identifier (GUID), i.e.128-bit unique identifiers generated according to the algorithms and encoding standards of RFC 4122.

name: Facility Acquisition Date
definition: The date the property/facility was acquired.

name: Facility Addition Year
definition: The year the construction on the addition was completed.

name: Facility Block Number Area
definition: The informal description of location sometimes used in rural areas, for example, "from the highway to the railroad tracks."

name: Facility Building Name
definition: The full, legally accepted or popularly accepted name of a building.

name: Facility Building Permanency
definition: An indication of whether the building is built for permanent use in the same location or is relocatable.

name: Facility Census Tract
definition: The census tract number of the school site.

name: Facility Construction Date
definition: The month, day, and year on which construction of a building, addition, or improvement was completed.

name: Facility Construction Date Type
definition: Designation of the nature of the construction completion date.

name: Facility Construction Material Type
definition: The primary material used for the construction of a building.

name: Facility Construction Year
definition: The year the building was first constructed.

name: Facility Expected Life
definition: The time, in years, of the expected useful life of a facility for the purposes of depreciation.

name: Facility Ownership Indicator
definition: Indicates the public or private entity holds legal title to the building and/or site.

name: Facility Replacement Value
definition: The estimated cost of replacing a facility using current per square foot estimates of total project costs.
format: Numeric - up to 2 digits after decimal place

name: Facility Site Area
definition: The total number of acres in a continuous piece of land, to the nearest tenth, including undeveloped areas as well as areas occupied by buildings, walks, drives, parking facilities, and other improvements.
format: Numeric - up to 1 digit after decimal place

name: Facility Site Identifier
definition: The lot and square number, or equivalent unique municipal number identification, of a parcel of land.

name: Facility Site Improvement Location Type
definition: The type of location of the designed and constructed improvements made to a site.

name: Organization Identification System
definition: A coding scheme that is used for identification and record-keeping purposes by schools, social services, or other agencies to refer to an organization.
use_case: Early Learning -> Program Quality

name: Organization Identifier
definition: A unique number or alphanumeric code assigned to an organization by a school, school system, a state, or other agency or entity.
use_case: Early Learning -> Program Quality
usage_notes:
CEDS "Identifier" elements reflect the intent of the XSD:Token format, i.e. a string in which carriage return, line feed, and tab characters have been removed as well as any internal sequences of two or more spaces and any leading or trailing spaces.

An Identifier MAY be a Universally Unique Identifier (UUID) / Globally Unique Identifier (GUID), i.e.128-bit unique identifiers generated according to the algorithms and encoding standards of RFC 4122.

name: Organization Name
definition: The name of a non-person entity such as an organization, institution, agency or business.
use_case: Early Learning -> Staff Quality

name: Organization Relationship Type
definition: The nature of one organization’s relationship to another.
usage_notes: Related Body would be used for a use case in which no hierarchy exists, such as a foundation related to a postsecondary institution. Neither organization has authority over the other, but is related to one another.

name: Organization Type
definition: The type of educational organization or entity.
usage_notes: This element is used in data models that are normalized and identifies the primary role of the organization.

name: Short Name of Organization
definition: The name of the organization, which could be abbreviated form of the full legally accepted name.
usage_notes: An abbreviated name of an institution is commonly used, especially in reports and applications, e.g. a K12 school with the full legal name "Dr. Martin Luther King, Jr. Elementary School" may use "King Elementary".

name: Building Charter School Realty Access Type
definition: The type of real estate vehicle through which a public charter school has access and control of its building space.

name: Building Cleaning Standard Type
definition: The standard for cleanliness, and benchmarks for how much space can be assigned to one properly supplied custodian to meet these standards.

name: Building Date of Certificate of Occupancy
definition: The month, day and year in which a certificate of occupancy was granted by the appropriate local authority.

name: Building Energy Conservation Measure Type
definition: The type of modification to, or replacement of, a piece of equipment or building shell/system that increases energy efficiency.

name: Building Energy Service Company Name
definition: The name of the company that designs, procures, finances, installs, maintains, and guarantees the performance of energy conservation measures in an owner's facility or facilities.

name: Building Energy Source Type
definition: The source of energy that directly powers a school district facility or building system.

name: Facilities Management Emergency Type
definition: The type of abnormal and urgent circumstances that disrupt the normal operation of the building, threaten the health and safety of the occupants, or require an emergency response.

name: Facilities Mandate Authority Type
definition: The authority that mandates through law, regulation, or standard that pertains to a specific mandate.

name: Facilities Plan Description
definition: A description of the management and accountability plan.

name: Facilities Plan Type
definition: The type of management and accountability plan.

name: Facility Audit Date
definition: The month, day, and year of the systematic review or audit of facility quality, management, decision making processes, controls, schedule and cost.

name: Facility Audit Type
definition: The type of systematic review or audit of facility quality, management, decision making processes, controls, schedule and cost.

name: Facility Capital Program Management Type
definition: The type of management organization for planning, design, and construction of major capital projects.

name: Facility Compliance Agency Type
definition: The type of agency that has ultimate responsibility for the compliance determination.

name: Facility Hazardous Materials or Condition Type
definition: The type of hazardous materials or conditions tested for at a site or building.

name: Facility Joint Development Type
definition: The type of development where two or more entities partner to plan, site, design, and/or build a new school or renovate an existing school to better support the joint use of the building and/or land.

name: Facility Maintenance Standard Type
definition: The standard for maintenance of a component, system, or building.

name: Facility Naturally Occurring Hazard Type
definition: Type of natural hazard that can affect the health, safety and operation of school facilities and their occupants.

name: Facility Operations Management Type
definition: The type of management arrangements whereby a district oversees and manages its facilities operations.

name: Facility Standard Type
definition: An indication of the district or state requirements or guidelines for the design and construction of school facilities.

name: Facility Utility Provider Type
definition: An indication of how utilities are supplied to a site or a building by a company or provider.

name: Facility Utility Type
definition: The type of utility used in the operation of a facility.

name: Adjusted Capacity
definition: The maximum number of participants that can be served in a program.

name: Adjusted Capacity Reason Type
definition: Identifies the reason for adjusted capacity in a program.

name: Available Utilized Instructional Space
definition: An indication that the instruction space in a school is used in the calculation of student capacity.

name: Building Capacity Factor Indicator
definition: A designation as to whether the space is included in the calculation of school building capacity under state or local guidelines.

name: Building Community Use Space Type
definition: The space designed primarily for community or shared use.

name: Building Hours of Public Use Per Week
definition: The number of hours that all or part of a building is used for purposes other than general education by the community or other organizations.

name: Building Instructional Space Factor Type
definition: A designation as to whether the space is considered an instructional space under state or local guidelines.

name: Building Joint Use Rationale Type
definition: The reasons for permitting and participating in joint-use.

name: Building Joint Use Scheduling Type
definition: The type of designation of non school district users by the amount of time they have access to public school for joint use.

name: Building Joint User Type
definition: The types of users sharing school district controlled, owned, or utilized facilities.

name: Building Net Area of Instructional Space
definition: The area of space directly used for instruction excluding circulation, administration, student services, and building support.
format: Numeric - up to 2 digits after decimal place

name: Building Number of Teaching Stations
definition: The number of teaching stations, as defined by how many spaces have, or could have, a teacher assigned to them for classroom instruction.

name: Building Public Use Policy Description
definition: A description of the policy that enables the community or other organizations to use all or part of a building for purposes other than general education.

name: Building Site Use Restrictions Type
definition: A characterization of a site that would define restrictions or opportunities.

name: Building Space Utilization Area
definition: The area in square feet measured between the principal wall that faces at or near floor level, including alcove spaces, and the outer limits of space designed to serve the activity. Structural space is excluded.
format: Numeric - up to 2 digits after decimal place

name: Building Unassigned Space Indicator
definition: An indication that the space in a school, including circulation, administration offices, support spaces, and common areas, is not part of the calculation for capacity.

name: Building Use Type
definition: How a building is principally used, regardless of its original design.

name: Enrollment Capacity
definition: Maximum number of age-appropriate students who can be enrolled.
usage_notes: Enrollment capacity can be collected at a variety of levels, such as classroom, grade, school, and facility.

name: Facility Enrollment Capacity
definition: The maximum number of age appropriate students who can be enrolled in a facility such that the district's programmatic, operational, and student/teacher work load requirements are met.
usage_notes: This element will be phased out in version 12. It is being replaced by Enrollment Capacity.

name: Facility Space Use Type
definition: The primary use of a space, as determined by its physical layout and built-in systems and equipment, regardless of its original design.

name: Organization Region GeoJSON
definition: The geo-political area of the organization's facility, building, or site.

name: Data Collection Academic School Year
definition: The year for a reported school session for which the data is applicable.

name: Data Collection Close Date
definition: The date the data collection closes or ends.

name: Data Collection Description
definition: The description of what is included in the data within the context of the data collection based on the source system and collection period as defined by the Data Collection Open Date and Data Collection Close Date.

name: Data Collection Name
definition: A human readable name used to identify the data within the collection.

name: Data Collection Open Date
definition: The date the data collection opens or commences.

name: Data Collection School Year
definition: The year for a reported school session in which the data collection occurs.

name: Data Collection Status
definition: A process indicator of the level of stability, quality, and/or preparedness of the collection of data.

name: Source System Data Collection Identifier
definition: The identifier specified by the source system that uniquely identifies the data collection.

name: Source System Name
definition: The name of the source system that provided the data within the collection.

name: Record Status Creator Entity
definition: The type of entity that created or indicated the Record Status Type

name: Record Status Date
definition: The date the record was marked with the Record Status Type.

name: Record Status Type
definition: A process indicator of the level of stability, quality, and/or preparedness of the record.

name: Count Date
definition: The effective month, day, and year on which the data was counted.
usage_notes: Implementation Note: This element is not defined in the CEDS Normalized Data Schema (NDS) reference model. It represents an implementation variable. Typical use would be in a reporting data store (RDS) rather than in a unit level operational data store.

name: Record End Date Time
definition: The end date and, optionally, time that a record is active as used to support version control.
usage_notes: See CEDS Integrated Data Store for use in version control. All CEDS Exit and End Dates represent the last day of the date range specified.

name: Record Start Date Time
definition: The start date and, optionally, time that a record is active as used to support version control.
usage_notes: See CEDS Integrated Data Store for use in version control.

name: Report Date
definition: The month, day, and year on which a report was produced.
usage_notes: Implementation Note: This element is not defined in the CEDS Normalized Data Schema (NDS) reference model. It represents an implementation variable. Typical use would be in a reporting data store (RDS) rather than in a unit level operational data store.

name: Submission Date
definition: The month, day, and year on which a report is submitted.
usage_notes: Implementation Note: This element is not defined in the CEDS Normalized Data Schema (NDS) reference model. It represents an implementation variable. Typical use would be in a reporting data store (RDS) rather than in a unit level operational data store.

name: Crisis Code
definition: A unique number or alphanumeric code used to identify a crisis. This code should be able to accommodate numerous crises within a single school year. It is associated with the displaced student identifier in order to link a crisis to a student who was displaced or otherwise affected by the event. If the same code values are to be used over multiple years, it is important to have enough crisis-specific items (e.g., school year, date/time) to keep the events unique over time.

name: Crisis Description
definition: A description of the crisis that caused the displacement of students.

name: Crisis End Date
definition: The date on which the crisis ceased to affect the agency.
usage_notes: All CEDS Exit and End Dates represent the last day of the date range specified, such as the last day that a person was enrolled, participated, or received services.

name: Crisis Name
definition: The name of the crisis that caused the displacement of students.

name: Crisis Start Date
definition: The year, month and day on which the crisis affected the agency. This date may not be the same as the date the crisis occurred if evacuation orders are implemented in anticipation of a crisis.

name: Crisis Type
definition: The type or category of crisis (ex., chemical, earthquake, flood, wildfire, etc.).

name: Calendar Event Date
definition: The date of the scheduled or unscheduled calendar event.

name: Calendar Event Day Name
definition: A name used for the day of the calendar event.

name: Calendar Event Type
definition: A type of scheduled or unscheduled calendar event.

name: End Time
definition: The ending hour, minute and second.

name: Start Time
definition: The starting hour, minute and second.

name: Alternate Day Name
definition: An alternate name used for the school day, typically used for the bell schedule (e.g., Blue day, Red day).

name: Calendar Code
definition: A unique number assigned by a school district to a school calendar.

name: Calendar Description
definition: A description or identification of the calendar.

name: School Year
definition: The year for a reported school session.
use_case: K-12 -> Teacher Compensation Survey
usage_notes: For academic years that span a calendar year this is the four digit year-end.  E.g. 2013 for 2012-2013

name: Session Attendance Term Indicator
definition: Indicates that the session is an attendance term.

name: Session Begin Date
definition: The year, month and day on which a session begins.
use_case: K-12 -> High School Generated Transcript K-12 -> LEA-to-LEA Student Record Exchange K-12 -> LEA-to-SEA Student Record Exchange K-12 -> Teacher-Student Data Link -> Class Section

name: Session Code
definition: A local code given to the session, usually for a session that represents a term within the school year such as a marking term.

name: Session Description
definition: A short description of the Session.

name: Session End Date
definition: The year, month and day on which a session ends.
use_case: K-12 -> High School Generated Transcript K-12 -> LEA-to-LEA Student Record Exchange K-12 -> LEA-to-SEA Student Record Exchange K-12 -> Teacher-Student Data Link -> Class Section
usage_notes: All CEDS Exit and End Dates represent the last day of the date range specified, such as the last day that a person was enrolled, participated, or received services.

name: Session End Time
definition: The hour, minute and second on which a session ends.
use_case: Early Learning -> Access to Services Early Learning -> Program Quality

name: Session Marking Term Indicator
definition: Indicates that the session is a marking term.

name: Session Scheduling Term Indicator
definition: Indicates that the session is a scheduling term.

name: Session Start Time
definition: The hour, minute and second on which a session begins.
use_case: Early Learning -> Access to Services Early Learning -> Program Quality

name: Attendance Event Date
definition: The date on which an attendance event takes place.

name: Attendance Event Type
definition: The type of attendance event.

name: Attendance Status
definition: The status of a person's attendance associated with an Attendance Event Type and Attendance Event Date in an organization-person-role context.

name: Available Carnegie Unit Credit
definition: Measured in Carnegie units, the amount of credit available to a student who successfully meets the objectives of the course. A course meeting every day for one period of the school day over the span of a school year offers one Carnegie unit. A Carnegie unit is thus a measure of "seat time" rather than a measure of attainment of the course objectives.
use_case: K-12 -> High School Generated Transcript K-12 -> LEA-to-LEA Student Record Exchange K-12 -> LEA-to-SEA Student Record Exchange K-12 -> Teacher-Student Data Link -> Class Section
format: Numeric - up to 2 digits after decimal place

name: Course Code System
definition: A system that is used to identify the organization of subject matter and related learning experiences provided for the instruction of students.
use_case: K-12 -> High School Generated Transcript K-12 -> LEA-to-LEA Student Record Exchange K-12 -> LEA-to-SEA Student Record Exchange K-12 -> Teacher-Student Data Link -> Class Section

name: Course Department Name
definition: Department with jurisdiction over this course.

name: Course Identifier
definition: The actual code that identifies the organization of subject matter and related learning experiences provided for the instruction of students.
use_case: K-12 -> High School Generated Transcript K-12 -> LEA-to-LEA Student Record Exchange K-12 -> LEA-to-SEA Student Record Exchange K-12 -> Teacher-Student Data Link -> Class Section Postsecondary Education -> Transition
usage_notes:
CEDS "Identifier" elements reflect the intent of the XSD:Token format, i.e. a string in which carriage return, line feed, and tab characters have been removed as well as any internal sequences of two or more spaces and any leading or trailing spaces.

An Identifier MAY be a Universally Unique Identifier (UUID) / Globally Unique Identifier (GUID), i.e.128-bit unique identifiers generated according to the algorithms and encoding standards of RFC 4122.

name: Course Level Approval Indicator
definition: An indication that there are school or program developed requirements for student participation in the course.
usage_notes: This element is used in conjunction with Course Level Characteristic.

name: Course Level Characteristic
definition: An indication of the general nature and difficulty of instruction provided throughout a course.
use_case: K-12 -> High School Generated Transcript K-12 -> LEA-to-LEA Student Record Exchange K-12 -> LEA-to-SEA Student Record Exchange K-12 -> Teacher-Student Data Link -> Class Section Postsecondary Education -> Transition

name: Course Repeatability Maximum Number
definition: The maximum number of times the course may be taken or completed for credit.

name: Course Section Assessment Reporting Method
definition: The method that the instructor of the course uses to report the performance and achievement of all students. It may be a qualitative method such as individualized teacher comments or a quantitative method such as a letter or a numerical grade. In some cases, more than one type of reporting method may be used.
use_case: K-12 -> High School Generated Transcript School Readiness

name: Course Title
definition: The descriptive name given to a course of study offered in a school or other institution or organization. In departmentalized classes at the elementary, secondary, and postsecondary levels (and for staff development activities), this refers to the name by which a course is identified (e.g., American History, English III). For elementary and other non-departmentalized classes, it refers to any portion of the instruction for which a grade or report is assigned (e.g., reading, composition, spelling, and language arts).
use_case: K-12 -> High School Generated Transcript K-12 -> LEA-to-LEA Student Record Exchange K-12 -> LEA-to-SEA Student Record Exchange K-12 -> Teacher-Student Data Link -> Class Section

name: Credit Unit Type
definition: The type of credits or units of value awarded for the completion of a course.
use_case: K-12 -> High School Generated Transcript K-12 -> LEA-to-LEA Student Record Exchange K-12 -> LEA-to-SEA Student Record Exchange

name: High School Course Requirement
definition: An indication that this course credit is required for a high school diploma.
use_case: K-12 -> High School Generated Transcript K-12 -> LEA-to-LEA Student Record Exchange K-12 -> LEA-to-SEA Student Record Exchange K-12 -> Teacher-Student Data Link -> Class Section

name: Related Competency Definitions
definition: An indication of the competency definition(s) addressed in the Course Section.
alternate_name: Related Learning Standard Items, Related Competency Items

name: School Courses for the Exchange of Data Sequence of Course
definition: Where a specific course lies when it is part of a consecutive sequence of courses. This element should be interpreted as "part 'n' of 'm' parts.
use_case: K-12 -> High School Generated Transcript K-12 -> LEA-to-LEA Student Record Exchange K-12 -> LEA-to-SEA Student Record Exchange K-12 -> Teacher-Student Data Link -> Class Section
usage_notes: For example: if a school offers 4 years of Theater, Theater 3 within this school would be indicated in the sequence elements as 3 4, denoting the 3rd part of a 4-part sequence of courses.

name: Course Section Enrollment Status End Date
definition: The date on which the enrollment status ended related to a student enrolled in an instance of a course.
usage_notes: Enrollment statuses may overlap, for example at one point in time a student may be both pre-registered and wait-listed for enrollment in a course, the start dates may be different and the end dates may be the same as the start date for "enrolled" status when the student moves off the wait list. All CEDS Exit and End Dates represent the last day of the date range specified, such as the last day that a person was enrolled, participated, or received services.

name: Course Section Enrollment Status Start Date
definition: The date on which the enrollment status began related to a student enrolled in an instance of a course.
usage_notes: Enrollment statuses may overlap, for example at one point in time a student may be both pre-registered and wait listed for enrollment in a course, the start dates may be different and the end dates may be the same as the start date for "enrolled" status when the student moves off the wait list.

name: Course Section Enrollment Status Type
definition: The status related to a student enrollment in an instance of a course.
usage_notes: Enrollment statuses may overlap, for example at one point in time a student may be both pre-registered and wait listed for enrollment in a course, the start dates may be different and the end dates may be the same as the start date for "enrolled" status when the student moves off the wait list.

name: Course Section Entry Type
definition: The process by which a student enters a school (Course Section) during a given academic session.
use_case: K-12 -> Teacher-Student Data Link -> Enrollment

name: Course Section Exit Type
definition: The circumstances under which the student exited from membership in a course section.
use_case: K-12 -> Teacher-Student Data Link -> Enrollment

name: Course Section Exit Withdrawal Date
definition: The year, month and day of the first day after the date of a person's last enrollment in a course section.
use_case: K-12 -> Teacher-Student Data Link -> Enrollment
usage_notes: All CEDS Exit and End Dates represent the last day of the date range specified, such as the last day that a person was enrolled, participated, or received services.

name: Enrollment Capacity
definition: Maximum number of age-appropriate students who can be enrolled.
usage_notes: Enrollment capacity can be collected at a variety of levels, such as classroom, grade, school, and facility.

name: Enrollment Entry Date
definition: The month, day, and year on which a person enters and begins to receive instructional services in a school, institution, program, or class-section during a given session.

name: Exit or Withdrawal Status
definition: An indication as to whether an instance of student exit/withdrawal is considered to be of a permanent or temporary nature.
use_case: K-12 -> Teacher-Student Data Link -> Enrollment

name: Grade Level When Course Taken
definition: Student's grade level at time of course.
use_case: K-12 -> High School Generated Transcript K-12 -> LEA-to-LEA Student Record Exchange K-12 -> LEA-to-SEA Student Record Exchange

name: Number of Credits Attempted
definition: The number of credits that a student can earn for enrolling in and completing a given course.
use_case: K-12 -> High School Generated Transcript K-12 -> LEA-to-LEA Student Record Exchange K-12 -> LEA-to-SEA Student Record Exchange
format: Numeric - up to 2 digits after decimal place

name: Number of Credits Earned
definition: The number of credits an individual earns by the successful completion of a course.
use_case: K-12 -> High School Feedback Report K-12 -> High School Generated Transcript K-12 -> LEA-to-LEA Student Record Exchange K-12 -> LEA-to-SEA Student Record Exchange Postsecondary Education -> Transition
format: Numeric - up to 2 digits after decimal place

name: Number of Days Absent
definition: The number of days a person is absent when school is in session during a given reporting period.
use_case: K-12 -> High School Generated Transcript K-12 -> LEA-to-LEA Student Record Exchange K-12 -> LEA-to-SEA Student Record Exchange K-12 -> Teacher-Student Data Link -> Enrollment
format: Numeric - up to 2 digits after decimal place

name: Number of Days Tardy
definition: The number of days a person is tardy when school is in session during a given reporting period.
format: Numeric - up to 2 digits after decimal place

name: Number of Days in Attendance
definition: The number of days a person is present when school is in session during a given reporting period.
use_case: Early Learning -> Program Compliance K-12 -> High School Generated Transcript K-12 -> LEA-to-LEA Student Record Exchange K-12 -> LEA-to-SEA Student Record Exchange K-12 -> Teacher-Student Data Link -> Enrollment
format: Numeric - up to 2 digits after decimal place
usage_notes: Note: This applies to an enrollment period record.  Separate records using this element definition could capture attendance for regular enrollment, an out-of-school program or other program requiring attendance records.  CEDS now supports the detailed attendance events to capture attendance status on any given day, class period, or session.  CEDS generally doesn't include elements for counts when it has the unit level elements to calculate the count.  However, this element has been retained to support the intended use cases, recognizing that the rules for attendance vary based on location.

name: Responsible District Type
definition: The type of responsibility the district has for the student.
use_case: K-12 -> EDFacts

name: Responsible School Type
definition: The type of services/instruction the school is responsible for providing to the student.
use_case: K-12 -> EDFacts

name: Student Course Section Grade Earned
definition: A final indicator of student performance in a course section as submitted by the instructor.
use_case: K-12 -> High School Generated Transcript K-12 -> LEA-to-LEA Student Record Exchange K-12 -> LEA-to-SEA Student Record Exchange

name: Student Course Section Grade Narrative
definition: The narrative of the student performance in a course section as submitted by the instructor.

name: Student Identification System
definition: A coding scheme that is used for identification and record-keeping purposes by schools, social services, or other agencies to refer to a student.
use_case: K-12 -> High School Generated Transcript K-12 -> LEA-to-LEA Student Record Exchange K-12 -> LEA-to-SEA Student Record Exchange K-12 -> Teacher-Student Data Link -> Enrollment Postsecondary Education -> Transition

definition: A unique number or alphanumeric code assigned to a student by a school, school system, a state, or other agency or entity.

name: Grade Value Qualifier
definition: The scale of equivalents, if applicable, for grades awarded as indicators of performance in schoolwork. For example, numerical equivalents for letter grades used in determining a student's Grade Point Average (A=4, B=3, C=2, D=1 in a four-point system) or letter equivalents for percentage grades (90-100%=A, 80-90%=B, etc.)
usage_notes: A list of "Academic Grade Qualifiers" is available from the Association of American Medical Colleges, 2450 N St., N.W., Washington, DC 20037

name: Marking Period Name
definition: The name or description of the marking period (e.g., fall, first marking period).

name: Mid Term Mark
definition: Indicator of student performance at the mid-point of the marking period.
use_case: K-12 -> High School Generated Transcript K-12 -> LEA-to-LEA Student Record Exchange K-12 -> LEA-to-SEA Student Record Exchange

name: Student Course Section Grade Earned
definition: A final indicator of student performance in a course section as submitted by the instructor.

name: Student Course Section Mark Final Indicator
definition: Indicates that the mark is a final mark the learner has earned for the course section.

name: Assignment End Date
definition: The last year, month and day on which the assignment is valid.
usage_notes: All CEDS Exit and End Dates represent the last day of the date range specified, such as the last day that a person was enrolled, participated, or received services.

name: Assignment Start Date
definition: The year, month and day from which the assignment is valid.

name: Classroom Position Type
definition: The type of position the staff member holds in the specific course section.

name: Staff Member Identification System
definition: A coding scheme that is used for identification and record-keeping purposes by schools, social services, registry, or other agencies to refer to a staff member.

name: Staff Member Identifier
definition: A unique number or alphanumeric code assigned to a staff member by a school, school system, a state, registry, or other agency or entity.
