An Identifier MAY be a Universally Unique Identifier (UUID) / Globally Unique Identifier (GUID), i.e.128-bit unique identifiers generated according to the algorithms and encoding standards of RFC 4122.

name: Teacher of Record
definition: Staff member who has a Teacher of Record responsibility for a Class Section based upon the state's definition of Teacher of Record.
use_case: K-12 -> Teacher-Student Data Link -> Staff Assignment
usage_notes: There is usually one Teacher of Record assignment in a Class Section except in the case of co-teaching/team-teaching.

name: Teaching Assignment Contribution Percentage
definition: A percentage used to weight the educator's assigned responsibility for student learning in a Class Section, particularly when more than one educator is assigned to the class section.
use_case: K-12 -> Teacher-Student Data Link -> Staff Assignment
format: Numeric - up to 3 digits before and 2 digits after decimal place

name: Teaching Assignment End Date
definition: The year, month and day on which a teaching assignment ends.
use_case: K-12 -> Teacher-Student Data Link -> Staff Assignment
usage_notes: All CEDS Exit and End Dates represent the last day of the date range specified, such as the last day that a person was employed.

name: Teaching Assignment Role
definition: The role that the Staff Member has been assigned for a Class Section.  (A teacher may have the lead responsibility for one section and serve a supporting role for another section of the same course.)
use_case: K-12 -> Teacher-Student Data Link -> Staff Assignment

name: Teaching Assignment Start Date
definition: The year, month and day on which a teaching assignment begins.
use_case: K-12 -> Teacher-Student Data Link -> Staff Assignment

name: Teacher Student Data Link Exclusion Flag
definition: Indicates that the student is excluded from calculation of value-added or growth attribution calculations used for teacher evaluation.
usage_notes: The context for this element is the intersection of a teacher assignment to a Class/Section and a student enrollment to a Class/Section.  It may be represented in a data model as a separate entity such as Teacher Student Data Link Exclusion.

name: Ability Grouping Status
definition: An indication of whether the school has students who are ability grouped for classroom instruction in mathematics or English/reading/language arts.
use_case: K-12 -> Civil Rights Data Collection

name: Additional Credit Type
definition: The type of credits or units of value available for the completion of a course in addition to Carnegie Units.

name: Adjusted Capacity
definition: The maximum number of participants that can be served in a program.

name: Adjusted Capacity Reason Type
definition: Identifies the reason for adjusted capacity in a program.

name: Advanced Placement Course Code
definition: Course areas for advanced placement or credit.  For a list of codes see http://apcentral.collegeboard.com/apc/public/courses/teachers_corner/index.html .

name: Blended Learning Model Type
definition: A type of formal education program in which a student learns at least in part through online learning, with some element of student control over time, place, path, and/or pace; at least in part in a supervised brick-and-mortar location away from home; and the modalities along each student’s learning path within a course or subject are connected to provide an integrated learning experience.
usage_notes: This may be an attribute of a Course (as designed) or a Class Section (as delivered). It also may be attributed to a school, institution, or program for "whole-school" blended models.

name: Career Cluster
definition: The career cluster that defines the industry or occupational focus which may be associated with a career pathways program, plan of study, or course.
usage_notes: Options from O*NET OnLine an application that was created for the general public to provide broad access to the O*NET database of occupational information. O*NET OnLine offers a variety of search options and occupational data, while My Next Move is a streamlined application for students and job seekers. Both applications were developed for the U.S. Department of Labor by the National Center for O*NET Development.  See onetonline.org for more information.

name: Class Beginning Time
definition: An indication of the time of day the class begins.
use_case: Early Learning -> Access to Services Early Learning -> Program Quality

name: Class Ending Time
definition: An indication of the time of day the class ends.
use_case: Early Learning -> Access to Services Early Learning -> Program Quality

name: Class Meeting Days
definition: The day(s) of the week (e.g., Monday, Wednesday) that the class meets or an indication that a class meets "out-of-school" or "self-paced".

name: Class Period
definition: An indication of the portion of a typical daily session in which students receive instruction in a specified subject (e.g., morning, sixth period, block period, or AB schedules).

name: Classroom Identifier
definition: A unique number or alphanumeric code assigned to a room by a school, school system, state, or other agency or entity.
usage_notes:
CEDS "Identifier" elements reflect the intent of the XSD:Token format, i.e. a string in which carriage return, line feed, and tab characters have been removed as well as any internal sequences of two or more spaces and any leading or trailing spaces.

An Identifier MAY be a Universally Unique Identifier (UUID) / Globally Unique Identifier (GUID), i.e.128-bit unique identifiers generated according to the algorithms and encoding standards of RFC 4122.

name: Classroom Position Type
definition: The type of position the staff member holds in the specific course section.

name: Course Aligned with Standards
definition: An indication whether a course is aligned with the established standards of a curriculum framework.

name: Course Applicable Education Level
definition: The education level, grade level or primary instructional level at which a course is intended.
usage_notes: This element is repeatable for most use cases.  Examples: (1.) SCED identifiers may specify a grade span of two or more grades.  (2) A postsecondary course designed to qualify a student for an associates degree and professional certification could be repeated with both of those options.

name: Course Certification Description
definition: A description of the certification or recognition associated with this course (ex. Networking, CAD, etc.)

name: Course Description
definition: A description of the course content and/or goals. Reference may be made to state or national content standards.

name: Course Funding Program
definition: A program through which the course is funded.
usage_notes: This may be a program targeted to a specific student population (e.g. SPED, ESOL) and the funding guidelines may specify that all or some of the students in the course are members of the subgroup.

name: Course Grade Point Average Applicability
definition: An indicator of whether or not this course being described is included in the computation of the student’s Grade Point Average (GPA).
use_case: K-12 -> High School Generated Transcript K-12 -> LEA-to-LEA Student Record Exchange K-12 -> LEA-to-SEA Student Record Exchange K-12 -> Teacher-Student Data Link -> Class Section

name: Course Interaction Mode
definition: The primary type of interaction, synchronous or asynchronous, defined for the course.
usage_notes: This may be an attribute of a Course (as designed) or an instance of a Class Section (as delivered).

name: Course Level Type
definition: The level of work which is reflected in the credits associated with the academic course being described or the level of the typical individual taking the academic course.

name: Course Section Identifier
definition: A unique number or alphanumeric code assigned by an institution, school, school system, state, or other agency or entity for a particular course-section.
usage_notes:
CEDS "Identifier" elements reflect the intent of the XSD:Token format, i.e. a string in which carriage return, line feed, and tab characters have been removed as well as any internal sequences of two or more spaces and any leading or trailing spaces.

An Identifier MAY be a Universally Unique Identifier (UUID) / Globally Unique Identifier (GUID), i.e.128-bit unique identifiers generated according to the algorithms and encoding standards of RFC 4122.

name: Course Section Instructional Delivery Mode
definition: The primary setting or medium of delivery for the course.

name: Course Section Maximum Capacity
definition: The maximum number of students the Course Section can maintain.
format: Integer - greater than or equal to 0

name: Course Section Single Sex Class Status
definition: Section in a co-educational school where only male or only female students are permitted to take the course.
use_case: K-12 -> Civil Rights Data Collection K-12 -> Teacher-Student Data Link -> Class Section

name: Course Section Time Required for Completion
definition: The actual or estimated number of clock minutes required for course completion. This number is especially important for career and technical education course and may represent (in minutes) the clock hour requirement of the course, the number of minutes (or clock hours) of class time per week, times the number of equivalent weeks the class typically meets.
use_case: K-12 -> Teacher-Student Data Link -> Class Section
format: Integer - greater than or equal to 0

name: Family and Consumer Sciences Course Indicator
definition: An indication that the course is associated with the Family and Consumer Sciences plan of study.

name: Instruction Language
definition: The language of instruction, other than English, used in the program or course.
use_case: K-12 -> Consolidated State Performance Report
usage_notes: The CEDS ISO 639-2 Language Code option set comes from the ISO 639-2 standard, the character encoding in ISO 8859-1 download. Discontinued codes from the ISO standard are not included in the CEDS list.

name: Interdisciplinary Indicator
definition: An indication that the course, projects, and/or learning activities develop knowledge and skills across multiple subject areas and highlight connections between subject area domains, with formal collaboration among teachers across subject areas.

name: National Collegiate Athletic Association Eligibility
definition: An indication that the course is approved for determining NCAA eligibility.

name: Project-Based Learning Indicator
definition: An indication that an instructional model is being implemented wherein a student learns through answering complex questions or solving for real-world problems. Also called problem-based learning, inquiry-based learning, or learning-by-doing.

name: Project-Based Learning Type
definition: The type of project-based instruction being offered.
usage_notes: Select all that apply.

name: Receiving Location of Instruction
definition: The type of location at which instruction or service takes place.

name: Session Attendance Term Indicator
definition: Indicates that the session is an attendance term.

name: Session Begin Date
definition: The year, month and day on which a session begins.
use_case: K-12 -> High School Generated Transcript K-12 -> LEA-to-LEA Student Record Exchange K-12 -> LEA-to-SEA Student Record Exchange K-12 -> Teacher-Student Data Link -> Class Section

name: Session Code
definition: A local code given to the session, usually for a session that represents a term within the school year such as a marking term.

name: Session Description
definition: A short description of the Session.

name: Session Designator
definition: The academic session for which the data are recorded and applicable.
use_case: K-12 -> High School Feedback Report Postsecondary Education -> Transition

name: Session End Date
definition: The year, month and day on which a session ends.
use_case: K-12 -> High School Generated Transcript K-12 -> LEA-to-LEA Student Record Exchange K-12 -> LEA-to-SEA Student Record Exchange K-12 -> Teacher-Student Data Link -> Class Section
usage_notes: All CEDS Exit and End Dates represent the last day of the date range specified, such as the last day that a person was enrolled, participated, or received services.

name: Session Marking Term Indicator
definition: Indicates that the session is a marking term.

name: Session Scheduling Term Indicator
definition: Indicates that the session is a scheduling term.

name: Session Type
definition: A prescribed span of time when an education institution is open, instruction is provided, and students are under the direction and guidance of teachers and/or education institution administration. A session may be interrupted by one or more vacations.
use_case: K-12 -> High School Generated Transcript K-12 -> LEA-to-LEA Student Record Exchange K-12 -> LEA-to-SEA Student Record Exchange K-12 -> Teacher-Student Data Link -> Class Section

name: Timetable Day Identifier
definition: The unique identifier for the locally defined rotation cycle date code when the class meets (e.g., in a two day schedule, valid values could be "A" and "B", or "1" and "2").
usage_notes:
CEDS "Identifier" elements reflect the intent of the XSD:Token format, i.e. a string in which carriage return, line feed, and tab characters have been removed as well as any internal sequences of two or more spaces and any leading or trailing spaces.

An Identifier MAY be a Universally Unique Identifier (UUID) / Globally Unique Identifier (GUID), i.e.128-bit unique identifiers generated according to the algorithms and encoding standards of RFC 4122.

name: Tuition Funded
definition: Indicates that tuition for person's participation in a program, service, or course is funded or partially funded by an external grant program.
usage_notes: The initial use case is for professional development courses/programs, but could apply to student programs/courses as well.

name: Virtual Indicator
definition: An indication that a childcare, early education, or early learning program, school, institution, program, or course section focuses primarily on instruction in which children and teachers are separated by time and/or location and interact through the use of computers and/or telecommunications technology.

name: Disciplinary Action End Date
definition: The year, month and day on which a discipline action ends.
use_case: K-12 -> Civil Rights Data Collection
usage_notes: All CEDS Exit and End Dates represent the last day of the date range specified, such as the last day that a person was enrolled, participated, or received services.

name: Disciplinary Action Start Date
definition: The year, month and day on which a discipline action begins.
use_case: K-12 -> Civil Rights Data Collection

name: Disciplinary Action Taken
definition: Identifies the consequences of an incident for the student(s) involved in an incident as perpetrator(s).
use_case: K-12 -> Civil Rights Data Collection

name: Discipline Action Length Difference Reason
definition: The reason for the difference, if any, between the official and actual lengths of a student’s disciplinary assignment.

name: Discipline Reason
definition: The reason why the student was disciplined.
use_case: K-12 -> EDFacts

name: Duration of Disciplinary Action
definition: The length, in school days, of the disciplinary action.
format: Numeric - up to 2 digits after decimal place

name: Educational Services After Removal
definition: An indication of whether children (students) were provided educational services when removed from the regular school program for disciplinary reasons.

name: Firearm Type
definition: The type of firearm.
use_case: K-12 -> EDFacts

name: Full Year Expulsion
definition: An expulsion with or without services for a period of one full year (i.e., 365 days).

name: IDEA Interim Removal
definition: The type of interim removal from current educational setting experienced by children with disabilities (IDEA).
use_case: K-12 -> EDFacts

name: IDEA Interim Removal Reason
definition: The reasons why children with disabilities were unilaterally removed from their current educational placement to an interim alternative educational setting.
use_case: K-12 -> EDFacts

name: Incident Behavior
definition: Categories of behavior coded for use in describing an incident.

name: Incident Cost
definition: The value of any quantifiable monetary loss directly resulting from the incident. Examples include the value of repairs necessitated by vandalism of a school facility, the value of personnel resources used for repairs or consumed by the incident, the value of stolen items, and the value of time consumed by an incident (e.g., instructional time involved in evacuating a school during a false fire alarm).  Cost may be reported by specific monetary amount or range.

name: Incident Date
definition: The year, month and day on which the incident occurred.

name: Incident Description
definition: The description for an incident.

name: Incident Identifier
definition: A locally assigned unique identifier (within the school or school district) to identify each specific incident or occurrence. The same identifier should be used to document the entire incident even if it included multiple offenses and multiple offenders.
usage_notes:
CEDS "Identifier" elements reflect the intent of the XSD:Token format, i.e. a string in which carriage return, line feed, and tab characters have been removed as well as any internal sequences of two or more spaces and any leading or trailing spaces.

An Identifier MAY be a Universally Unique Identifier (UUID) / Globally Unique Identifier (GUID), i.e.128-bit unique identifiers generated according to the algorithms and encoding standards of RFC 4122.

name: Incident Injury Type
definition: An indication of the occurrence of physical injury to participants involved in the incident and, if so, the level of injury sustained.
usage_notes: Incident Injury Type can be linked to any person involved in the incident.

name: Incident Location
definition: Identifies where the incident occurred and whether or not it occurred on campus.

name: Incident Multiple Offense Type
definition: An indication of whether the offense was primary or secondary in nature when a single incident included more than one type of offense.

name: Incident Perpetrator Identifier
definition: Identifies the perpetrator of the incident by use of a pre-existing unique identifier assigned to a student or staff member by a school or district.
usage_notes:
CEDS "Identifier" elements reflect the intent of the XSD:Token format, i.e. a string in which carriage return, line feed, and tab characters have been removed as well as any internal sequences of two or more spaces and any leading or trailing spaces.

An Identifier MAY be a Universally Unique Identifier (UUID) / Globally Unique Identifier (GUID), i.e.128-bit unique identifiers generated according to the algorithms and encoding standards of RFC 4122.

name: Incident Perpetrator Injury Type
definition: An indication of the occurrence of physical injury to the perpetrator(s) (participants) involved in the incident and‚ if so‚ the level of injury sustained.

name: Incident Perpetrator Type
definition: Information on the type of individual who committed an incident. A “perpetrator” is an individual involved in an incident as an offender (the person who committed the infraction constituting the incident).

name: Incident Person Role Type
definition: The role or type of participation of a person in a discipline incident.

name: Incident Regulation Violated Description
definition: A description of the rule‚ regulation‚ or standard that was violated when an incident occurred (e.g.‚ the identification of a relevant law‚ conduct standard‚ or acceptable use policy).

name: Incident Related to Disability Manifestation
definition: An indication whether a student’s behavior (offense) was a manifestation of‚ or related to‚ a disability condition.
usage_notes: Under IDEA §300.530(e), a manifestation determination must occur within 10 days of any decision to change the child’s placement because of a violation of a code of student conduct.

name: Incident Reported to Law Enforcement Indicator
definition: An indication that the school resource officer or any other law enforcement official was notified about the incident‚ regardless of whether official action is taken.

name: Incident Reporter Type
definition: Information on the type of person who reported the incident. When known and/or if useful, use a more specific option code (e.g., "Counselor" rather than "Professional Staff").

name: Incident Time
definition: An indication of the time of day the incident took place.

name: Incident Time Description Code
definition: A code for the description of the time of day that an incident took place.

name: Incident Victim Identifier
definition: Identifies the victim of the incident by use of a pre-existing unique identifier assigned to a student or staff member by a school or district.
usage_notes:
CEDS "Identifier" elements reflect the intent of the XSD:Token format, i.e. a string in which carriage return, line feed, and tab characters have been removed as well as any internal sequences of two or more spaces and any leading or trailing spaces.

An Identifier MAY be a Universally Unique Identifier (UUID) / Globally Unique Identifier (GUID), i.e.128-bit unique identifiers generated according to the algorithms and encoding standards of RFC 4122.

name: Incident Victim Type
definition: Information on the type of individual who was injured or otherwise harmed as a direct result of the incident. A “victim” is the individual who suffers injury or harm that directly results from the incident.

name: Incident Witness Identifier
definition: Identifies the witness of the incident by use of a pre-existing unique identifier assigned to a student or staff member by a school or district. Using this data element permits linkage to descriptive information about the individual in the student or staff database.
usage_notes:
CEDS "Identifier" elements reflect the intent of the XSD:Token format, i.e. a string in which carriage return, line feed, and tab characters have been removed as well as any internal sequences of two or more spaces and any leading or trailing spaces.

An Identifier MAY be a Universally Unique Identifier (UUID) / Globally Unique Identifier (GUID), i.e.128-bit unique identifiers generated according to the algorithms and encoding standards of RFC 4122.

name: Incident Witness Type
definition: Information on the type of individual who witnessed the incident and can give a firsthand account of an incident that was seen‚ heard‚ or experienced.

name: Related to Zero Tolerance Policy
definition: An indication of whether or not any of the disciplinary actions taken against a student were imposed as a consequence of state or local zero tolerance policies.

name: Reporter Identifier
definition: Identifies the reporter of the incident using  a pre-existing unique student identifier or unique staff identifier, when the reporter is a student or staff member.
usage_notes:
CEDS "Identifier" elements reflect the intent of the XSD:Token format, i.e. a string in which carriage return, line feed, and tab characters have been removed as well as any internal sequences of two or more spaces and any leading or trailing spaces.

An Identifier MAY be a Universally Unique Identifier (UUID) / Globally Unique Identifier (GUID), i.e.128-bit unique identifiers generated according to the algorithms and encoding standards of RFC 4122.

name: Secondary Incident Behavior
definition: Supplemental information about an incident when the primary offense is more serious in nature than alcohol or drug, etc. offenses.

name: Shortened Expulsion
definition: An expulsion with or without services that is shortened to a term of less than one year by the superintendent or chief administrator of a school district.

name: Weapon Type
definition: Identifies the type of weapon used during an incident.
usage_notes: See Forum Guide to Crime, Violence, and Discipline Incident Data http://nces.ed.gov/pubs2011/2011806.pdf Forum Guide.

name: Ability Grouping Status
definition: An indication of whether the school has students who are ability grouped for classroom instruction in mathematics or English/reading/language arts.
use_case: K-12 -> Civil Rights Data Collection

name: Additional Credit Type
definition: The type of credits or units of value available for the completion of a course in addition to Carnegie Units.

name: Advanced Placement Course Code
definition: Course areas for advanced placement or credit.  For a list of codes see http://apcentral.collegeboard.com/apc/public/courses/teachers_corner/index.html .

name: Available Carnegie Unit Credit
definition: Measured in Carnegie units, the amount of credit available to a student who successfully meets the objectives of the course. A course meeting every day for one period of the school day over the span of a school year offers one Carnegie unit. A Carnegie unit is thus a measure of "seat time" rather than a measure of attainment of the course objectives.
use_case: K-12 -> High School Generated Transcript K-12 -> LEA-to-LEA Student Record Exchange K-12 -> LEA-to-SEA Student Record Exchange K-12 -> Teacher-Student Data Link -> Class Section
format: Numeric - up to 2 digits after decimal place

name: Blended Learning Model Type
definition: A type of formal education program in which a student learns at least in part through online learning, with some element of student control over time, place, path, and/or pace; at least in part in a supervised brick-and-mortar location away from home; and the modalities along each student’s learning path within a course or subject are connected to provide an integrated learning experience.
usage_notes: This may be an attribute of a Course (as designed) or a Class Section (as delivered). It also may be attributed to a school, institution, or program for "whole-school" blended models.

name: Career Cluster
definition: The career cluster that defines the industry or occupational focus which may be associated with a career pathways program, plan of study, or course.
usage_notes: Options from O*NET OnLine an application that was created for the general public to provide broad access to the O*NET database of occupational information. O*NET OnLine offers a variety of search options and occupational data, while My Next Move is a streamlined application for students and job seekers. Both applications were developed for the U.S. Department of Labor by the National Center for O*NET Development.  See onetonline.org for more information.

name: Core Academic Course
definition: The course meets the state definition of a core academic course.

name: Course Aligned with Standards
definition: An indication whether a course is aligned with the established standards of a curriculum framework.

name: Course Applicable Education Level
definition: The education level, grade level or primary instructional level at which a course is intended.
usage_notes: This element is repeatable for most use cases.  Examples: (1.) SCED identifiers may specify a grade span of two or more grades.  (2) A postsecondary course designed to qualify a student for an associates degree and professional certification could be repeated with both of those options.

name: Course Certification Description
definition: A description of the certification or recognition associated with this course (ex. Networking, CAD, etc.)

name: Course Code System
definition: A system that is used to identify the organization of subject matter and related learning experiences provided for the instruction of students.
use_case: K-12 -> High School Generated Transcript K-12 -> LEA-to-LEA Student Record Exchange K-12 -> LEA-to-SEA Student Record Exchange K-12 -> Teacher-Student Data Link -> Class Section

name: Course Credit Units
definition: The type of credit (unit, semester, or quarter) associated with the credit hours earned for the course.
use_case: Postsecondary Education -> Transition

name: Course Department Name
definition: Department with jurisdiction over this course.

name: Course Description
definition: A description of the course content and/or goals. Reference may be made to state or national content standards.

name: Course Funding Program
definition: A program through which the course is funded.
usage_notes: This may be a program targeted to a specific student population (e.g. SPED, ESOL) and the funding guidelines may specify that all or some of the students in the course are members of the subgroup.

name: Course Grade Point Average Applicability
definition: An indicator of whether or not this course being described is included in the computation of the student’s Grade Point Average (GPA).
use_case: K-12 -> High School Generated Transcript K-12 -> LEA-to-LEA Student Record Exchange K-12 -> LEA-to-SEA Student Record Exchange K-12 -> Teacher-Student Data Link -> Class Section

name: Course Identifier
definition: The actual code that identifies the organization of subject matter and related learning experiences provided for the instruction of students.
use_case: K-12 -> High School Generated Transcript K-12 -> LEA-to-LEA Student Record Exchange K-12 -> LEA-to-SEA Student Record Exchange K-12 -> Teacher-Student Data Link -> Class Section Postsecondary Education -> Transition
usage_notes:
CEDS "Identifier" elements reflect the intent of the XSD:Token format, i.e. a string in which carriage return, line feed, and tab characters have been removed as well as any internal sequences of two or more spaces and any leading or trailing spaces.

An Identifier MAY be a Universally Unique Identifier (UUID) / Globally Unique Identifier (GUID), i.e.128-bit unique identifiers generated according to the algorithms and encoding standards of RFC 4122.

name: Course Interaction Mode
definition: The primary type of interaction, synchronous or asynchronous, defined for the course.
usage_notes: This may be an attribute of a Course (as designed) or an instance of a Class Section (as delivered).

name: Course Level Approval Indicator
definition: An indication that there are school or program developed requirements for student participation in the course.
usage_notes: This element is used in conjunction with Course Level Characteristic.

name: Course Level Characteristic
definition: An indication of the general nature and difficulty of instruction provided throughout a course.
use_case: K-12 -> High School Generated Transcript K-12 -> LEA-to-LEA Student Record Exchange K-12 -> LEA-to-SEA Student Record Exchange K-12 -> Teacher-Student Data Link -> Class Section Postsecondary Education -> Transition

name: Course Repeatability Maximum Number
definition: The maximum number of times the course may be taken or completed for credit.

name: Course Subject Abbreviation
definition: The alphabetic abbreviation of the academic department or discipline offering the course. It is one part of the total course identifier number.
use_case: Postsecondary Education -> Transition

name: Course Title
definition: The descriptive name given to a course of study offered in a school or other institution or organization. In departmentalized classes at the elementary, secondary, and postsecondary levels (and for staff development activities), this refers to the name by which a course is identified (e.g., American History, English III). For elementary and other non-departmentalized classes, it refers to any portion of the instruction for which a grade or report is assigned (e.g., reading, composition, spelling, and language arts).
use_case: K-12 -> High School Generated Transcript K-12 -> LEA-to-LEA Student Record Exchange K-12 -> LEA-to-SEA Student Record Exchange K-12 -> Teacher-Student Data Link -> Class Section

name: Credit Value
definition: The amount of credit available to the student who successfully meets the objectives of the course or learning opportunity based on the units defined by Credit Unit Type.
use_case: Postsecondary Education -> Transition
format: Numeric - up to 2 digits after decimal place
usage_notes: For K-12 a course meeting every day for one period of the school day over the span of a school year typically offers one Carnegie unit. In this case a Carnegie unit is  a measure of "seat time" rather than a measure of attainment of the course objectives.

name: Curriculum Framework Type
definition: An indication of the standard curriculum used for this course.

name: Family and Consumer Sciences Course Indicator
definition: An indication that the course is associated with the Family and Consumer Sciences plan of study.

name: High School Course Requirement
definition: An indication that this course credit is required for a high school diploma.
use_case: K-12 -> High School Generated Transcript K-12 -> LEA-to-LEA Student Record Exchange K-12 -> LEA-to-SEA Student Record Exchange K-12 -> Teacher-Student Data Link -> Class Section

name: Instruction Language
definition: The language of instruction, other than English, used in the program or course.
use_case: K-12 -> Consolidated State Performance Report
usage_notes: The CEDS ISO 639-2 Language Code option set comes from the ISO 639-2 standard, the character encoding in ISO 8859-1 download. Discontinued codes from the ISO standard are not included in the CEDS list.

name: Interdisciplinary Indicator
definition: An indication that the course, projects, and/or learning activities develop knowledge and skills across multiple subject areas and highlight connections between subject area domains, with formal collaboration among teachers across subject areas.

name: K12 End of Course Requirement
definition: An indication that this course has an end of course examination required by the SEA or LEA.

name: National Collegiate Athletic Association Eligibility
definition: An indication that the course is approved for determining NCAA eligibility.

name: Project-Based Learning Indicator
definition: An indication that an instructional model is being implemented wherein a student learns through answering complex questions or solving for real-world problems. Also called problem-based learning, inquiry-based learning, or learning-by-doing.

name: Project-Based Learning Type
definition: The type of project-based instruction being offered.
usage_notes: Select all that apply.

name: School Courses for the Exchange of Data Course Code
definition: The five-digit SCED code. The first two-digits of the code represent the Course Subject Area and the next three digits identify the course number. These identifiers are fairly general but provide enough specificity to identify the course's topic and to distinguish it from other courses in that subject area.
usage_notes: https://nces.ed.gov/forum/SCED.asp

name: School Courses for the Exchange of Data Course Level
definition: The course's level of rigor.

name: School Courses for the Exchange of Data Course Subject Area
definition: The intended major subject area of the education course.
usage_notes: This is a compilation of Secondary Course Subject Area and Prior to Secondary Course Subject Area.  This version merges SCED and pSCED.

name: School Courses for the Exchange of Data Grade Span
definition: The grade span for which the course is appropriate.
usage_notes: The span is represented by a four-character code with no decimals.  Each grade level from 1 through 12 is represented by a two-digit code, ranging from 01 to 12; kindergarten is represented by the letters KG and prekindergarten by the letters PK.

name: School Courses for the Exchange of Data Sequence of Course
definition: Where a specific course lies when it is part of a consecutive sequence of courses. This element should be interpreted as "part 'n' of 'm' parts.
use_case: K-12 -> High School Generated Transcript K-12 -> LEA-to-LEA Student Record Exchange K-12 -> LEA-to-SEA Student Record Exchange K-12 -> Teacher-Student Data Link -> Class Section
usage_notes: For example: if a school offers 4 years of Theater, Theater 3 within this school would be indicated in the sequence elements as 3 4, denoting the 3rd part of a 4-part sequence of courses.

name: Tuition Funded
definition: Indicates that tuition for person's participation in a program, service, or course is funded or partially funded by an external grant program.
usage_notes: The initial use case is for professional development courses/programs, but could apply to student programs/courses as well.

name: Work-based Learning Opportunity Type
definition: The type of work-based learning opportunity a student participated in.

name: Additional Targeted Support and Improvement Status
definition: The designation given to a school by the state for additional targeted support and improvement as part of its statewide system of annual meaningful differentiation.

name: Adequate Yearly Progress Appeal Changed Designation
definition: An indication that the appeal resulted in a change in a school or district's AYP designation.
use_case: K-12 -> Consolidated State Performance Report

name: Adequate Yearly Progress Appeal Process Date
definition: The last date that an appeal of an AYP designation was processed.
use_case: K-12 -> Consolidated State Performance Report

name: Adequate Yearly Progress Status
definition: An indication of whether the state, district, or school met the Adequate Yearly Progress (AYP) requirements for the school year, as determined by the state-established criteria.
use_case: K-12 -> EDFacts

name: Alternate Adequate Yearly Progress Approach Indicator
definition: An indication of whether the district or school used an approved alternate approach for calculating Adequate Yearly Progress (AYP).
use_case: K-12 -> EDFacts

name: Appealed Adequate Yearly Progress Designation
definition: An indication that a school or district appealed its AYP designation.
use_case: K-12 -> Consolidated State Performance Report

name: Comprehensive Support and Improvement Status
definition: The designation given to a school by the state for comprehensive support and improvement as part of its statewide system of annual meaningful differentiation.

name: Corrective Action Type
definition: The types of corrective actions under ESEA as amended.
use_case: K-12 -> EDFacts

name: Elementary-Middle Additional Indicator Status
definition: An indication of whether the school or district met the Elementary/Middle Additional Indicator requirement in accordance with state definition for the purpose of determining Adequate Yearly Progress (AYP).
use_case: K-12 -> EDFacts

name: Gun Free Schools Act Reporting Status
definition: An indication of whether the school or local education agency (LEA) submitted a Gun-Free Schools Act (GFSA) of 1994 report to the state, as defined by Title 18, Section 921.
use_case: K-12 -> EDFacts

name: High School Graduation Rate Indicator Status
definition: An indication of whether the school or district met the High School Graduation Rate requirement in accordance with state definition for the purposes of determining AYP.
use_case: K-12 -> EDFacts

name: Participation Status for Math
definition: An indication of whether the school or district met the 95 percent participation requirement in the mathematics assessment in accordance with state definition for the purposes of determining AYP.
use_case: K-12 -> EDFacts

name: Participation Status for Reading and Language Arts
definition: An indication of whether the school or district met the 95 percent participation requirement on the reading/language arts assessment in accordance with state definition for the purposes of determining AYP.
use_case: K-12 -> EDFacts

name: Persistently Dangerous Status
definition: An indication of whether the school is identified as persistently dangerous in accordance with state definition.
use_case: K-12 -> EDFacts

name: Persistently Lowest Achieving School Status
definition: An indication of whether the school is identified by the state as persistently lowest-achieving.
use_case: K-12 -> EDFacts

name: Proficiency Target Status for Math
definition: An indication of whether the school or district met the math proficiency target in accordance with state definition for the purposes of determining AYP.
use_case: K-12 -> EDFacts

name: Proficiency Target Status for Reading and Language Arts
definition: An indication of whether the school or district met the reading/language arts proficiency target in accordance with state definition for the purposes of determining AYP.
use_case: K-12 -> EDFacts

name: Reconstituted Status
definition: An indication that the school was restructured, transformed or otherwise changed as a consequence of the state’s accountability system under ESEA or as a result of School Improvement Grants (SIG).
use_case: K-12 -> EDFacts

name: Restructuring Action
definition: The types of actions being implemented in Title I schools as a result of the school being in an improvement status of restructuring – year 2 (implementation year).
use_case: K-12 -> EDFacts

name: School Improvement Exit Date
definition: Date the school exited school improvement status.
use_case: K-12 -> Consolidated State Performance Report
usage_notes: All CEDS Exit and End Dates represent the last day of the date range specified, such as the last day that a person was enrolled, participated, or received services.

name: School Improvement Funds Status
definition: An indication of whether the school received funds under Section 1003 of ESEA, as amended.
use_case: K-12 -> EDFacts

name: School Year
definition: The year for a reported school session.
use_case: K-12 -> Teacher Compensation Survey
usage_notes: For academic years that span a calendar year this is the four digit year-end.  E.g. 2013 for 2012-2013

name: Targeted Support and Improvement Status
definition: The designation given to a school by the state for targeted support and improvement as part of its statewide system of annual meaningful differentiation.

name: Address Apartment Room or Suite Number
definition: The apartment, room, or suite number of an address.
use_case: Early Learning -> Licensing Early Learning -> Program Compliance Early Learning -> Program Entry Early Learning -> Staff Quality Early Learning -> Workforce Development K-12 -> High School Generated Transcript K-12 -> LEA-to-LEA Student Record Exchange K-12 -> LEA-to-SEA Student Record Exchange Postsecondary Education -> Complete College America Postsecondary Education -> IPEDS

name: Address City
definition: The name of the city in which an address is located.
use_case: Early Learning -> Licensing Early Learning -> Program Compliance Early Learning -> Program Entry Early Learning -> Staff Quality Early Learning -> Workforce Development K-12 -> High School Generated Transcript K-12 -> LEA-to-LEA Student Record Exchange K-12 -> LEA-to-SEA Student Record Exchange Postsecondary Education -> Complete College America Postsecondary Education -> IPEDS

name: Address County Name
definition: The name of the county, parish, borough, or comparable unit (within a state) in which an address is located.
use_case: Early Learning -> Licensing Early Learning -> Program Compliance Early Learning -> Program Entry Early Learning -> Staff Quality Early Learning -> Workforce Development K-12 -> High School Generated Transcript K-12 -> LEA-to-LEA Student Record Exchange K-12 -> LEA-to-SEA Student Record Exchange Postsecondary Education -> Complete College America Postsecondary Education -> IPEDS

name: Address Postal Code
definition: A number that identifies each postal delivery area in the United States used as a portion of an address.
use_case: Early Learning -> Licensing Early Learning -> Program Compliance Early Learning -> Program Entry Early Learning -> Staff Quality Early Learning -> Workforce Development K-12 -> High School Generated Transcript K-12 -> LEA-to-LEA Student Record Exchange K-12 -> LEA-to-SEA Student Record Exchange Postsecondary Education -> Complete College America Postsecondary Education -> IPEDS

name: Address Street Number and Name
definition: The street number and street name or post office box number of an address.
use_case: Early Learning -> Licensing Early Learning -> Program Compliance Early Learning -> Program Entry Early Learning -> Staff Quality Early Learning -> Workforce Development K-12 -> High School Generated Transcript K-12 -> LEA-to-LEA Student Record Exchange K-12 -> LEA-to-SEA Student Record Exchange Postsecondary Education -> Complete College America Postsecondary Education -> IPEDS

name: Address Type for Organization
definition: The type of address listed for an organization.
use_case: K-12 -> High School Generated Transcript K-12 -> LEA-to-LEA Student Record Exchange K-12 -> LEA-to-SEA Student Record Exchange

name: Building Site Number
definition: The number of the building on the site, if more than one building shares the same address.

name: County ANSI Code
definition: County code as defined for the identification of counties and equivalent areas of the United States, Puerto Rico, and the insular areas as established by the American National Standards Institute (ANSI) Inter-National Committee for Information Technology Standards (INCITS) in specification BSR INCITS 31-200x or more current updates. See https://www.census.gov/library/reference/code-lists/ansi.html#par_statelist.

name: Do Not Publish Indicator
definition: An indication that the record should not be published.

name: Latitude
definition: The north or south angular distance from the equator that, when combined with longitude, reflects an estimation of where the address is physically situated.

name: Longitude
definition: The east or west angular distance from the prime meridian that, when combined with latitude, reflects an estimation of where the address is physically situated.

name: State ANSI Code
definition: The American National Standards Institute (ANSI) two-digit code for the state.
use_case: Early Learning -> Staff Quality K-12 -> EDFacts K-12 -> Teacher Compensation Survey

name: State Abbreviation
definition: The abbreviation for the state (within the United States) or outlying area in which an address is located.
use_case: Early Learning -> Licensing Early Learning -> Program Compliance Early Learning -> Program Entry Early Learning -> Staff Quality Early Learning -> Workforce Development K-12 -> High School Feedback Report K-12 -> High School Generated Transcript K-12 -> LEA-to-LEA Student Record Exchange K-12 -> LEA-to-SEA Student Record Exchange K-12 -> Teacher Compensation Survey Postsecondary Education -> Complete College America Postsecondary Education -> IPEDS Postsecondary Education -> Transition

name: Administrative Funding Control
definition: The type of education institution as classified by its funding source.

name: Advanced Placement Course Self Selection
definition: An indication of whether enrollment via self-selection by the student is permitted for all Advanced Placement (AP) courses offered.
use_case: K-12 -> Civil Rights Data Collection

name: Alternative School Focus Type
definition: An indication of the specific group of students whose needs the alternative school is designed to meet.
use_case: K-12 -> Civil Rights Data Collection

name: Blended Learning Model Type
definition: A type of formal education program in which a student learns at least in part through online learning, with some element of student control over time, place, path, and/or pace; at least in part in a supervised brick-and-mortar location away from home; and the modalities along each student’s learning path within a course or subject are connected to provide an integrated learning experience.
usage_notes: This may be an attribute of a Course (as designed) or a Class Section (as delivered). It also may be attributed to a school, institution, or program for "whole-school" blended models.

name: Charter School Approval Year
definition: The school year in which a charter school was initially approved.

name: Charter School Contract Approval Date
definition: The effective date of the contract (or charter) that an approved charter school authorizer authorized the charter school to operate in the state under the state's charter school legislation.
use_case: K-12 -> EDFacts

name: Charter School Contract Id Number
definition: The unique number the SEA assigns to the contract (or charter) that authorizes the charter school to operate in the state under the state's charter school legislation.
use_case: K-12 -> EDFacts

name: Charter School Contract Renewal Date
definition: The date by which the charter school must renew its contract (or charter) with an approved charter school authorizer in order to continue to operate in the state under the state's charter school legislation.
use_case: K-12 -> EDFacts

name: Charter School Indicator
definition: An indication that a public school provides free public elementary and/or secondary education to eligible students under a specific charter executed, pursuant to a state charter school law, by an authorized chartering agency/authority and that is designated by such authority to be a public charter school.
use_case: K-12 -> High School Generated Transcript K-12 -> LEA-to-LEA Student Record Exchange K-12 -> LEA-to-SEA Student Record Exchange
usage_notes: When the element is used for an LEA, it means the LEA is a Charter District meaning any and all schools under the authority of the LEA are charter schools. Don't flag an LEA as a charter district if it has a mix of charter schools and non-charter schools.

name: Charter School Open Enrollment Indicator
definition: Indicates that the charter school offers open enrollment.

name: Charter School Type
definition: The category of charter school.

name: Enrollment Capacity
definition: Maximum number of age-appropriate students who can be enrolled.
usage_notes: Enrollment capacity can be collected at a variety of levels, such as classroom, grade, school, and facility.

name: Grade Levels Approved
definition: The specific grade or combination of grades approved by an organization to be offered by an education institution.

name: Grades Offered
definition: The specific grade or combination of grades offered by an education institution.
use_case: K-12 -> High School Generated Transcript K-12 -> LEA-to-LEA Student Record Exchange K-12 -> LEA-to-SEA Student Record Exchange

name: Interdisciplinary Indicator
definition: An indication that the course, projects, and/or learning activities develop knowledge and skills across multiple subject areas and highlight connections between subject area domains, with formal collaboration among teachers across subject areas.

name: Internet Access
definition: The type of internet access available.
use_case: K-12 -> EDFacts

name: Magnet or Special Program Emphasis School
definition: A school that has been designed: 1) to attract students of different racial/ethnic backgrounds for the purpose of reducing, preventing, or eliminating racial isolation; and/or 2)to provide an academic or social focus on a particular theme (e.g., science/math, performing arts, gifted/talented, career academy or foreign language).
use_case: K-12 -> High School Generated Transcript K-12 -> LEA-to-LEA Student Record Exchange K-12 -> LEA-to-SEA Student Record Exchange

name: Operational Status Effective Date
definition: The effective date for a change in operational status.
use_case: K-12 -> EDFacts

name: Primary Program Indicator
definition: An indication that the associated program is the primary function of this organization.
usage_notes: This element is used in conjunction with Program Type.

name: Program Type
definition: The system outlining instructional or non-instructional activities and procedures designed to accomplish a predetermined educational objective or set of objectives or to provide support services to a person and/or the community.
use_case: K-12 -> High School Generated Transcript K-12 -> LEA-to-LEA Student Record Exchange K-12 -> LEA-to-SEA Student Record Exchange

name: Progress Achieving English Language Proficiency Indicator Type
definition: The category used to report the school's performance on the progress of achieving the English language proficiency indicator.

name: Progress Achieving English Language Proficiency State Defined Status
definition: The state defined status assigned to the school's performance on the progress of achieving the English language proficiency indicator.

name: Project-Based Learning Indicator
definition: An indication that an instructional model is being implemented wherein a student learns through answering complex questions or solving for real-world problems. Also called problem-based learning, inquiry-based learning, or learning-by-doing.

name: Project-Based Learning Type
definition: The type of project-based instruction being offered.
usage_notes: Select all that apply.

name: School Improvement Status
definition: An indication of the improvement stage of the school.
use_case: K-12 -> EDFacts

name: School Level
definition: An indication of the level of the education institution.

name: School Operational Status
definition: The current status of the school operations, exclusive of scheduled breaks, holidays, or other temporary interruptions.
use_case: K-12 -> EDFacts

name: School Type
definition: The type of education institution as classified by its primary focus.
use_case: K-12 -> High School Generated Transcript K-12 -> LEA-to-LEA Student Record Exchange K-12 -> LEA-to-SEA Student Record Exchange

name: Shared Time Indicator
definition: An indication that a school offers career and technical education or other educational services in which some or all students are enrolled at a separate school of record and attend the shared-time school on a part-time basis.
use_case: K-12 -> EDFacts

name: Virtual Indicator
definition: An indication that a childcare, early education, or early learning program, school, institution, program, or course section focuses primarily on instruction in which children and teachers are separated by time and/or location and interact through the use of computers and/or telecommunications technology.

name: Virtual School Status
definition: An indication of the extent to which a school offers instruction in which students and teachers are separated by time and/or location, and interaction occurs via computers and/or telecommunications technologies.

name: Web Site Address
definition: The Uniform Resource Locator (URL) for the unique address of a Web page.
use_case: K-12 -> EDFacts

name: Charter School Authorizer Type
definition: The type of agency that authorized the establishment or continuation of a charter school.

name: Organization Identification System
definition: A coding scheme that is used for identification and record-keeping purposes by schools, social services, or other agencies to refer to an organization.
use_case: Early Learning -> Program Quality

name: Organization Identifier
definition: A unique number or alphanumeric code assigned to an organization by a school, school system, a state, or other agency or entity.
use_case: Early Learning -> Program Quality
usage_notes:
CEDS "Identifier" elements reflect the intent of the XSD:Token format, i.e. a string in which carriage return, line feed, and tab characters have been removed as well as any internal sequences of two or more spaces and any leading or trailing spaces.

An Identifier MAY be a Universally Unique Identifier (UUID) / Globally Unique Identifier (GUID), i.e.128-bit unique identifiers generated according to the algorithms and encoding standards of RFC 4122.

name: Charter School Management Organization Type
definition: The type of organization that is a separate legal entity that 1) contracts with one or more charter schools to manage, operate, and oversee the charter schools; or 2) holds a charter, or charters, to operate multiple charter schools.
use_case: K-12 -> EDFacts

name: Organization Identification System
definition: A coding scheme that is used for identification and record-keeping purposes by schools, social services, or other agencies to refer to an organization.
use_case: Early Learning -> Program Quality

name: Organization Identifier
definition: A unique number or alphanumeric code assigned to an organization by a school, school system, a state, or other agency or entity.
use_case: Early Learning -> Program Quality
usage_notes:
CEDS "Identifier" elements reflect the intent of the XSD:Token format, i.e. a string in which carriage return, line feed, and tab characters have been removed as well as any internal sequences of two or more spaces and any leading or trailing spaces.

An Identifier MAY be a Universally Unique Identifier (UUID) / Globally Unique Identifier (GUID), i.e.128-bit unique identifiers generated according to the algorithms and encoding standards of RFC 4122.

name: Consolidated Migrant Education Program Funds Status
definition: An indication of whether the school has a school-wide program, as defined by current law, in which federal Migrant Education Program (MEP) funds are consolidated.
use_case: K-12 -> EDFacts

name: Federal Program Code
definition: The unique five-digit number assigned to each federal program as listed in the Assistance Listings. See https://sam.gov/content/assistance-listings
use_case: K-12 -> EDFacts
format: Numeric - up to 2 digits before and 3 digits after decimal place

name: Federal Programs Funding Allocation
definition: The amount of federal dollars distributed to local education agencies (LEAs), retained by the state education agency (SEA) for program administration or other approved state-level activities (including unallocated, transferred to another state agency, or distributed to entities other than LEAs).
use_case: K-12 -> EDFacts
format: Numeric - up to 2 digits after decimal place

name: Funds Transfer Amount
definition: The total amount of FY appropriated funds transferred from and to each eligible program.
use_case: K-12 -> Consolidated State Performance Report
format: Numeric - up to 2 digits after decimal place

name: Innovative Dollars Spent
definition: The total Title V, Part A funds expended by LEAs.
use_case: K-12 -> Consolidated State Performance Report
format: Numeric - up to 2 digits after decimal place

name: Innovative Dollars Spent on Strategic Priorities
definition: The total amount of Title V, Part A funds expended by LEAs for the four strategic priorities.
use_case: K-12 -> Consolidated State Performance Report
format: Numeric - up to 2 digits after decimal place

name: Innovative Programs Funds Received
definition: The total Title V, Part A funds received by LEAs.
use_case: K-12 -> Consolidated State Performance Report
format: Numeric - up to 2 digits after decimal place

name: Public School Choice Funds Spent
definition: The dollar amount spent on transportation for public school choice during the school year under Title I of ESEA as amended, Part A, Section 1116.
use_case: K-12 -> EDFacts
format: Numeric - up to 2 digits after decimal place

name: School Improvement Allocation
definition: The amount of Section 1003(a) and 1003(g) allocations to LEAs and Schools.
use_case: K-12 -> Consolidated State Performance Report
format: Numeric - up to 2 digits after decimal place

name: School Improvement Grant Intervention Type
definition: The type of intervention used by the school under the School Improvement Grant (SIG).
use_case: K-12 -> EDFacts

name: School Improvement Reserved Funds Percentage
definition: An indication of the percentage of the Title I, Part A allocation that the SEA reserved in accordance with Section 1003(a) of ESEA and §200.100(a) of ED's regulations governing the reservation of funds for school improvement under Section 1003(a) of ESEA.
use_case: K-12 -> Consolidated State Performance Report
format: Numeric - up to 3 digits before and 2 digits after decimal place

name: Supplemental Education Services Public School Choice Twenty Percent Obligation
definition: The dollar amount of the 20 percent reservation for supplemental educational services and choice-related transportation.
use_case: K-12 -> EDFacts
format: Numeric - up to 2 digits after decimal place
alternate_name: SES Public School Choice Twenty Percent Obligation

name: Supplemental Educational Services Funds Spent
definition: The dollar amount spent on supplemental educational services during the school year under Title I, Part A, Section 1116 of ESEA as amended.
use_case: K-12 -> EDFacts
format: Numeric - up to 2 digits after decimal place

name: Supplemental Educational Services Per Pupil Expenditure
definition: The maximum dollar amount that may be spent per child for expenditures related to supplemental educational services under Title I of the ESEA.
use_case: K-12 -> EDFacts
format: Numeric - up to 2 digits after decimal place

name: Type of Use of the Rural Low-Income Schools Program
definition: The type of use of the Rural Low-Income Schools Program (RLIS) (Title VI, Part B, Subpart 2) Grant Funds.
use_case: K-12 -> Consolidated State Performance Report
alternate_name: Type of Use of the RLIS Program

name: Federal Program Subgrant Code
definition: An additional code appended to the Federal Program Code used to identify a subgrant of the grant identified by the Federal Program Code.

name: Financial Account Balance Sheet Code
definition: Balance sheet accounts and statement of net position accounts are used to track financial transactions for each fund. Such financial statements only report assets, deferred outflows of resources, liabilities, deferred inflows of resources, and equity accounts and are considered "snapshots" of how these accounts stand as of a certain point in time.
usage_notes: Based on codes specified in the NCES Handbook "Financial Accounting for Local and State School Systems: 2014 Edition".

name: Financial Account Category
definition: A label for a grouping of financial accounts, based on type and purpose.

name: Financial Account Coding System Organization Type
definition: The type of organization that created the coding system for the financial account information.

name: Financial Account Description
definition: The description for the financial account in an organization's accounting system.

name: Financial Account Fund Classification
definition: A fund is a separate fiscal and accounting entity with a self-balancing set of accounts recording cash and other financial resources, together with all related liabilities and residual equities or balances or changes therein.
usage_notes: Based on codes specified in the NCES Handbook "Financial Accounting for Local and State School Systems: 2014 Edition".

name: Financial Account Local Balance Sheet Code
definition: A local code used to describe balance sheet accounts and statement of net position accounts which are used to track financial transactions for each fund. Such financial statements only report assets, deferred outflows of resources, liabilities, deferred inflows of resources, and equity accounts and are considered "snapshots" of how these accounts stand as of a certain point in time.

name: Financial Account Local Fund Classification
definition: A local code used to classify a fund which is a separate fiscal and accounting entity with a self-balancing set of accounts recording cash and other financial resources, together with all related liabilities and residual equities or balances or changes therein.

name: Financial Account Local Program Code
definition: A local code used to describe a plan of activities and procedures designed to accomplish a predetermined objective or set of objectives.

name: Financial Account Local Revenue Code
definition: A local code used to record revenue and other receivables by source.

name: Financial Account Name
definition: The name given to the financial account in an organization's accounting system.

name: Financial Account Number
definition: A number given to a financial account within a local source accounting system. The number may be a concatenation of a standard  prefix for the type of account with digits added that have specific meaning within the local system.

name: Financial Account Program Code
definition: A program is a plan of activities and procedures designed to accomplish a predetermined objective or set of objectives. The program classification provides the organization with a framework to classify instructional and other expenditures by program to determine cost.
usage_notes: Based on codes specified in the NCES Handbook "Financial Accounting for Local and State School Systems: 2014 Edition".

name: Financial Account Program Name
definition: The name given to the program area in an organization's accounting system.

name: Financial Account Program Number
definition: A number given to a program area within an organization's accounting system.

name: Financial Account Revenue Code
definition: These codes are for recording revenue and other receivables by source.  Major revenue categories have codes ending in 00 and are further subdivided.
usage_notes:
Based on codes specified in the NCES Handbook "Financial Accounting for Local and State School Systems: 2014 Edition".

Early Learning: If related to an "in kind" contribution use codes 1920 or 100.

name: Financial Accounting Date
definition: The date of a financial transaction or when an account balance is reported.

name: Financial Accounting Period Actual Value
definition: The actual value of a financial account for the specified accounting period or fiscal year.
format: Numeric - up to 2 digits after decimal place

name: Financial Accounting Period Budgeted Value
definition: The budgeted value of a financial account for the specified accounting period or fiscal year.
format: Numeric - up to 2 digits after decimal place

name: Financial Accounting Period Encumbered Value
definition: The planned or obligated expense value of a financial account for the specified accounting period or fiscal year.
format: Numeric - up to 2 digits after decimal place
usage_notes: Used for purchase order balances, the value not already included in "Financial Accounting Period Actual Value" as an expense.

name: Financial Accounting Value
definition: The value of a financial account balance or transaction.
format: Numeric - up to 2 digits after decimal place
usage_notes: Used to represent a point-in-time transaction or snapshot of an account/fund balance. Use “Financial Accounting Period Budgeted Value”, “Financial Accounting Period Actual Value”, and “Financial Accounting Period Encumbered Value” for values representing a period (with begin and end dates).

name: Financial Expenditure Function Code
definition: The function describes the activity for which a service or material object is acquired. The functions of an organization are classified into five broad areas: instruction, support services, operation of non-instructional services, facilities acquisition and construction, and debt service. Functions are further classified into sub functions.
usage_notes: Based on codes specified in the NCES Handbook "Financial Accounting for Local and State School Systems: 2014 Edition".

name: Financial Expenditure Level of Instruction Code
definition: This classification permits expenditures to be segregated by instructional level.
usage_notes: Based on codes specified in the NCES Handbook "Financial Accounting for Local and State School Systems: 2014 Edition".

name: Financial Expenditure Local Function Code
definition: A local code used to describe the activity for which a service or material object is acquired.

name: Financial Expenditure Local Level of Instruction Code
definition: A local code used to classify the segregation of expenditures by instructional level.

name: Financial Expenditure Local Object Code
definition: A local code used to describe the service or commodity obtained as the result of a specific expenditure.

name: Financial Expenditure Object Code
definition: This classification is used to describe the service or commodity obtained as the result of a specific expenditure.  Nine major object categories have codes ending in 00 and are further subdivided.
usage_notes: Based on codes specified in the NCES Handbook "Financial Accounting for Local and State School Systems: 2014 Edition".

name: Financial Expenditure Project Reporting Code
definition: The project/reporting code permits organizations to accumulate expenditures to meet a variety of specialized reporting requirements at the local, state, and federal levels. It is a three-digit code with the format 00X. The first two digits identify the particular funding source, authority, or expenditure purpose for which a special record or report is required. The third digit is available to identify particular projects and the fiscal year of the appropriation within that funding source. Each classification is presented by a code range followed by a description.
usage_notes:
Based on the following code conventions specified in the NCES Handbook "Financial Accounting for Local and State School Systems: 2014 Edition":

010 to 190 Local Projects. Expenditures that require specialized reporting and are funded from local sources.

200 to 390 State Projects. Expenditures that require specialized reporting for categorically funded state programs.

400 to 990 Federal Projects. Expenditures that require specialized reporting to the federal government directly or through the state.

1000 Noncategorical. Expenditures that do not require specialized reporting.

name: Fiscal Period Begin Date
definition: The year, month and day on which an accounting period begins.

name: Fiscal Period End Date
definition: The year, month and day on which an accounting period ends.
usage_notes: All CEDS Exit and End Dates represent the last day of the date range specified, such as the last day that a person was enrolled, participated, or received services.

name: Fiscal Year
definition: The year an organization uses for budgeting, accounting, and reporting financials.

name: Name of Institution
definition: The full legally accepted name of the institution.

name: Organization Relationship Type
definition: The nature of one organization’s relationship to another.
usage_notes: Related Body would be used for a use case in which no hierarchy exists, such as a foundation related to a postsecondary institution. Neither organization has authority over the other, but is related to one another.

name: Organization Type
definition: The type of educational organization or entity.
usage_notes: This element is used in data models that are normalized and identifies the primary role of the organization.

name: School Identification System
definition: A coding scheme that is used for identification and record-keeping purposes by schools, social services, or other agencies to refer to an institution.

name: School Identifier
definition: A unique number or alphanumeric code assigned to an institution by a school, school system, a state, or other agency or entity.
use_case: K-12 -> High School Feedback Report K-12 -> High School Generated Transcript K-12 -> LEA-to-LEA Student Record Exchange K-12 -> LEA-to-SEA Student Record Exchange K-12 -> Teacher Compensation Survey K-12 -> Teacher-Student Data Link -> Class Section Postsecondary Education -> Transition
usage_notes:
CEDS "Identifier" elements reflect the intent of the XSD:Token format, i.e. a string in which carriage return, line feed, and tab characters have been removed as well as any internal sequences of two or more spaces and any leading or trailing spaces.

An Identifier MAY be a Universally Unique Identifier (UUID) / Globally Unique Identifier (GUID), i.e.128-bit unique identifiers generated according to the algorithms and encoding standards of RFC 4122.

name: Short Name of Organization
definition: The name of the organization, which could be abbreviated form of the full legally accepted name.
usage_notes: An abbreviated name of an institution is commonly used, especially in reports and applications, e.g. a K12 school with the full legal name "Dr. Martin Luther King, Jr. Elementary School" may use "King Elementary".

name: Ability Grouping Status
definition: An indication of whether the school has students who are ability grouped for classroom instruction in mathematics or English/reading/language arts.
use_case: K-12 -> Civil Rights Data Collection

name: Accreditation Agency Name
definition: The full name of an agency that accredited a school.

name: Accreditation Award Date
definition: The year, month and day when an accreditation was awarded.
use_case: Early Learning -> Program Quality

name: Accreditation Expiration Date
definition: The year, month and day when an accreditation expires.
use_case: Early Learning -> Program Quality

name: Increased Learning Time Type
definition: The types of increased learning time provided.
use_case: K-12 -> EDFacts
usage_notes: If your data is granular enough to differentiate between Before School and After School, it is recommended those options be selected over using the combined Before or After School option.

name: National School Lunch Program Status
definition: The classification of participation by a school in the National School Lunch Program.

name: Program Gifted Eligibility Criteria
definition: State/local code used to determine a student's eligibility for Gifted/Talented program.

name: State Poverty Designation
definition: The designation of a school’s poverty quartile for purposes of determining classes taught by highly qualified teachers in high and low poverty schools, according to state’s indicator of poverty.
use_case: K-12 -> EDFacts

name: Student Support Service Availability Type
definition: The group of students to whom related or ancillary service is offered within the formal educational system or by an outside agency which provides non-instructional service to support the general welfare of students.

name: Student Support Service Type
definition: Type of related or ancillary services offered or provided to a person or a group of persons within the formal educational system or by an outside agency which provides non-instructional services to support the general welfare of students. This includes physical and emotional health, the ability to select an appropriate course of study, admission to appropriate educational programs, and the ability to adjust to and remain in school through the completion of programs. In serving a student with an identified disability, related services include developmental, corrective, or supportive services required to ensure that the person benefits from special education.
usage_notes: At the organization level, this element indicates the services offered to students. At the person level, this element indicates the services received by students.

name: Title I Program Type
definition: The type of Title I program offered in the school or district.
use_case: K-12 -> EDFacts

name: Title I School Status
definition: An indication that a school is designated under state and federal regulations as being eligible for participation in programs authorized by Title I of ESEA as amended and whether it has a Title I program.
use_case: K-12 -> EDFacts

name: Title III Language Instruction Program Type
definition: The type of Title III language instructional education programs.
use_case: K-12 -> Consolidated State Performance Report

name: Days in Session
definition: The total number of days that the school was or is anticipated to be in session during the school year. Also included are days on which the education institution facility is closed and the student body as a whole is engaged in planned activities off-campus under the guidance and direction of staff members.
format: Integer - greater than or equal to 0

name: Enrollment Capacity
definition: Maximum number of age-appropriate students who can be enrolled.
usage_notes: Enrollment capacity can be collected at a variety of levels, such as classroom, grade, school, and facility.

name: First Instruction Date
definition: The year, month and day of the first day of student instruction for the school year.

name: Instructional Minutes
definition: The total number of instruction minutes in a given session, as determined by time in class, time on task (e.g., engaged in a class), or as estimated by a qualified course designer.
format: Integer - greater than or equal to 0

name: Last Instruction Date
definition: The year, month and day of the last day of student instruction (including days or times that students are present for purposes of testing and/or evaluation, but not including whole or part-days whose sole purposes is for distribution of report cards).

name: Minutes Per Day
definition: The number of minutes in the day in which the school is normally in session.
format: Integer - greater than or equal to 0

name: School Year
definition: The year for a reported school session.
use_case: K-12 -> Teacher Compensation Survey
usage_notes: For academic years that span a calendar year this is the four digit year-end.  E.g. 2013 for 2012-2013

name: School Year Minutes
definition: The number of minutes that all students were required to be at school and any additional learning time (e.g., before or after school, weekend school, summer school) for which all students had the opportunity to participate.
use_case: K-12 -> EDFacts
format: Integer - greater than or equal to 0

name: Session Attendance Term Indicator
definition: Indicates that the session is an attendance term.

name: Session Begin Date
definition: The year, month and day on which a session begins.
use_case: K-12 -> High School Generated Transcript K-12 -> LEA-to-LEA Student Record Exchange K-12 -> LEA-to-SEA Student Record Exchange K-12 -> Teacher-Student Data Link -> Class Section

name: Session Code
definition: A local code given to the session, usually for a session that represents a term within the school year such as a marking term.

name: Session Description
definition: A short description of the Session.

name: Session Designator
definition: The academic session for which the data are recorded and applicable.
use_case: K-12 -> High School Feedback Report Postsecondary Education -> Transition

name: Session End Date
definition: The year, month and day on which a session ends.
use_case: K-12 -> High School Generated Transcript K-12 -> LEA-to-LEA Student Record Exchange K-12 -> LEA-to-SEA Student Record Exchange K-12 -> Teacher-Student Data Link -> Class Section
usage_notes: All CEDS Exit and End Dates represent the last day of the date range specified, such as the last day that a person was enrolled, participated, or received services.

name: Session Marking Term Indicator
definition: Indicates that the session is a marking term.

name: Session Scheduling Term Indicator
definition: Indicates that the session is a scheduling term.

name: Session Type
definition: A prescribed span of time when an education institution is open, instruction is provided, and students are under the direction and guidance of teachers and/or education institution administration. A session may be interrupted by one or more vacations.
use_case: K-12 -> High School Generated Transcript K-12 -> LEA-to-LEA Student Record Exchange K-12 -> LEA-to-SEA Student Record Exchange K-12 -> Teacher-Student Data Link -> Class Section

name: Technical Assistance Approved Indicator
