name: Federal Program Subgrant Code
definition: An additional code appended to the Federal Program Code used to identify a subgrant of the grant identified by the Federal Program Code.

name: Financial Account Balance Sheet Code
definition: Balance sheet accounts and statement of net position accounts are used to track financial transactions for each fund. Such financial statements only report assets, deferred outflows of resources, liabilities, deferred inflows of resources, and equity accounts and are considered "snapshots" of how these accounts stand as of a certain point in time.
usage_notes: Based on codes specified in the NCES Handbook "Financial Accounting for Local and State School Systems: 2014 Edition".

name: Financial Account Category
definition: A label for a grouping of financial accounts, based on type and purpose.

name: Financial Account Coding System Organization Type
definition: The type of organization that created the coding system for the financial account information.

name: Financial Account Description
definition: The description for the financial account in an organization's accounting system.

name: Financial Account Fund Classification
definition: A fund is a separate fiscal and accounting entity with a self-balancing set of accounts recording cash and other financial resources, together with all related liabilities and residual equities or balances or changes therein.
usage_notes: Based on codes specified in the NCES Handbook "Financial Accounting for Local and State School Systems: 2014 Edition".

name: Financial Account Local Balance Sheet Code
definition: A local code used to describe balance sheet accounts and statement of net position accounts which are used to track financial transactions for each fund. Such financial statements only report assets, deferred outflows of resources, liabilities, deferred inflows of resources, and equity accounts and are considered "snapshots" of how these accounts stand as of a certain point in time.

name: Financial Account Local Fund Classification
definition: A local code used to classify a fund which is a separate fiscal and accounting entity with a self-balancing set of accounts recording cash and other financial resources, together with all related liabilities and residual equities or balances or changes therein.

name: Financial Account Local Program Code
definition: A local code used to describe a plan of activities and procedures designed to accomplish a predetermined objective or set of objectives.

name: Financial Account Local Revenue Code
definition: A local code used to record revenue and other receivables by source.

name: Financial Account Name
definition: The name given to the financial account in an organization's accounting system.

name: Financial Account Number
definition: A number given to a financial account within a local source accounting system. The number may be a concatenation of a standard  prefix for the type of account with digits added that have specific meaning within the local system.

name: Financial Account Program Code
definition: A program is a plan of activities and procedures designed to accomplish a predetermined objective or set of objectives. The program classification provides the organization with a framework to classify instructional and other expenditures by program to determine cost.
usage_notes: Based on codes specified in the NCES Handbook "Financial Accounting for Local and State School Systems: 2014 Edition".

name: Financial Account Program Name
definition: The name given to the program area in an organization's accounting system.

name: Financial Account Program Number
definition: A number given to a program area within an organization's accounting system.

name: Financial Account Revenue Code
definition: These codes are for recording revenue and other receivables by source.  Major revenue categories have codes ending in 00 and are further subdivided.
usage_notes:
Based on codes specified in the NCES Handbook "Financial Accounting for Local and State School Systems: 2014 Edition".

Early Learning: If related to an "in kind" contribution use codes 1920 or 100.

name: Financial Accounting Date
definition: The date of a financial transaction or when an account balance is reported.

name: Financial Accounting Period Actual Value
definition: The actual value of a financial account for the specified accounting period or fiscal year.
format: Numeric - up to 2 digits after decimal place

name: Financial Accounting Period Budgeted Value
definition: The budgeted value of a financial account for the specified accounting period or fiscal year.
format: Numeric - up to 2 digits after decimal place

name: Financial Accounting Period Encumbered Value
definition: The planned or obligated expense value of a financial account for the specified accounting period or fiscal year.
format: Numeric - up to 2 digits after decimal place
usage_notes: Used for purchase order balances, the value not already included in "Financial Accounting Period Actual Value" as an expense.

name: Financial Accounting Value
definition: The value of a financial account balance or transaction.
format: Numeric - up to 2 digits after decimal place
usage_notes: Used to represent a point-in-time transaction or snapshot of an account/fund balance. Use “Financial Accounting Period Budgeted Value”, “Financial Accounting Period Actual Value”, and “Financial Accounting Period Encumbered Value” for values representing a period (with begin and end dates).

name: Financial Expenditure Function Code
definition: The function describes the activity for which a service or material object is acquired. The functions of an organization are classified into five broad areas: instruction, support services, operation of non-instructional services, facilities acquisition and construction, and debt service. Functions are further classified into sub functions.
usage_notes: Based on codes specified in the NCES Handbook "Financial Accounting for Local and State School Systems: 2014 Edition".

name: Financial Expenditure Level of Instruction Code
definition: This classification permits expenditures to be segregated by instructional level.
usage_notes: Based on codes specified in the NCES Handbook "Financial Accounting for Local and State School Systems: 2014 Edition".

name: Financial Expenditure Local Function Code
definition: A local code used to describe the activity for which a service or material object is acquired.

name: Financial Expenditure Local Level of Instruction Code
definition: A local code used to classify the segregation of expenditures by instructional level.

name: Financial Expenditure Local Object Code
definition: A local code used to describe the service or commodity obtained as the result of a specific expenditure.

name: Financial Expenditure Object Code
definition: This classification is used to describe the service or commodity obtained as the result of a specific expenditure.  Nine major object categories have codes ending in 00 and are further subdivided.
usage_notes: Based on codes specified in the NCES Handbook "Financial Accounting for Local and State School Systems: 2014 Edition".

name: Financial Expenditure Project Reporting Code
definition: The project/reporting code permits organizations to accumulate expenditures to meet a variety of specialized reporting requirements at the local, state, and federal levels. It is a three-digit code with the format 00X. The first two digits identify the particular funding source, authority, or expenditure purpose for which a special record or report is required. The third digit is available to identify particular projects and the fiscal year of the appropriation within that funding source. Each classification is presented by a code range followed by a description.
usage_notes:
Based on the following code conventions specified in the NCES Handbook "Financial Accounting for Local and State School Systems: 2014 Edition":

010 to 190 Local Projects. Expenditures that require specialized reporting and are funded from local sources.

200 to 390 State Projects. Expenditures that require specialized reporting for categorically funded state programs.

400 to 990 Federal Projects. Expenditures that require specialized reporting to the federal government directly or through the state.

1000 Noncategorical. Expenditures that do not require specialized reporting.

name: Fiscal Period Begin Date

name: Fiscal Period End Date

name: Fiscal Year

name: Insurance Deductible

name: Public Education Mill Rate

name: Integrated Technology Status

name: Interscholastic Sport Participants - Female Only
definition: The number of female students who participated on an interscholastic team.  A student should be counted once for each team she was on.
format: Integer - greater than or equal to 0

name: Interscholastic Sport Participants - Male Only
definition: The number of male students who participated on an interscholastic team.  A student should be counted once for each team he was on.

name: Interscholastic Sports - Female Only

name: Financial Account Balance Sheet Code
definition: Balance sheet accounts and statement of net position accounts are used to track financial transactions for each fund. Such financial statements only report assets, deferred outflows of resources, liabilities, deferred inflows of resources, and equity accounts and are considered "snapshots" of how these accounts stand as of a certain point in time.
usage_notes: Based on codes specified in the NCES Handbook "Financial Accounting for Local and State School Systems: 2014 Edition".

name: Financial Account Category
definition: A label for a grouping of financial accounts, based on type and purpose.

name: Financial Account Description
definition: The description for the financial account in an organization's accounting system.

name: Financial Account Fund Classification
definition: A fund is a separate fiscal and accounting entity with a self-balancing set of accounts recording cash and other financial resources, together with all related liabilities and residual equities or balances or changes therein.
usage_notes: Based on codes specified in the NCES Handbook "Financial Accounting for Local and State School Systems: 2014 Edition".

name: Financial Account Name
definition: The name given to the financial account in an organization's accounting system.

name: Financial Account Number
definition: A number given to a financial account within a local source accounting system. The number may be a concatenation of a standard  prefix for the type of account with digits added that have specific meaning within the local system.

name: Financial Account Program Code
definition: A program is a plan of activities and procedures designed to accomplish a predetermined objective or set of objectives. The program classification provides the organization with a framework to classify instructional and other expenditures by program to determine cost.
usage_notes: Based on codes specified in the NCES Handbook "Financial Accounting for Local and State School Systems: 2014 Edition".

name: Financial Account Program Name
definition: The name given to the program area in an organization's accounting system.

name: Financial Account Program Number
definition: A number given to a program area within an organization's accounting system.

name: Financial Account Revenue Code
definition: These codes are for recording revenue and other receivables by source.  Major revenue categories have codes ending in 00 and are further subdivided.
usage_notes:
Based on codes specified in the NCES Handbook "Financial Accounting for Local and State School Systems: 2014 Edition".

Early Learning: If related to an "in kind" contribution use codes 1920 or 100.

name: Financial Accounting Date
definition: The date of a financial transaction or when an account balance is reported.

name: Financial Accounting Period Actual Value
definition: The actual value of a financial account for the specified accounting period or fiscal year.
format: Numeric - up to 2 digits after decimal place

name: Financial Accounting Period Budgeted Value
definition: The budgeted value of a financial account for the specified accounting period or fiscal year.
format: Numeric - up to 2 digits after decimal place

name: Financial Accounting Period Encumbered Value
definition: The planned or obligated expense value of a financial account for the specified accounting period or fiscal year.
format: Numeric - up to 2 digits after decimal place
usage_notes: Used for purchase order balances, the value not already included in "Financial Accounting Period Actual Value" as an expense.

name: Financial Accounting Value
definition: The value of a financial account balance or transaction.
format: Numeric - up to 2 digits after decimal place
usage_notes: Used to represent a point-in-time transaction or snapshot of an account/fund balance. Use “Financial Accounting Period Budgeted Value”, “Financial Accounting Period Actual Value”, and “Financial Accounting Period Encumbered Value” for values representing a period (with begin and end dates).

name: Financial Expenditure Function Code
definition: The function describes the activity for which a service or material object is acquired. The functions of an organization are classified into five broad areas: instruction, support services, operation of non-instructional services, facilities acquisition and construction, and debt service. Functions are further classified into sub functions.
usage_notes: Based on codes specified in the NCES Handbook "Financial Accounting for Local and State School Systems: 2014 Edition".

name: Financial Expenditure Level of Instruction Code
definition: This classification permits expenditures to be segregated by instructional level.
usage_notes: Based on codes specified in the NCES Handbook "Financial Accounting for Local and State School Systems: 2014 Edition".

name: Financial Expenditure Object Code
definition: This classification is used to describe the service or commodity obtained as the result of a specific expenditure.  Nine major object categories have codes ending in 00 and are further subdivided.
usage_notes: Based on codes specified in the NCES Handbook "Financial Accounting for Local and State School Systems: 2014 Edition".

name: Financial Expenditure Project Reporting Code
definition: The project/reporting code permits organizations to accumulate expenditures to meet a variety of specialized reporting requirements at the local, state, and federal levels. It is a three-digit code with the format 00X. The first two digits identify the particular funding source, authority, or expenditure purpose for which a special record or report is required. The third digit is available to identify particular projects and the fiscal year of the appropriation within that funding source. Each classification is presented by a code range followed by a description.
usage_notes:
Based on the following code conventions specified in the NCES Handbook "Financial Accounting for Local and State School Systems: 2014 Edition":

010 to 190 Local Projects. Expenditures that require specialized reporting and are funded from local sources.

200 to 390 State Projects. Expenditures that require specialized reporting for categorically funded state programs.

400 to 990 Federal Projects. Expenditures that require specialized reporting to the federal government directly or through the state.

1000 Noncategorical. Expenditures that do not require specialized reporting.

name: Fiscal Period Begin Date
definition: The year, month and day on which an accounting period begins.

name: Fiscal Period End Date
definition: The year, month and day on which an accounting period ends.
usage_notes: All CEDS Exit and End Dates represent the last day of the date range specified, such as the last day that a person was enrolled, participated, or received services.

name: Fiscal Year
definition: The year an organization uses for budgeting, accounting, and reporting financials.

name: Competency Set Completion Criteria
definition: The criteria for the set of competencies that represent completion or partial completion of a unit, course, program, degree, certification, or other achievement/award. Specifies whether completion requires achievement of all items in the set or some number of items.
usage_notes: The criteria may be ‘all’ competencies in the set or ‘at-least’ # of competencies. Sets may be nested, e.g. all in subset A and 3 of 5 from subset B.

name: Competency Set Completion Criteria Threshold
definition: The minimum number of competencies in the set that must be achieved for completion or partial completion of a unit, course, program, degree, certification, or other achievement/award.
format: Integer - greater than or equal to 0
usage_notes: Used to define the completion criteria when Competency Set Completion Criteria is "At Least".  Not used when Competency Set Completion Criteria is "All".

name: Duration Length in Minutes
definition: The number of minutes in an instance.

name: Frequency of Service
definition: The frequency at which a service is planned to occur or has occurred.
usage_notes: This element is used to describe the planned frequency of services to be delivered and the actual frequency of services delivered.

name: Goal Description
definition: A statement that describes the desired outcomes.

name: Goal Measurement Criterion Metric
definition: A metric used for evaluating achievement of a goal.

name: Goal Success Criteria
definition: One or more statements that describes the criteria used by teachers and students to check for attainment of a goal.

name: Instructional Minutes
definition: The total number of instruction minutes in a given session, as determined by time in class, time on task (e.g., engaged in a class), or as estimated by a qualified course designer.
format: Integer - greater than or equal to 0

definition: Annual date the State receives the Title III allocation from U.S. Department of Education (ED).

definition: The unique five-digit number assigned to each federal program as listed in the Assistance Listings. See https://sam.gov/content/assistance-listings

format: Numeric - up to 2 digits before and 3 digits after decimal place

name: Federal Programs Funding Allocation
definition: The amount of federal dollars distributed to local education agencies (LEAs), retained by the state education agency (SEA) for program administration or other approved state-level activities (including unallocated, transferred to another state agency, or distributed to entities other than LEAs).
use_case: K-12 -> EDFacts
format: Numeric - up to 2 digits after decimal place

name: Federal Programs Funding Allocation Type
definition: The type of federal program funding allocation or distribution made.

name: Number of Days for Title III Subgrants
definition: Average number of days for States receiving Title III funds to make subgrants to subgrantees beginning from July 1 of each year, except under conditions where funds are being withheld.
use_case: K-12 -> Consolidated State Performance Report
format: Numeric - up to 2 digits after decimal place

name: State Transferability of Funds
definition: Did the State transfer funds under the State Transferability authority of Section 6123(a)
use_case: K-12 -> Consolidated State Performance Report

name: Financial Account Balance Sheet Code
definition: Balance sheet accounts and statement of net position accounts are used to track financial transactions for each fund. Such financial statements only report assets, deferred outflows of resources, liabilities, deferred inflows of resources, and equity accounts and are considered "snapshots" of how these accounts stand as of a certain point in time.
usage_notes: Based on codes specified in the NCES Handbook "Financial Accounting for Local and State School Systems: 2014 Edition".

name: Financial Account Category
definition: A label for a grouping of financial accounts, based on type and purpose.

name: Financial Account Description
definition: The description for the financial account in an organization's accounting system.

name: Financial Account Fund Classification
definition: A fund is a separate fiscal and accounting entity with a self-balancing set of accounts recording cash and other financial resources, together with all related liabilities and residual equities or balances or changes therein.
usage_notes: Based on codes specified in the NCES Handbook "Financial Accounting for Local and State School Systems: 2014 Edition".

name: Financial Account Name
definition: The name given to the financial account in an organization's accounting system.

name: Financial Account Number
definition: A number given to a financial account within a local source accounting system. The number may be a concatenation of a standard  prefix for the type of account with digits added that have specific meaning within the local system.

name: Financial Account Program Code
definition: A program is a plan of activities and procedures designed to accomplish a predetermined objective or set of objectives. The program classification provides the organization with a framework to classify instructional and other expenditures by program to determine cost.
usage_notes: Based on codes specified in the NCES Handbook "Financial Accounting for Local and State School Systems: 2014 Edition".

name: Financial Account Program Name
definition: The name given to the program area in an organization's accounting system.

name: Financial Account Program Number
definition: A number given to a program area within an organization's accounting system.

name: Financial Account Revenue Code
definition: These codes are for recording revenue and other receivables by source.  Major revenue categories have codes ending in 00 and are further subdivided.
usage_notes:
Based on codes specified in the NCES Handbook "Financial Accounting for Local and State School Systems: 2014 Edition".

Early Learning: If related to an "in kind" contribution use codes 1920 or 100.

name: Financial Accounting Date
definition: The date of a financial transaction or when an account balance is reported.

name: Financial Accounting Period Actual Value
definition: The actual value of a financial account for the specified accounting period or fiscal year.
format: Numeric - up to 2 digits after decimal place

name: Financial Accounting Period Budgeted Value
definition: The budgeted value of a financial account for the specified accounting period or fiscal year.
format: Numeric - up to 2 digits after decimal place

name: Financial Accounting Period Encumbered Value
definition: The planned or obligated expense value of a financial account for the specified accounting period or fiscal year.
format: Numeric - up to 2 digits after decimal place
usage_notes: Used for purchase order balances, the value not already included in "Financial Accounting Period Actual Value" as an expense.

name: Financial Accounting Value
definition: The value of a financial account balance or transaction.
format: Numeric - up to 2 digits after decimal place
usage_notes: Used to represent a point-in-time transaction or snapshot of an account/fund balance. Use “Financial Accounting Period Budgeted Value”, “Financial Accounting Period Actual Value”, and “Financial Accounting Period Encumbered Value” for values representing a period (with begin and end dates).

name: Financial Expenditure Function Code
definition: The function describes the activity for which a service or material object is acquired. The functions of an organization are classified into five broad areas: instruction, support services, operation of non-instructional services, facilities acquisition and construction, and debt service. Functions are further classified into sub functions.
usage_notes: Based on codes specified in the NCES Handbook "Financial Accounting for Local and State School Systems: 2014 Edition".

name: Financial Expenditure Level of Instruction Code
definition: This classification permits expenditures to be segregated by instructional level.
usage_notes: Based on codes specified in the NCES Handbook "Financial Accounting for Local and State School Systems: 2014 Edition".

name: Financial Expenditure Object Code
definition: This classification is used to describe the service or commodity obtained as the result of a specific expenditure.  Nine major object categories have codes ending in 00 and are further subdivided.
usage_notes: Based on codes specified in the NCES Handbook "Financial Accounting for Local and State School Systems: 2014 Edition".

name: Financial Expenditure Project Reporting Code
definition: The project/reporting code permits organizations to accumulate expenditures to meet a variety of specialized reporting requirements at the local, state, and federal levels. It is a three-digit code with the format 00X. The first two digits identify the particular funding source, authority, or expenditure purpose for which a special record or report is required. The third digit is available to identify particular projects and the fiscal year of the appropriation within that funding source. Each classification is presented by a code range followed by a description.
usage_notes:
Based on the following code conventions specified in the NCES Handbook "Financial Accounting for Local and State School Systems: 2014 Edition":

010 to 190 Local Projects. Expenditures that require specialized reporting and are funded from local sources.

200 to 390 State Projects. Expenditures that require specialized reporting for categorically funded state programs.

400 to 990 Federal Projects. Expenditures that require specialized reporting to the federal government directly or through the state.

1000 Noncategorical. Expenditures that do not require specialized reporting.

name: Fiscal Period Begin Date
definition: The year, month and day on which an accounting period begins.

name: Fiscal Period End Date
definition: The year, month and day on which an accounting period ends.
usage_notes: All CEDS Exit and End Dates represent the last day of the date range specified, such as the last day that a person was enrolled, participated, or received services.

name: Fiscal Year
definition: The year an organization uses for budgeting, accounting, and reporting financials.

name: Organization Name
definition: The name of a non-person entity such as an organization, institution, agency or business.
use_case: Early Learning -> Staff Quality

name: Organization Relationship Type
definition: The nature of one organization’s relationship to another.
usage_notes: Related Body would be used for a use case in which no hierarchy exists, such as a foundation related to a postsecondary institution. Neither organization has authority over the other, but is related to one another.

name: Organization Type
definition: The type of educational organization or entity.
usage_notes: This element is used in data models that are normalized and identifies the primary role of the organization.

name: State Agency Identification System
definition: A coding scheme that is used for identification and record-keeping purposes to refer to a state agency.

name: State Agency Identifier
definition: A unique number or alphanumeric code assigned to a state agency.
usage_notes:
CEDS "Identifier" elements reflect the intent of the XSD:Token format, i.e. a string in which carriage return, line feed, and tab characters have been removed as well as any internal sequences of two or more spaces and any leading or trailing spaces.

An Identifier MAY be a Universally Unique Identifier (UUID) / Globally Unique Identifier (GUID), i.e.128-bit unique identifiers generated according to the algorithms and encoding standards of RFC 4122.

name: Organization Image URL
definition: The Uniform Resource Locator (URL) for the unique address of an image representing the Organization.

name: Organization Region GeoJSON
definition: The geo-political area of the organization's facility, building, or site.

name: Learning Resource Peer Rating Sample Size
definition: The sample size of a peer rating value. Only used when the Peer Rating Value is collected in aggregate as an average of multiple atomic/individual ratings.
format: Integer - greater than or equal to 0

name: Learning Resource Peer Rating Value
definition: An individual score, rating or level assigned to a Learning Resource by a person within the boundaries set by a Peer Rating System that may be aggregated to derive an overall score for the learning resource.
format: Numeric - up to 4 digits after decimal place

name: Peer Rating Date
definition: The date on which the Peer Rating was entered.

name: Career Cluster
definition: The career cluster that defines the industry or occupational focus which may be associated with a career pathways program, plan of study, or course.
usage_notes: Options from O*NET OnLine an application that was created for the general public to provide broad access to the O*NET database of occupational information. O*NET OnLine offers a variety of search options and occupational data, while My Next Move is a streamlined application for students and job seekers. Both applications were developed for the U.S. Department of Labor by the National Center for O*NET Development.  See onetonline.org for more information.

name: Competency Association Identifier URI
definition: A URI that establishes uniqueness of an association between a competency definition and another competency item or other objects such as learning resources.
alternate_name: Learning Standard Item Association Identifier URI

name: Competency Association Type
definition: Defines the nature of the association between a Competency Definition and an associated data object such as a Learning Resource, an Assessment Item, or even another Competency Definition.
usage_notes:
The Learning Standard Item Association entity defines metadata relationships between a Learning Standard Item and other objects or relationships between Learning Standard Items not otherwise defined in the normal taxonomy of the framework such as for competency-based pathways, relationships between different versions of the same learning standard, and relationships to resources.


For example, "Prerequisite" may indicate that the Associated Learning Standard Item is a Prerequisite of this Learning Standards Item. Another association may specify that a Learning Resource "Teaches" the specified Learning Standard Item, or is aligned to the "Reading Level" specified as part of the Learning Standard Item.

name: Learning Resource Access API Type
definition: Indicates that the learning resource is compatible with the referenced accessibility application programming interface (API).
usage_notes: Options derive primarily from IMS Global's Access for All (AfA) specification, specifically:  apiInteroperable.

name: Learning Resource Access Hazard Type
definition: A characteristic of the described learning resource that is physiologically dangerous to some users.

name: Learning Resource Access Mode Type
definition: An access mode through which the intellectual content of a described learning resource or adaptation is communicated; if adaptations for the resource are known, the access modes of those adaptations are not included.
usage_notes: Options derive primarily from IMS Global's Access for All (AfA) specification, specifically: AccessModeRequired.Type/existingAccessMode.

name: Learning Resource Access Rights URL
definition: A Uniform Resource Locator (URL) that identifies the conditions that govern the user’s ability to access a learning resource.

name: Learning Resource Adaptation URL
definition: The Uniform Resource Locator of a learning resource that is an adaptation for this resource.

name: Learning Resource Adapted From URL
definition: URL identifier of a learning resource for which this resource is an adaptation.

name: Learning Resource Assistive Technologies Compatible Indicator
definition: Indicates that the learning resource is compatible with assistive technologies.
usage_notes: For example, that the resource complies to Web Content Accessibility Guidelines (WCAG) 2.0 checkpoints: 1.1.1, 1.3.1, 1.3.2, 2.4.4, 3.1.1, 3.1.2, 3.3.2, 4.1.1, 4.1.2.

name: Learning Resource Author Email
definition: An email address for the author of the learning resource.

name: Learning Resource Author Type
definition: The type of entity, organization or person, that authored the learning resource.

name: Learning Resource Author URL
definition: A Uniform Resource Locator (URL) attributed to the author of a learning resource.

name: Learning Resource Based on URL
definition: A resource that was used in the creation of this resource. This term can be repeated for multiple sources.
usage_notes: Ex: “http://example.com/great-multiplication-intro.html“

name: Learning Resource Book Format Type
definition: Specifies the format for a learning resource that is a book.  Other options may be considered for inclusion in the option set.

name: Learning Resource Competency Alignment Type
definition: The alignment relationship between the resource and a competency definition object.
usage_notes: A community of SEAs have agreed to use a limited set of Learning Resource Competency Alignment Type options when tagging learning resources in shared resource repositories. Those options are assesses, teaches, and requires.

name: Learning Resource Concept Keyword
definition: The significant topicality of the Learning Resource using free-text keywords and phrases.

name: Learning Resource Control Flexibility Type
definition: Identifies a single input method that is sufficient to control the described learning resource.

name: Learning Resource Copyright Holder Name
definition: The name(s) of the person(s) or organization(s) holding the copyright for the Learning Resource.

name: Learning Resource Copyright Year
definition: The copyright year for the Learning Resource.

name: Learning Resource Creator
definition: The name of a person or organization credited with the creation of the resource.

name: Learning Resource Date Created
definition: The date on which the resource was created.

name: Learning Resource Date Modified
definition: The most recent date that the learning resource was updated.

name: Learning Resource Description
definition: A short description of the Learning Resource.

name: Learning Resource Digital Media Sub Type
definition: The media or file subtype of the digital resource being based on the Media Types and Subtypes, formerly known as MIME types, defined by the Internet Assigned Numbers Authority (IANA).

name: Learning Resource Digital Media Type
definition: The media or file type of the digital resource being based on the media types defined by the Internet Assigned Numbers Authority (AINA) at http://www.iana.org/assignments/media-types.

name: Learning Resource Education Level
definition: The education level, grade level or primary instructional level at which a Learning Resource is intended.

name: Learning Resource Educational Use
definition: The purpose of the work in the context of education.

name: Learning Resource Intended End User Role
definition: The individual or group for which the resource was produced.

name: Learning Resource Interaction Mode
definition: The primary type of interaction, synchronous or asynchronous, defined for the learning resource.

name: Learning Resource Interactivity Type
definition: The predominate mode of learning supported by the learning resource. Acceptable values are active, expositive, or mixed.

name: Learning Resource Language
definition: The primary language of the resource.
usage_notes:
The CEDS ISO 639-2 Language Code option set comes from the ISO 639-2 standard, the character encoding in ISO 8859-1 download. Discontinued codes from the ISO standard are not included in the CEDS list.
Note: For accessible resources LRMI uses language codes from the IETF BCP 47 standard which also refers to ISO 639. (Equivalent of the AfA languageOfAdaptation property.)

name: Learning Resource License URL
definition: The URL where the owner specifies permissions for using the resource.
usage_notes: Ex: “http://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/3.0/“

name: Learning Resource Media Feature Type
definition: Accessible content features included with the learning resource.
usage_notes: Options derive primarily from IMS Global's Access for All (AfA) specification, specifically: AdaptationTypeRequired.Type/adaptationRequest.

name: Learning Resource Physical Media Type
definition: A type of physical media on which the Learning Resource is delivered or available.

name: Learning Resource Publisher Email
definition: An email address for the publisher of the learning resource.

name: Learning Resource Publisher Name
definition: The name of the organization credited with publishing the resource.

name: Learning Resource Publisher URL
definition: A Uniform Resource Locator (URL) attributed to the publisher of a learning resource.

name: Learning Resource Subject Code
definition: The code used to identify the organization of subject matter and related learning experiences addressed by the learning resource.
usage_notes: A promising practice is to use a URL as the Learning Resource Subject Code, that resolves to a web page describing a term in a subject taxonomy.  For example, for "Mathematics", the URL http://id.loc.gov/authorities/classification/BH301.M35.html points to the Library of Congress classification for "Mathematics".  For K12 curriculum "SCED" - School Courses for the Exchange of Data (SCED) may be used, e.g. https://ceds.ed.gov/ScedCourseCodes.aspx#02031 is "Mathematics (grade 1)"

name: Learning Resource Subject Code System
definition: The system that is used to identify the organization of subject matter and related learning experiences addressed by the learning resource.
usage_notes: This may be a URL to a web page describing the subject code system or a name or abbreviation for the system if no authoritative web page exists.  When the associated learning resource Subject Code is a URL, that URL usually provides enough context so that the "Subject Code System" need not be specified.  However, this may be the URL to a page describing the classification system and/or the entry point to the web hosted classification system.  E.g. for the Library of Congress Classification System use: http://id.loc.gov/authorities/classification.html

name: Learning Resource Subject Name
definition: The descriptive name for the subject of the content for the learning resource.

name: Learning Resource Text Complexity System
definition: The scaling system used to specify the text complexity of an Learning Resource

name: Learning Resource Text Complexity Value
definition: The complexity of the text using the scaling system defined by Text Complexity System, e.g. Lexile(tm).

name: Learning Resource Time Required
definition: The approximate or typical time it takes to work with or through this learning resource for the typical intended target audience.

name: Learning Resource Title
definition: The title of the resource.

name: Learning Resource Type
definition: The predominate type or kind characterizing the learning resource.
usage_notes: A community of SEAs have agreed to use a limited set of Learning Resource Type options when tagging learning resources in shared resource repositories. The options defined for this element align with those common tagging specifications.

name: Learning Resource Typical Age Range Maximum
definition: The maximum for the typical range of ages of the content’s intended end user.
format: Integer - greater than or equal to 0

name: Learning Resource Typical Age Range Minimum
definition: The minimum for the typical range of ages of the content’s intended end user.
format: Integer - greater than or equal to 0

name: Learning Resource URL
definition: The Uniform Resource Locator where the resource may be accessed, or a proxy for the resource, such as an information page for a commercially available resource.

name: Learning Resource Version
definition: Defines the version of the learning resource as defined by the publisher.

name: Peer Rating System Maximum Value
definition: The maximum value allowed by the Peer Rating System.
format: Numeric - up to 4 digits after decimal place

name: Peer Rating System Minimum Value
definition: The minimum value allowed by the Peer Rating System.
format: Numeric - up to 4 digits after decimal place

name: Peer Rating System Name
definition: The name of the scaling system used to specify the Peer Rating.

name: Peer Rating System Optimum Value
definition: The optimum value allowed by the Peer Rating System.  The optimum or best rating may be the maximum value, the minimum value, or something in between.
format: Numeric - up to 4 digits after decimal place

name: Agency Course Identifier
definition: The course identifier as it may be recorded at the regional or state level to conform to a standardized course classification system.
usage_notes:
CEDS "Identifier" elements reflect the intent of the XSD:Token format, i.e. a string in which carriage return, line feed, and tab characters have been removed as well as any internal sequences of two or more spaces and any leading or trailing spaces.

An Identifier MAY be a Universally Unique Identifier (UUID) / Globally Unique Identifier (GUID), i.e.128-bit unique identifiers generated according to the algorithms and encoding standards of RFC 4122.

name: Classification of Instructional Program Code
definition: A six-digit code in the form xx.xxxx that identifies instructional program specialties within educational institutions.
use_case: K-12 -> High School Feedback Report Postsecondary Education -> Complete College America Postsecondary Education -> IPEDS Postsecondary Education -> Transition

name: Classification of Instructional Program Version
definition: The version of CIP being reported.
use_case: Postsecondary Education -> Complete College America Postsecondary Education -> IPEDS

name: Course Begin Date
definition: The year, month and day an instance of a course officially began.
use_case: K-12 -> High School Feedback Report Postsecondary Education -> Transition

name: Course Credit Units
definition: The type of credit (unit, semester, or quarter) associated with the credit hours earned for the course.
use_case: Postsecondary Education -> Transition

name: Course End Date
definition: The year, month and day an instance of a course ends.
use_case: K-12 -> High School Feedback Report Postsecondary Education -> Transition
usage_notes: All CEDS Exit and End Dates represent the last day of the date range specified, such as the last day that a person was enrolled, participated, or received services.

name: Course Subject Abbreviation
definition: The alphabetic abbreviation of the academic department or discipline offering the course. It is one part of the total course identifier number.
use_case: Postsecondary Education -> Transition

name: Credit Value
definition: The amount of credit available to the student who successfully meets the objectives of the course or learning opportunity based on the units defined by Credit Unit Type.
use_case: Postsecondary Education -> Transition
format: Numeric - up to 2 digits after decimal place
usage_notes: For K-12 a course meeting every day for one period of the school day over the span of a school year typically offers one Carnegie unit. In this case a Carnegie unit is  a measure of "seat time" rather than a measure of attainment of the course objectives.

name: NCES College Course Map Code
definition: A taxonomy system for coding postsecondary courses in NCES research studies.

name: Postsecondary Course Title
definition: The name or title of the course taken by a student at an academic institution.
use_case: Postsecondary Education -> Transition

name: Course Academic Grade
definition: The final grade awarded for participation in the course.
use_case: K-12 -> High School Feedback Report Postsecondary Education -> Transition

name: Course Add Date
definition: The date an individual was added to an academic course at a school.

name: Course Drop Date
definition: The date on which the individual drops or withdraws from the course.
use_case: Postsecondary Education -> Student Achievement Measure

name: Course Override School
definition: The school where the credit was earned if different from the institution reporting.
use_case: Postsecondary Education -> Transition

name: Course Quality Points Earned
definition: The numerical value assigned to a letter grade to provide a basis of quantitative determination of an average.
use_case: Postsecondary Education -> Transition
format: Numeric - up to 2 digits after decimal place

name: Degree Applicability
definition: An indication that the course is a part of a degree program.
use_case: Postsecondary Education -> Transition

name: Enrollment Capacity
definition: Maximum number of age-appropriate students who can be enrolled.
usage_notes: Enrollment capacity can be collected at a variety of levels, such as classroom, grade, school, and facility.

name: Number of Credits Attempted
definition: The number of credits that a student can earn for enrolling in and completing a given course.
use_case: K-12 -> High School Generated Transcript K-12 -> LEA-to-LEA Student Record Exchange K-12 -> LEA-to-SEA Student Record Exchange
format: Numeric - up to 2 digits after decimal place

name: Number of Credits Earned
definition: The number of credits an individual earns by the successful completion of a course.
use_case: K-12 -> High School Feedback Report K-12 -> High School Generated Transcript K-12 -> LEA-to-LEA Student Record Exchange K-12 -> LEA-to-SEA Student Record Exchange Postsecondary Education -> Transition
format: Numeric - up to 2 digits after decimal place

name: Student Course Section Grade Earned

name: Student Course Section Grade Narrative
definition: The narrative of the student performance in a course section as submitted by the instructor.

name: Grade Value Qualifier
definition: The scale of equivalents, if applicable, for grades awarded as indicators of performance in schoolwork. For example, numerical equivalents for letter grades used in determining a student's Grade Point Average (A=4, B=3, C=2, D=1 in a four-point system) or letter equivalents for percentage grades (90-100%=A, 80-90%=B, etc.)
usage_notes: A list of "Academic Grade Qualifiers" is available from the Association of American Medical Colleges, 2450 N St., N.W., Washington, DC 20037

name: Marking Period Name

name: Mid Term Mark

name: Assignment Start Date

definition: The maximum number of participants that can be served in a program.

definition: Course areas for advanced placement or credit.  For a list of codes see http://apcentral.collegeboard.com/apc/public/courses/teachers_corner/index.html .

name: Course Academic Grade Scale Code
definition: The grading scale used by an academic educational institution for an academic course.
usage_notes: Based on the American Medical Colleges Admissions Services (AMCAS) grade scale, values 01 through 99. See Appendix E of the PESC XML High School Transcript Implementation Guide for a complete list of code values. 3-digit values (500 and above) established in earlier versions of the standard for miscellaneous grades are deprecated.

name: Course Credit Basis Type
definition: The type of enrollment associated with the credit hours for the course.

name: Course Credit Level Type
definition: The level of credit associated with the credit hours earned for the course.

name: Course Grade Point Average Applicability
definition: An indicator of whether or not this course being described is included in the computation of the student’s Grade Point Average (GPA).

name: Course Honors Type
definition: An indication that the course is or can be counted as an honors course.

name: Course Instruction Method
definition: The primary method of instruction used for the course.

name: Course Instruction Site Name
definition: The name of the location at which the course is taught.

name: Course Instruction Site Type
definition: An indication of the type of location at which the course is taught.

name: Course Level Type
definition: The level of work which is reflected in the credits associated with the academic course being described or the level of the typical individual taking the academic course.

name: Course Narrative Explanation Grade
definition: The narrative of the grade awarded to an individual in an academic course in those cases where a course does not receive a letter or numeric grade included in the grading scale of the Course Academic Grade Qualifier.

name: Course Number
definition: The official reference number portion of a course identifier.  This number normally designates the level of the course as well as the level of the individual expected to enroll in the course.

name: Course Repeat Code
definition: Indicates that an academic course has been repeated by a student and how that repeat is to be computed in the student's academic grade average.

name: Course Section Number

usage_notes: First sentence from IPEDS, not CDS; Second sentence from CDS instructions.  All options except "No" should be able to be collapsed into "Yes" for IPEDS reporting.

name: Application Date
definition: The year, month and day on which an individual  application is received by the organization.
use_case: Early Learning -> Program Compliance Early Learning -> Program Entry

name: Grade Point Average Cumulative
definition: A measure of average performance in all courses taken by a person during his or her school career as determined for record-keeping purposes. This is obtained by dividing the total grade points received by the total number of credits attempted. This usually includes grade points received and credits attempted in his or her current school as well as those transferred from schools in which the person was previously enrolled.
use_case: College Readiness K-12 -> High School Feedback Report K-12 -> High School Generated Transcript K-12 -> LEA-to-LEA Student Record Exchange K-12 -> LEA-to-SEA Student Record Exchange Postsecondary Education -> Common Data Set Postsecondary Education -> Transition
format: Numeric - up to 4 digits after decimal place
usage_notes: Related Connection; linked to Grade Point Average Weighted Indicator, High School Percentile, High School Rank, and Size of High School Graduating Class

name: Grade Point Average Domain
definition: The domain to which the Grade Point Average is referencing.
use_case: Postsecondary Education -> Common Data Set
usage_notes: Used to indicate to which academic domain a grade point element is referencing

name: Grade Point Average Weighted Indicator
definition: An indication of whether the reported Grade Point Average is weighted or unweighted.
use_case: Postsecondary Education -> Common Data Set Postsecondary Education -> Transition

name: High School Percentile
definition: The High School Rank divided by the Size of High School Graduating Class expressed as a percentage.
use_case: Postsecondary Education -> Common Data Set
format: Numeric - up to 3 digits before and 2 digits after decimal place
usage_notes:
Related Connection; linked to High School Grade Point Average Cumulative, Grade Point Average Weighted Indicator, High School Rank, and Size of High School Graduating Class
0% to 99% (where 99% corresponds to the valedictorian, 0% to the bottom rank in the class)

name: High School Student Class Rank
definition: The academic rank of a student in relation to his or her high school graduating class (e.g., 1, 2, 3) based on high school GPA.
use_case: K-12 -> High School Generated Transcript K-12 -> LEA-to-LEA Student Record Exchange K-12 -> LEA-to-SEA Student Record Exchange Postsecondary Education -> Common Data Set
format: Integer - greater than or equal to 0

name: Postsecondary Applicant
definition: An individual who has fulfilled the institution’s requirements to be considered for admission (including payment or waiving of the application fee, if any) and who has been notified of one of the following actions: admission, nonadmission, placement on waiting list, or application withdrawn (by applicant or institution). Include early decision, early action, and students who began studies during summer in this cohort.
use_case: Postsecondary Education -> Common Data Set
usage_notes: CDS definition/instructions; first part matches IPEDS

name: Size of High School Graduating Class
definition: The total number of students in the student's high school graduating class.
use_case: K-12 -> High School Generated Transcript K-12 -> LEA-to-LEA Student Record Exchange K-12 -> LEA-to-SEA Student Record Exchange Postsecondary Education -> Common Data Set
format: Integer - greater than or equal to 0

name: Wait Listed Student
definition: A person who meets the admission requirements but will only be offered a place in the class if space becomes available.
use_case: Postsecondary Education -> Common Data Set
usage_notes: Common Data Set definition

name: Accreditation Award Date
definition: The year, month and day when an accreditation was awarded.
use_case: Early Learning -> Program Quality

name: Accreditation Expiration Date
definition: The year, month and day when an accreditation expires.
use_case: Early Learning -> Program Quality

name: Address Apartment Room or Suite Number
definition: The apartment, room, or suite number of an address.

name: Address City
definition: The name of the city in which an address is located.

name: Address County Name
definition: The name of the county, parish, borough, or comparable unit (within a state) in which an address is located.

name: Address Postal Code
definition: A number that identifies each postal delivery area in the United States used as a portion of an address.
